":\"Chinese Piano Prodigy Niu Niu and Conductor Muhai Tang are coming to Shanghai\",\"remark\":\" Piano: Niu Niu (Shengliang Zhang) Chinese Piano Prodigy Niu Niu began studying the piano when he was 3 years old. He held his first recital when he was 6 and was recruited by the primary school attached to the Shanghai Conservatory of Music two years later. He was the youngest student at the time. In his first album in 2008 he played Mozart, in his second in 2010 he played Chopin, and in 2012 it was Liszt.   Conductor: Muhai Tang Tang was chief conductor of the Finnish National Opera and artistic director of Zurich Chamber Orchestra and the Shanghai Concert Hall since 2006. He also teaches at Shanghai Conservatory of Music.   Samuel Barber: Adagio for Strings Samuel Barber: Piano Concerto, Op.38 Edward Elgar: Enigma Variations, Op.36 Edward Elgar: Military Marches (\'Pomp and Circumstance\'), Op.39, No.1 HERE to buy tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/312779f89922a7a68d63a6224baa1d99.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1449818263\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-11\\/299.html\",\"tid\":\"299\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:08\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 26, 2015 |Time=7:30pm|Tickets=680-1280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Gymnasium\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"2015&2016 \\u201CTHE SQUALL\\u201D Rain Asia Tour in Shanghai\",\"ftitle\":\"2015&2016 \\u201CTHE SQUALL\\u201D Rain Asia Tour in Shanghai will be held at Shanghai Grand Stage on Dec.26, 2015. \",\"remark\":\"2015&2016 \\u201CTHE SQUALL\\u201D Rain Asia Tour in Shanghai will be held at Shanghai Grand Stage on Dec.26, 2015. Rain is a South Korean singer-songwriter, actor, and music producer.Rain\'s musical career includes seven albums (six Korean, one Japanese), 28 singles and numerous concert tours around the world.  His acting career began in 2003, when he won the KBS Best New Actor award for his role in the drama Sang Doo! Let\'s Go To School. In 2004, Rain won the KBS Excellence in Acting (Best Actor) award for his role in the drama Full House.  After starring in A Love To Kill, he acted in his first Korean film, I\'m a Cyborg, But That\'s OK (2006), which won the Alfred Bauer Prize at the Berlin International Film Festival. Rain has acted in the American films Speed Racer (2008) and Ninja Assassin (2009), the latter of which made him the first Korean to win an MTV award. Rain acted in another Korean film, R2B: Return to Base, that was released in August 2012. As a precursor to his new album, Rain starred in a reality show Rain Effect which Cube Entertainment stated \\\"You can meet Jung Ji Hoon as a human being.\\\" The show premieres on December 19. The new album, also titled Rain Effect, debuted on January 2, 2014 with music videos for double title tracks, \\\"30 Sexy\\\" and \\\"La Song,\\\" released beforehand. Click HERE to buy tickets.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/ad3f46ee0d43a5ab9a6e00ddc27da21a.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1449647465\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-09\\/298.html\",\"tid\":\"298\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:09\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=January 3, 2016|Time=8pm|Tickets=380-1080 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall - Concert Hall\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"ORF Radio-Symphonie orchester Wien 2016 Shanghai Concert\",\"ftitle\":\"ORF Radio-Symphonie orchester Wien will bring their New Year concert to Shanghai\",\"remark\":\"ORF Vienna Radio Symphony Orchestra   The Vienna RSO is one of the three top orchestras alongside the Philharmonic and Symphoniker. It originated out of the orchestra of Austrian Radio in 1969 for the purpose of presenting contemporary orchestral works. Over the years, the repertoire expanded in different directions.   Conductor: Patrick Lange   ♪ Programme W.A. Mozart: Le nozze di Figaro Overture Antonín Dvořák: Symphony No.8 in G major, Op.88 Franz von Suppé: Light CalvaryOverture Johann Strauss II: KaiserWalzer (Emperor Waltz), Op.437 Gerhard E. Winkler: PussyPolka Johann Strauss II: AnnenPolka, Op.117 Johann Strauss II: Tritsch Tratsch Polka, Op.214   HERE to buy tickets.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7993724fe34b1d914f249b94badcd660.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1449647166\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-09\\/297.html\",\"tid\":\"297\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:10\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 9, 2015-April 7, 2016|Time=10am-9:30pm |Tickets=130-252 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Hongqiao Tiandi Square\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Da Vinci - The Genius Exhibition\",\"ftitle\":\"The exhibition appears at The Hub Pub Performance & Exhibition Center for a limited four-month engagement starting on December 8, 2015 and ending on April 7, 2016.\",\"remark\":\"The exhibition appears at The Hub Pub Performance & Exhibition Center for a limited four-month engagement starting on December 8, 2015 and ending on April 7, 2016.   The interactive experience immerses guests in Leonardo\\u2019s timeless brilliance through full-scale interpretations of the mastermind\\u2019s inventions and unparalleled studies of his iconic art.   Five Hundred Years of Genius Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius demonstrates the full scope of Leonardo da Vinci\\u2019s remarkable genius as a painter, inventor, artist, anatomist, sculptor, engineer, musician and architect. The exhibition features 17 compelling themed areas of Da Vinci\\u2019s work, offering visitors an unmatched look inside the mind of the ultimate Renaissance man who laid the groundwork for some of modern society\\u2019s most impactful inventions, such as the helicopter, airplane, automobile, submarine, parachute and bicycle.   Italian artisans handcrafted all of the inventions brought to life for Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius, using the same techniques and materials from the Renaissance period. Scouring more than 6,000 pages from Da Vinci\\u2019s personal notebooks, the Artisans deciphered hidden clues, intentional mistakes and the unique mirror-image writing system that Da Vinci employed to keep his works top secret.   Visitors of Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius are invited to embrace the history, theory and objective behind each of Da Vinci\\u2019s designs and artworks through engaging and entertaining technologies. Guests will enjoy more than 200 unique pieces including 75 life-size machine inventions, entertaining animations of da Vinci\\u2019s most notable Renaissance works and an eye-opening, in-depth analysis of his most famous piece, \\u201CMona Lisa.\\u201D   Other highlights include reproductions of \\u201CVirgin of the Rocks\\u201D, and \\u201CThe Annunciation\\u201D, the controversial new Leonardo discovery \\u201CBella Principessa\\u201D, amazing anatomical sketches, the preparatory drawings of the \\u201CAnghiari Battle,\\u201D and educational animation presentations of \\u201CThe Last Supper\\u201D, displayed at actual size (29 x 14.5ft) where possible, the \\u201CVitruvian Man,\\u201D and the \\u201CSforza Horse\\u201D sculpture that offer never before seen perspectives on these famous works. Guests also will enjoy a glimpse into da Vinci\\u2019s mysterious alphabet and writing techniques as they browse touch-screen versions of his actual codices.   The Secrets of Mona Lisa \\u2013 Revelaed! \\\"Point a 240 megapixel camera with 13 color filters spanning the infrared, ultraviolet and normally visible spectra at the Mona Lisa, and what do you get? A whole new painting.\\u201D --Brandon Keim, Reporter, Wired Magazine   One highlight of Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius is the Secrets of Mona Lisa exhibit, featuring the findings of French scientific engineer and examiner of fine art, Pascal Cotte. Granted unprecedented access to \\u201CMona Lisa\\u201D by the French government and the Louvre Museum. Cotte was permitted to take \\u201CMona Lisa\\u201D off the wall and out of its frame to conduct a scientific analysis that revealed dozens of secrets about history\\u2019s most elusive art piece, all verified and approved by the Louvre Museum curators over a 2 year period. The exhibit showcases Cotte\\u2019s studies and 25 of his most compelling revelations, illustrated by 40 super-magnified, high-resolution sectional images exploring every aspect of the work.     Scientific Committee and Official Recognitions Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius was created with the assistance of the Museo Leonardo Da Vinci in Rome, Italy, Pascal Cotte of Lumiere Technologies, France, and a number of other experts in Italy and France. It is furthermore under the kind auspices of the City Council of Rome, the City Council of Florence and the City Council of Venice. Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius celebrates one of the most revered and dynamic minds of all time. The exhibition has toured around 55 cities worldwide and attracted more than five million visitors.     Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3fa0c982601180ceac2bd9eabe0432d4.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1449646825\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-09\\/296.html\",\"tid\":\"296\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:10\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Dec 22, 2015 |Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-300 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0464|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Piano Recital by Yulianna Avdeeva\",\"ftitle\":\"Piano Recital by Yulianna Avdeeva is coming to Shanghai\",\"remark\":\"Following her sensational win of the First Prize at the International Fryderyk Chopin Competition 2010 in Warsaw, Yulianna Avdeeva is fast establishing herself as an artist whose performances combine intense musicality and emotional depth with a formidable technique and intellectual rigour. She has performed with Czech Philharmonic, Warsaw Philharmonic Orchestra, Rundfunk-Sinfonieorchester Berlin, Finnish Radio Symphony orchestras, London Philharmonic Orchestra, Pittsburgh Symphony Orchestra, Orchestre Philharmonique Royal de Liège, Polish National Radio Symphony Orchestra, Pacific Symphony, Tchaikovsky Symphony Orchestra of Moscow Radio, Osaka Philharmonic Orchestra, to name just a few. Click HERE to buy tickets.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/54076fd12ae62f404ad0e2ddea820053.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1449043178\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-02\\/294.html\",\"tid\":\"294\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:11\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Dec 29, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-1680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0464|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center Concert Hall\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Czech Philharmonic Shanghai New Year\\u2019s Concert\",\"ftitle\":\" the Czech Philharmonic will bring a New Year\\u2019s Concert to Shanghai\",\"remark\":\"For over a century, the Czech Philharmonic has represented the pinnacle of Czech cultural achievement. In 1896, Dvořák conducted the orchestra\\u2019s debut performance at the Rudolfinum, still home to the orchestra\\u2019s Prague concerts. In 1908, Mahler conducted the Czech Philharmonic for the world premiere of his Symphony No.7. The orchestra\\u2019s reputation grew under Czech conductors Václav Talich, Rafael Kubelík, Karel Ančerl and Václav Neumann. Jiří Bělohlávek became Chief Conductor of the orchestra in 1990. Following his achievements, Gerd Albrecht, Vladimir Ashkenazy, Zdeněk Mácal and Eliahu Inbal took the role. In 2012, Jiří Bělohlávek returns as the orchestra\\u2019s Chief Conductor. Click HERE to buy tickets.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/d9424307ced1f1b002c2580f5ad694df.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1449042921\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-02\\/293.html\",\"tid\":\"293\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:12\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Jan 22, 2016-Jan 23, 2016|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=980-2280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0464|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Riccardo Muti & Chicago Symphony Orchestra\",\"ftitle\":\"Riccardo Muti leads Chicago Symphony Orchestra to Shanghai\",\"remark\":\"Born in Naples, Italy, Riccardo Muti is one of the preeminent conductors of our day. In 2010, when he became the tenth music director of the world-renowned Chicago Symphony Orchestra (CSO), he had more than forty years of experience at the helm of Maggio Musicale Fiorentino (1968\\u20131980), the Philharmonia Orchestra (1972\\u20131982), the Philadelphia Orchestra (1980\\u20131992), and Teatro alla Scala (1986\\u20132005), and he has had a close relationship with the Vienna Philharmonic and the Salzburg Festival for more than 45 years.  He is an honorary member of Vienna\\u2019s Gesellschaft der Musikfreunde, the Vienna Hofmusikkapelle, the Vienna Philharmonic, and the Vienna State Opera.   Muti has received innumerable international honors. He is a Cavaliere di Gran Croce of the Italian Republic, Knight Commander of the British Empire, Officer of the French Legion of Honor, Knight of the Grand Cross First Class of the Order of Saint Gregory the Great and a recipient of the German Verdienstkreuz and the Russian Order of Friendship. Muti has also received Israel\\u2019s Wolf Prize for the arts, Sweden\\u2019s Birgit Nilsson Prize, and Spain\\u2019s Prince of Asturias Award. Passionate about teaching young musicians, Muti founded the Luigi Cherubini Youth Orchestra in 2004 and the Riccardo Muti Italian Opera Academy in 2015. Click HERE to buy tickets.  \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/5359200f4038f901425b53af1b934326.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1449042563\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-02\\/292.html\",\"tid\":\"292\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:12\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Jan 9, 2016|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=480-1280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0464|Add=Shanghai International Gymnastics Center, 777 Wuyi Rd \",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Love Radio Victor Wong 2016 Shanghai Concert\",\"ftitle\":\"\",\"remark\":\"Love Radio Victor Wong 2016 Shanghai Concert will be held at Shanghai International Gymnastics Center on Jan.9, 2016. Victor Wong Pin Kuan is a Chinese singer of Malaysian citizenship who has made his name in the Taiwan music scene. He formed a duo group with Michael Wong named Michael & Victor in 1995 when they first started out as singers under Rock Records. On Jan.9, 2016, with the warm love songs, he comes for you. Click HERE to buy tickets.  \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/777d20a81b11afc18d3567d1dfd086d4.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1449041432\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-02\\/291.html\",\"tid\":\"291\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:13\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Dee 31, 2015-Jan 2, 2016|Time=2:30pm, 7:30pm|Tickets=280-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 苗江路800号上海儿童艺术剧场\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Angel-voiced youngsters to serenade local audiences\",\"ftitle\":\"Renowned Italian children\\u2019s choir Piccolo Coro Dell\\u2019Antoniano will perform in Shanghai from December 31 to January 2. \",\"remark\":\"Renowned Italian children\\u2019s choir Piccolo Coro Dell\\u2019Antoniano will perform in Shanghai from December 31 to January 2. The choir was established in 1963, and has since become one of the most famous children\\u2019s choirs in the world \\u2014 as well as a Good Will Ambassador for UNICEF. The group has recorded more than 1,000 songs over a 50-year period, in addition to countless concerts and performances on television and radio. The concerts in Shanghai will be conducted by Sabrina Simoni and last for roughly 90 minutes. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3877cf7597bf0aaa55bacf98c066fe5c.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1447839402\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-18\\/290.html\",\"tid\":\"290\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:13\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Dec 31, 2015|Time=2pm, 7:30pm, 10:30pm|Tickets:80-980 yuan|Phone=021-5386 6666|Add:523 Yan\\\\\'an Rd 延安东路523号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"New Year concert from Vienna\",\"ftitle\":\"Vienna Johann Strauss Capelle will present a New Year concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on December 31.\",\"remark\":\"Vienna Johann Strauss Capelle will present a New Year concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on December 31. The orchestra has given nearly 3,000 concerts since its debut in 1977 in countries such as Spain, Portugal, Italy, the United States, China and Japan. All the musicians wear red jackets and white trousers as their predecessors more than 100 years ago. HERE to buy the tickets.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/d069f0f2b80f2f7ced731bb4af49ceab.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1447839153\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-18\\/289.html\",\"tid\":\"289\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:13\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through January 31, 2016|Time=10:30am-8:30pm|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Global Harbor, 3300 Zhongshan Rd N. 中山北路3300号上海环球港\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Thirty top Picasso pieces on display\",\"ftitle\":\"Pablo Picasso (1881-1973) is an icon in Western modern art history. A special exhibition titled \\u201CThe Legend of Art: Picasso\\u201D is on display at Global Harbor Museum through to January 31, 2016.\",\"remark\":\"Pablo Picasso (1881-1973) is an icon in Western modern art history. A special exhibition titled \\u201CThe Legend of Art: Picasso\\u201D is on display at Global Harbor Museum through to January 31, 2016. As one of the greatest and most influential artists of the 20th century, Picasso, a Spanish painter, sculptor, printmaker, ceramist, stage designer, poet and playwright, spent most of his adult life in France.  He is known for co-founding the Cubist movement. Picasso, Henri Matisse and Marcel Duchamp are regarded as the three artists who most defined the revolutionary developments in arts in the opening decades of the 20th century.  The exhibition features nearly 87 artworks created by Picasso and 81 pictures on loan from a group of private collectors around the world. The art forms vary from canvas, print, sketches to paper cutting, sculpture and porcelain. During the first decade of the 20th century, Picasso\\u2019s style changed as he experimented with different theories, techniques, and ideas. His work is often categorized into periods. While the names of many of his later periods are debated, the most commonly accepted in his work are the Blue Period (1901\\u20131904), the Rose Period (1904\\u20131906), the African-influenced Period (1907\\u20131909), Analytic Cubism (1909\\u20131912), and Synthetic Cubism (1912\\u20131919), also referred to as the Crystal period. Yuexing Group chairman Ding Zuohong said: \\u201CThe exhibition includes nearly 30 important artworks by Picasso, such as \\u2018The Musketeer\\u2019 and \\u2018Melon Slice\\u2019 from his idyllic period and \\u2018Bacchanal with Acrobats\\u2019 from his new classicism period.\\u201D As well as the regular artworks on display, the organizer has developed an opportunity for patrons to fuse illusionary art with realistic art.  Visitors can wear 3D glasses to appreciate the masterpieces of Picasso from six different periods. It will also be fun to take your own photo and develop it into a \\u201CCubism\\u201D period picture.   HERE to buy the tickets.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3e553ef83edb1b7481ed0986bb2fb12c.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1446802570\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-06\\/288.html\",\"tid\":\"288\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:13\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 14-15, 2015|Time=10:30am, 7:30pm|Tickets=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theatre, 800 Miaojiang Rd 苗江路800号，上海儿童艺术剧院\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Joja Wendt plans concerts in Shanghai\",\"ftitle\":\"In 1990, pianist Joja Wendt joined Joe Cocker\\u2019s world tour. \",\"remark\":\"In 1990, pianist Joja Wendt joined Joe Cocker\\u2019s world tour. After several collaborations with famous artists, Wendt began to focus more on his own recitals. His style is a mix of jazz, classical music, ballads and rock. A recipient of the renowned Louis-Armstrong Award, Wendt was the top ticket selling artist in Germany among pianists. Furthermore, he presents his music in a very humorous and creative way. His strong stage presence and interaction with the audience are key factors in his success. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f9b40a6c1e090db97f8ed122e6a9ee00.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1446800592\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-06\\/287.html\",\"tid\":\"287\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:13\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 28-29, 2015|Time=10:20am, 2:30pm|Tickets=180 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=800 Miaojiang Rd, Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theatre 苗江路800号上海儿童艺术剧场\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Tiny figurines come to life in magical children\\u2019s play\",\"ftitle\":\"\\u201CA Mano\\u201D is a play told with small figurines fashioned out  of plasticine, like the ones children often make. \",\"remark\":\"\\u201CA Mano\\u201D is a play told with small figurines fashioned out  of plasticine, like the ones children often make. The play tells a story of friendship on a temporary stage barricaded with furniture. With movements set to the music of Edith Piaf, the tiny characters first appear, then interact, then get to know each other and eventually forge ties based on small and shared dreams. These subtle exchanges slowly give rise to stronger feelings of caring and friendship. \\u201CA Mano\\u201D is a story brimming with imagination and inventiveness, told with  four hands and presented for the very first time in China. This is a definite must-see!   HERE to buy the tickets.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/de86242c0273f375c1936688d09bb839.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1446633170\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-04\\/286.html\",\"tid\":\"286\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:14\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 20-22, 2015|Time=10:30am, 3pm, 7:30pm|Tickets=280-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1200 Shibo Ave, Mercedes-Benz Arena 世博大道1200号梅赛德斯奔驰文化中心\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Heart-warming fun at \\u2018Magic Ice Festival\\u2019\",\"ftitle\":\"Get ready to enter a world of enchantment featuring the most magical moments from across the land as Disney On Ice presents \\u201CMagical Ice Festival.\\u201D\",\"remark\":\"Get ready to enter a world of enchantment featuring the most magical moments from across the land as Disney On Ice presents \\u201CMagical Ice Festival.\\u201D Audiences be whisked away into the wintery world of Disney\\u2019s Academy-Award winning film \\u201CFrozen,\\u201D to join royal sisters Elsa and Anna, the hilarious snowman Olaf, rugged mountainman Kristoff and his loyal reindeer Sven in a story full of action, adventure, magic and unforgettable characters. HERE to buy the tickets.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/324d9245a54c373cabe5238699af6cd4.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1446633014\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-04\\/285.html\",\"tid\":\"285\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:14\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 3-4, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-300 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=288 Anfu Rd, Shanghai Drama Art Center 安福路288号上海话剧艺术中心\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Indian adaptation of Shakespeare\\u2019s \\u2018Twelfth Night\\u2019\",\"ftitle\":\"In the household of Olivia, two campaigns are being quietly waged \\u2014 one by lovesick Lord Orsino against the heart of the indifferent Olivia.\",\"remark\":\"In the household of Olivia, two campaigns are being quietly waged \\u2014 one by lovesick Lord Orsino against the heart of the indifferent Olivia; the other by an alliance of servants and hangers-on against her steward, the pompous Malvolio. Filled with a cast of unforgettable characters, this Indian adaptation of Shakespeare\\u2019s \\u201CTwelfth Night\\u201D mixes cruelty with high comedy and pangs of unrequited love. The comedy will be presented with Chinese and English subtitles.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/a1609653228c415943a440ea838bae38.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1446199517\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-30\\/284.html\",\"tid\":\"284\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:14\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 15, 2015-January 17, 2016|Time=2pm; 7:15pm|Tickets=200-1280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Culture Square, 36 Yongjia Rd 永嘉路36号上海文化广场\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"War Horse\",\"ftitle\":\"The Chinese version of \\u201CWar Horse\\u201D will be staged at Shanghai Culture Square.\",\"remark\":\"The Chinese version of \\u201CWar Horse\\u201D will be staged at Shanghai Culture Square. It is a play based on the book of the same name by children\'s writer Michael Morpurgo, adapted for stage by Nick Stafford. Its West End and Broadway productions met with critical acclaim and won several awards, including an Olivier Award and five Tony Awards. The Chinese production premiered at Beijing\\u2019s National Theatre Company of China in September and will tour to the theaters in Shanghai. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/aebc78736df91a8271fb5002b1ba87dd.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1446199395\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-30\\/283.html\",\"tid\":\"283\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:14\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 13-14, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=180-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People Ave. 人民大道300号上海大剧院\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Modern dance examines meaning of life\",\"ftitle\":\"Life, conceived within fragile bodies, exists in a fierce world. To fight against the tide or be carried along with it, choices tend to play tricks  with our minds.\",\"remark\":\"Life, conceived within fragile bodies, exists in a fierce world. To fight against the tide or be carried along with it, choices tend to play tricks  with our minds. But as long as the soul is free from binding, we can always find our way. As some might say, life is a battle field and one needs to fight back like a tiger to move forward. D.LAB will present the modern dance \\u201CFragile\\u201D at Shanghai Grand Theater. The group\\u2019s ides about dancing  transcend body movements. They consider all types of artistic expression integrated with music, performance, video and sound, painting and art to add value to any dance. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4bc395e4e5491e3b4ba1d3f93ce75477.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1445593181\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-23\\/282.html\",\"tid\":\"282\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:14\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 13, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=180-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Musicians to celebrate victory against Japan with concert\",\"ftitle\":\"Pianist Gong Tianpeng, conductor Zhang Liang, violist Liu Xiao and the Shanghai Opera House chorus will present a concert that celebrates the 70th anniversary of victory in the War of Resistance against Japanese Aggression at Shanghai Symphony Hall on December 13. \",\"remark\":\"Pianist Gong Tianpeng, conductor Zhang Liang, violist Liu Xiao and the Shanghai Opera House chorus will present a concert that celebrates the 70th anniversary of victory in the War of Resistance against Japanese Aggression at Shanghai Symphony Hall on December 13.  Described by The Washington Post as an artist \\u201Cwith the confidence of a weathered veteran and a welcome unbridled quality to his playing,\\u201D Gong has established himself as one of the most gifted musicians of his generation. At 18, Gong has become an internationally active concert pianist and a six-time American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers National Award-winning composer since 2006. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/efa2e597778dd9eca9bbe101765dc5b3.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1445593016\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-23\\/281.html\",\"tid\":\"281\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:14\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 18-20， 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"\\\\\'Seven Young Goats and the Wolf\\u2019\",\"ftitle\":\"Adapted from the classic Grimms\\u2019 fairy tale into an easily digestible and educational stage play, \",\"remark\":\"Adapted from the classic Grimms\\u2019 fairy tale into an easily digestible and educational stage play, the \\u201CSeven Young Goats and the Wolf\\u201D features adorable puppet costumes, gorgeous stage effects, melodious songs and refined performances. This lively story teaches children how to identify risks, to avoid being cheated and to protect themselves from being harmed. Children will learn the immensity of maternal love and the power that courage can bring. The play also tells children the importance of getting along with others and respecting those with different values. Children will quickly be drawn in by this compelling story. \\\\ \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7ecdd23ba4cc815b06350c2ccf703c91.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1445332688\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-20\\/280.html\",\"tid\":\"280\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:15\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 28， 2015|Time=7:45pm|Tickets=180-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Fleishers to play Brahms, Debussy and Schubert\",\"ftitle\":\"American pianist and conductor Leon Fleisher and Katherine Jacobson Fleisher will give a concert at the Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 28.\",\"remark\":\"American pianist and conductor Leon Fleisher and Katherine Jacobson Fleisher will give a concert at the Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 28. Those attending can expect to hear Johannes Brahms\\u2019 \\u201CLiebesliederWaltzer, Op. 52a 20,\\u2019\\u201D Claude Debussy\\u2019s \\u201CLa Puerta del Vino from Préludes, Book II 4,\\u201D and Franz Schubert \\u2019s \\u201CFantasy in F minor for piano four-hands, D. 940 20.\\u201D Leon Fleisher was born in San Francisco into a poor Jewish family and started studying the piano at age four. He made his public debut at age eight and played with the New York Philharmonic under Pierre Monteux at the age of 16. Monteux famously called him \\u201Cthe pianistic find of the century.\\u201D \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/cbae391066ad2bf8c1a37cc04301add7.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1445332480\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-20\\/279.html\",\"tid\":\"279\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:15\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 31, 2015|Time=7:45pm|Tickets=280-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall, 1380 Fuxing Rd M. 复兴中路1380号，上海交响乐团音乐厅\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Bostridge at Shanghai Symphony Hall\",\"ftitle\":\"The acclaimed tenor Ian Bostridge will perform with guitarist Yang Xuefei at Shanghai Symphony Hall on October 31.\",\"remark\":\"The acclaimed tenor Ian Bostridge will perform with guitarist Yang Xuefei at Shanghai Symphony Hall on October 31. Songs include Dominick Argento\\u2019s \\u201CLetters from Composers,\\u201D John Dowland\\u2019s \\u201CIn Darkness Let Me Dwell\\u201D and Franz Schubert\\u2019s \\u201CDie Mainacht, D.194.\\u201D Bostridge was a post-doctoral fellow in history at Corpus Christi College, Oxford, before embarking on a full-time career as a singer. He has performed at some of the world\\u2019s major concert halls and at festivals in Salzburg, Edinburgh, Munich and Vienna. He made his operatic debut in 1994 as Lysander in Britten\\u2019s \\u201CA Midsummer Night\\u2019s Dream\\u201D with Opera Australia at the Edinburgh Festival. In 1999, he premiered a songcycle written for him by Hans Werner Henze. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/40bf7b71492855ba33189ec64142a4f3.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1444990325\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-16\\/277.html\",\"tid\":\"277\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:15\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 16-18, 2015|Time=11am,5pm,7:30pm,11pm|Tickets:80-680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"World\\u2019s longest opera coming to Shanghai\",\"ftitle\":\"\\u201CDer Ring des Nibelungen\\u201D is the longest opera in the world. It consists of four parts including Das Rheingold, Die Walküre, Siegfried and Gotterdammerung.\",\"remark\":\"\\u201CDer Ring des Nibelungen\\u201D is the longest opera in the world. It consists of four parts including Das Rheingold, Die Walküre, Siegfried and Gotterdammerung. The complete 24-hour Ring cycle was launched by Gustav Kuhn at the Tirol Festival in 2003. Since then, as Kuhn\\u2019s reading has both broadened and deepened, this opera has also been improved and the work as a whole has a more integrated feel than ever before. The opera was written by Richard Wagner over a period of 24 years.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/0e4bd03b5361afb13b9bb34b921ddded.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1444730255\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-13\\/275.html\",\"tid\":\"275\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:15\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 18, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Phone=021-5292 0164|Venue=Shanghai Culture Square\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Dance legend Guillem presents \\u2018Life in Progress\\u2019\",\"ftitle\":\"Famous dancer Sylvie Guillem will present her final dance program, \\u201CLife in Progress,\\u201D a Sadler \\\\\'s Wells London Production co-produced with Les Nuits de Fourvière, China Shanghai International Arts Festival and Guillem.\",\"remark\":\"Famous dancer Sylvie Guillem will present her final dance program, \\u201CLife in Progress,\\u201D a Sadler \'s Wells London Production co-produced with Les Nuits de Fourvière, China Shanghai International Arts Festival and Guillem. She will dance two new works including Technê, a solo choreographed by Sacred Monsters\\u2019creator Akram Khan and Here & After, a duet with Italian dancer Emanuela Montanari from La Scala. Guillem, a world famous dancer with an extensive career at the Paris Opera Ballet, has diversified as a dancer forging an undisputable reputation as a major force in the world of contemporary dance. Her awards include an Olivier award, a Golden Lion for Lifetime Achievement by the Venice Biennale, the Officier de la Légion d\\u2019Honneur, Commandeur dans l\\u2019Ordre National du Mérite, Officier des Arts et Lettres, and, in Britain, an honorary CBE.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!  \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/ccc90e7dd969e09f17a445833460d92d.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1444730011\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-13\\/274.html\",\"tid\":\"274\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:15\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 3-4, 2015|Add=Binjiang Greenland in Xuhui District 徐汇滨江绿地\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"2015 Storm Electronic Music Festival\",\"ftitle\":\"The 2015 Storm Electronic Music Festival, the largest outdoor electronic dance music festival in China, will be staged on October 3 and 4 at Binjiang Greenland. \",\"remark\":\"The 2015 Storm Electronic Music Festival, the largest outdoor electronic dance music festival in China, will be staged on October 3 and 4 at Binjiang Greenland. Scheduled to perform are electronic music heavyweights Tiesto, Skrillex, and Avicii. Tiesto was named \\u201Cthe greatest DJ of all time\\u201D by Mixmag, while Skrillex has won three Grammy Awards. The French Apple Art Festival will also run between September 30 and October 10 at Shanghai Chenshan Botanic Garden. The festival will feature some 1,000 apples decorated with images of the Mona Lisa, the Summer Palace and other scenes.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/8cef4b9004c0beae44a0b9282213c3bc.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1443513538\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-29\\/273.html\",\"tid\":\"273\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:15\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 30-October 7, 2015|Add=Chenshan Botanical Garden, 3888 Chenhua Rd 辰花公路3888号，辰山植物园\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"French Apple Art Festival\",\"ftitle\":\"These apples were cultivated at the Les Jardins Fruitiers de Laquenexy in Moselle, France, using an old but refined technique. As they grew, these apples were covered by black paper cut into different patterns \\u2014 the areas which were not exposed to the sun did not turn red, allowing artistic patterns to emerge in the lighter-colored areas.\",\"remark\":\"These apples were cultivated at the Les Jardins Fruitiers de Laquenexy in Moselle, France, using an old but refined technique. As they grew, these apples were covered by black paper cut into different patterns \\u2014 the areas which were not exposed to the sun did not turn red, allowing artistic patterns to emerge in the lighter-colored areas. According to organizers, out of 1,000 apples this process will only work correctly for four or five. The apples will be available to purchase at prices up to 1,000 yuan (US$161). This is the first time such apples have been displayed outside France. Also on display will be seven large-scale mosaics each made from thousands of different colored apples.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/023f2fe53bebb776379f0c06ee872035.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1443513436\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-29\\/272.html\",\"tid\":\"272\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:15\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 3, 2015|Time=8pm|Tickets=280-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Taiwan Philharmonic\",\"ftitle\":\"Taiwan Philharmonic, led by conductor Shao-Chia Lu and violinist Cho-Liang Lin, will present a concert on November 3 at Shanghai Symphony Hall. \",\"remark\":\"Taiwan Philharmonic, led by conductor Shao-Chia Lu and violinist Cho-Liang Lin, will present a concert on November 3 at Shanghai Symphony Hall. The program includes Huang Ruo\\u2019s \\u201CBecoming Another,\\u201D Tchaikovsky\\u2019s \\u201CViolin Concerto in D major,\\u201D and Rachmaninov\\u2019s Symphony No.2 in E minor. Founded in 1986, the Taiwan Philharmonic has given thousands of concerts, launched many music activities and become one of the top orchestras in Asia. Taiwan Philharmonic works regularly with and internationally acclaimed musicians, such as Lorin Maazel and Rudolf Barshai. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3a41ed5c98c29ad6f6300013acecad4f.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1442913527\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-22\\/271.html\",\"tid\":\"271\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:15\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 7, 2015|Time=7:45pm|Tickets=80-280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add:1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"New Cologne Piano Trio pops by in November\",\"ftitle\":\"The trio will present a concert at Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 7. The Cologne Piano Trio comprises violin soloist Walter Schreiber, cello soloist Joanna Schryn and pianist Xin Sui. \",\"remark\":\"The trio will present a concert at Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 7. The Cologne Piano Trio comprises violin soloist Walter Schreiber, cello soloist Joanna Schryn and pianist Xin Sui. Xin has succeeded Guenter Ludwig, who retired. They have performed many concerts in China. Recently the threesome released their first CD with masterpieces from Ludwig van Beethoven. \\u201CThe idea of our new style is to use our highly developed skills on the instruments paired with virtuosity to give life to the music notes. Tolerance paired with highly emotional expressions is significant for our music,\\u201D they said in a press release. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/604b2640b094dd46d0d92781dc6cdd2b.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1442913271\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-22\\/270.html\",\"tid\":\"270\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:15\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 1, 2015|Time=7:45pm|Tickets=180-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Xu and friends plan special performance\",\"ftitle\":\"Xu Zhong and his friends Ni Haiye, Liu Yunjie, Manuel Kastl and Klaidi Sahatci will perform at Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 1. \",\"remark\":\"Xu Zhong and his friends Ni Haiye, Liu Yunjie, Manuel Kastl and Klaidi Sahatci will perform at Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 1. They will play Schumann\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quintet in E flat Major\\u201D and Shostakovich\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quintet in G minor.\\u201D Xu is one of the most internationally renowned Chinese pianists and conductors. He is the founding member and artistic director of the China Shanghai International Piano Competition, deputy chairman of Shanghai Oriental Art Center Arts Committee. Xu has won prestigious international piano competitions since 1988. He has collaborated with some of the world\\u2019s best musicians and orchestras. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/c38c8efbffc174e467ef65afbc70f467.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1442559617\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-18\\/269.html\",\"tid\":\"269\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:16\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 1-2, 2015|Time=2:30pm, 7:30pm|Tickets=180-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Music from the \\u2018Frozen Plane\\u2019 documentary\",\"ftitle\":\"Shanghai Opera House Orchestra will perform the score from the BBC television series \\u201CFrozen Plane\\u201D about the world\\u2019s polar regions.\",\"remark\":\"Shanghai Opera House Orchestra will perform the score from the BBC television series \\u201CFrozen Plane\\u201D about the world\\u2019s polar regions. The music will be accompanied by the documentary in high-definition. George Fenton composed the score. \\u201CFrozen Planet\\\" documents the melting polar ice and the creatures living that live in these regions. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/14db930118b34ac0bf391716cdfae0a8.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1442559380\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-18\\/268.html\",\"tid\":\"268\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:16\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December24，2015|Time=180-380 yuan|Tickets=180-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Tang, Huang to perform in December\",\"ftitle\":\"To celebrate the 70th anniversary of the victory in World War II, a concert led by conductor Tang Muhai and violist Huang Mengla will be presented at Shanghai Symphony Hall on December 24. \",\"remark\":\"To celebrate the 70th anniversary of the victory in World War II, a concert led by conductor Tang Muhai and violist Huang Mengla will be presented at Shanghai Symphony Hall on December 24. The program includes Aram Khachaturian\\u2019s \\u201CViolin Concerto in D minor\\u201D and Dmitri Shostakovich\\u2019s \\u201CSymphony No. 9 in E-flat major.\\u201D Tang initially learned music with his parents, and later studied composition and conducting at the Shanghai Conservatory of Music, receiving a diploma in both. Tang won a 2002 Grammy Award for Best Classical Contemporary Composition for Christopher Rouse\\u2019s Concert de Gaudí. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/35d8e2513bc030a0db999158c158abee.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1441962497\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-11\\/266.html\",\"tid\":\"266\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:16\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 26, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=180-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Concert Hall, 523 Yan\\\\\'an Rd E. 上海音乐厅， 延安东路523号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Ditto will show some love for Schubert and Brahms\",\"ftitle\":\"The ensemble Ditto will present a concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on September 26. The program includes Schubert\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quintet in A major\\u201D and Brahms\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quartet in G minor.\\u201D\",\"remark\":\"The ensemble Ditto will present a concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on September 26. The program includes Schubert\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quintet in A major\\u201D and Brahms\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quartet in G minor.\\u201D Ditto, formed in 2007, has a legion of fans from teenage girls to women in their thirties. They ranked first in ticket sales at Seoul Arts Center\\u2019s concert hall for the first half of this year. They also ranked first in 2008 and 2009. Ditto first gained fame by performing on a real-time live broadcast concert for the portal site NAVER. They have also held a street concert to reach a broader audience. Another characteristic of the ensemble is that members perform long solos in order to raise the reputation of the group. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/e86cdd425935c0e248462ba90c66c276.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1441961200\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-11\\/265.html\",\"tid\":\"265\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:16\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 7, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=280-880 yuan|Phone+021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Full metal racket\",\"ftitle\":\"For a blast of German Brass, head to Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 7.\",\"remark\":\"For a blast of German Brass, head to Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 7. Founded in 1974 as a brass quintet by Enrique Cresp, German Brass creates \\u201Cdiversity in unity  \\u2014 producing a unique collective sound with 10 individualists and renowned soloists from outstanding German orchestras. They play chamber music but with symphonic magnificence and dynamics that only brass instrumentalists can produce. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3680b45cab33949365615a7f81a0e823.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1440748534\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-28\\/264.html\",\"tid\":\"264\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 4-5，2015|Time=10:30am, 2:30pm|Tickets=180-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"It\\u2019s grrreat!\",\"ftitle\":\"Adapted and directed by David Wood, Judith Kerr\\u2019s Olivier Award nominated \\u201CThe Tiger Who Came to Tea\\u201D is the perfect slice of teatime mayhem, with sing-a-long tunes, oodles of magic and interactive fun for children aged three plus and their families.\",\"remark\":\"Adapted and directed by David Wood, Judith Kerr\\u2019s Olivier Award nominated \\u201CThe Tiger Who Came to Tea\\u201D is the perfect slice of teatime mayhem, with sing-a-long tunes, oodles of magic and interactive fun for children aged three plus and their families. The tiger comes to have afternoon tea? Maybe it sounds incredible. However, in the world of Kerr\\u2019s picture books, it seems very natural. When Sophie and her mummy welcome the hungry tiger to tea, he proceeds to eat all the sandwiches, buns and biscuits \\u2014 and manages to the drink all the water in the tap! And if you\\u2019ve never had a tiger arrive for tea, then this lovable production is the perfect way to show the whole family how to behave the next time you ring the doorbell.  \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/aa0b86649fcd9ff836b2b8cae9592ee9.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1440748321\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-28\\/263.html\",\"tid\":\"263\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:19\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 4-6, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=80-680 yuan|Add=shanghai Grand Theater, 300 Renmin Ave. 上海大剧院 人民大道300号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Endangered ibis inspiration for new dance show\",\"ftitle\":\"The crested ibis \\u2014 with its red face and pink, orange wings \\u2014 has long been appreciated throughout East Asia for its beautiful appearance and as a symbol of good luck and happiness.\",\"remark\":\"The crested ibis \\u2014 with its red face and pink, orange wings \\u2014 has long been appreciated throughout East Asia for its beautiful appearance and as a symbol of good luck and happiness. The bird itself though has not been so lucky. Starting in the early 20th century, urbanization across the region has pushed the species to the brink of extinction. The striking bird and its harrowing story are the subject of a dance drama entitled \\u201CCrested Ibises,\\u201D which is coming to the Shanghai Grand Theater this October. The touring show, presented by Shanghai Dance Theater, was performed in 19 cities across Japan over the summer. The show\\u2019s creator, Chen Feihua, was inspired by video images of the crested ibis shown at the Japan Pavilion during the World Expo Shanghai 2010. \\u201CThey were so elegant and beautiful, just like dancers moving on stage,\\u201D says Chen, who is also the president of Shanghai Dance Theater. After learning about the human efforts to pull the species back from extinction, Chen became even more determined to bring the bird and its story to the stage. In ancient times, the crested ibis was widely seen and admired in both China and Japan. The species began to dwindle in the 20th century as growing cities in both countries lead to habitat loss. The bird was believed to have been wiped out completely in the wild until 1981, when seven crested ibises were spotted in Yangxian County of central China\\u2019s Shaanxi Province. Scientists from China and Japan eventually joined hands to save the crested ibis. With the help of artificial insemination and conservation areas, there are now an estimated 2,000 crested ibises living in China, plus another 200 in Japan. \\u201CWe are not the only residents on this Earth. We should leave living space for other creatures while protecting ours as well,\\u201D says Chen. Work on Chen\\u2019s show was finally completed last year with the help of playwright Luo Huaizhen and director Tong Ruirui. At the beginning of the show, man coexists peacefully with the ibis in a lush natural environment. Later, the bird is shown slowing succumbing to the forces of urbanization. According to Chen, the bird\\u2019s near extinction is represented by a glass cover descending upon the drama\\u2019s main avian protagonist, turning her into a specimen. \\u201CI\\u2019m glad this message is being delivered,\\u201D says Chen. \\u201CI think our success largely lies in the realization that environmental protection is a shared problem facing people all over the world. This has helped pave the way for cross-cultural communication.\\u201D Pulling off dance moves based on the crested ibis was no easy feat, according to Zhu Jiejing, the show\\u2019s lead dancer during its recent tour of Japan. Many of the show\\u2019s moves involve unfamiliar gestures and poses, such as exaggerated forearm movements meant to represent the bird\\u2019s natural movements. \\u201CThis is the first time the crested ibis has been depicted in dance, so we had no available models to learn from. We had to make things distinctive,\\u201D says Zhu. \\u201CThe crested ibis is not dazzling like the peacock and does not have the wide wingspan of the swan. Fragility and sensitivity are the soul of the crested ibis.\\u201D   \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/33fce0f5c93361d3995b4dd7626da442.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1440747884\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-28\\/262.html\",\"tid\":\"262\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:19\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 19|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=280-1280 yuan|Add:Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 Renmin Ave. 上海大剧院 人民大道300号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"WDR Symphony Orchestra Cologne plans big concert\",\"ftitle\":\"WDR Symphony Orchestra Cologne with its conductor Jukka-Pekka Saraste and violinist Frank Peter Zimmermann will present a concert on October 19 at Shanghai Grand Theater. \",\"remark\":\"WDR Symphony Orchestra Cologne with its conductor Jukka-Pekka Saraste and violinist Frank Peter Zimmermann will present a concert on October 19 at Shanghai Grand Theater. The program includes Brahms Violin Concerto and Brahms Symphony No. 4. Existing for more than 65 years, the WDR Symphony Orchestra Cologne is one of the most important broadcast orchestras in Europe. Since the 2010-11 season, Saraste has been the chief conductor of the orchestra. Zimmermann has performed with all major orchestras and many renowned conductors around the world.  \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3b38aa79b536564564850b25dfcd4156.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1440747718\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-28\\/261.html\",\"tid\":\"261\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:20\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 15, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-680 yuan|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd. 上海东方艺术中心,丁香路425号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Mikhail Pletnev to play piano recital in Shanghai\",\"ftitle\":\"Russian pianist Mikhail Pletnev will give a recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 15. He will play Beethoven\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Sonata No. 10\\u201D and \\u201CPiano Sonata No. 17\\u201D and Scriabin\\u2019s \\u201C24 Preludes.\\u201D\",\"remark\":\"Russian pianist Mikhail Pletnev will give a recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 15. He will play Beethoven\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Sonata No. 10\\u201D and \\u201CPiano Sonata No. 17\\u201D and Scriabin\\u2019s \\u201C24 Preludes.\\u201D  Born into a Russian family of musicians, Pletnev went to study at the Moscow Central School of Music at age 13 and won the first prize of the 1978 Tchaikovsky International Piano Competition at age 21. He became international famous overnight and his recordings garnered numerous prizes, including the 2005 Grammy Award. Pletnev is now one of Russia\'s most respected artists. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/631770d4b81c241c37a9b6dd863d1782.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1440576990\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-26\\/260.html\",\"tid\":\"260\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:20\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 4, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=280-480|Add=Shanghai Concert Hall, 523 East Yanan Rd. 延安东路523号，上海音乐厅\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Clarinetist Meyer\\\\\'s solo show\",\"ftitle\":\"Paul Meyer will come to Shanghai and give a concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on September 4. Songs include Claude Debussy\\u2019s \\u201CPremière rapsodie for Clarinet and Piano,\\u201D Leonard Bernstein\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Clarinet and Piano\\u201D and Alban Berg\\u2019s \\u201CFour Pieces for Clarinet and Piano, Op. 5.\\u201D\",\"remark\":\"Paul Meyer will come to Shanghai and give a concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on September 4. Songs include Claude Debussy\\u2019s \\u201CPremière rapsodie for Clarinet and Piano,\\u201D Leonard Bernstein\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Clarinet and Piano\\u201D and Alban Berg\\u2019s \\u201CFour Pieces for Clarinet and Piano, Op. 5.\\u201D Born in 1965, Meyer is recognized as one of the most outstanding clarinet soloists in this era. He made his debut in 1982, at the age of 17, as laureate of the prestigious Eurovision Contest. In 1983, he was appointed principal clarinet with the Orchestre de l\\u2019Opéra National de Lyon, then with the Ensemble intercontemporain in 1984 and with the Opéra de Paris in 1985. He soon left these orchestras to begin an international career as soloist. Simultaneously his passion for conducting led him early on to study with Charles Bruck at the Pierre Monteux school in Maine.     \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f47bff825c292cee8cdae45e059760b2.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1440576453\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-26\\/259.html\",\"tid\":\"259\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:20\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 12, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=480-1280 yuan|Phone=52920164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 丁香路425号 上海东方艺术中心\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Violin Rectial by Itzhak Perlman\",\"ftitle\":\"The Israeli conductor Itzhak Perlman will present the violin recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on November 12. The programs include Leclair\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Violin and Piano in D major\\u201D, Brahms\\u2019s \\u201CSonatensatz in C minor\\u201D and Franck\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Violin and Piano in A Major\\u201D.\",\"remark\":\"    The Israeli conductor Itzhak Perlman will present the violin recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on November 12. The programs include Leclair\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Violin and Piano in D major\\u201D, Brahms\\u2019s \\u201CSonatensatz in C minor\\u201D and Franck\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Violin and Piano in A Major\\u201D. Born in 1945, Perlman started his music life at the age of three and completed his initial training at the Academy of Music in Tel Aviv. He has performed as conductor with every major orchestras and in recitals and festival around the world. Perlam also has been a soloist for a number of film scores such as the theme of the 1993 film Schindler\'s List by John Williams, which subsequently won an Academy Award for Best Original Score. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/dff3477c5f55b77e92a6dd785729186f.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1439883207\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-18\\/258.html\",\"tid\":\"258\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:20\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 26-27, 2015|Time=10:30am, 2:30pm|Tickets=80-380 yuan|Phone=4009215686|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 苗江路800号, 上海儿童艺术剧场\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Fun for children with the dancing Moomins\",\"ftitle\":\"Dancing Moominvalley, a dance production based on Tove Jansson\\u2019s book \\u201CThe Tales from the Moominvalley,\\u201D will be presented at Shanghai Children\\u2019s Theater in September.\",\"remark\":\"Dancing Moominvalley, a dance production based on Tove Jansson\\u2019s book \\u201CThe Tales from the Moominvalley,\\u201D will be presented at Shanghai Children\\u2019s Theater in September.  A visually spectacular, fully composed contemporary dance piece for the whole family, Dancing Moominvalley takes a new approach to the Moomins, but the themes will be familiar to those who have read the books.  \\u201CDancing Moominvalley @ Shanghai Expo\\u201D was presented at Shanghai World Expo 2010. It received a Shanghai Expo 2010 Culture Award, the only such award received by the Finnish Pavilion Culture Program.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4eb1c8e3473636f22426ee1c4d13cc1d.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1439878446\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-18\\/257.html\",\"tid\":\"257\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:20\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 15-17,2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=100-200 yuan|Phone=53866666|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 Renmin Ave. 上海大剧院 人民大道300号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Tiger\\u2019 looks at life of a dysfunctional family\",\"ftitle\":\"UK-Barrowland Ballet will make its Asian debut at Shanghai Grand Theater on September 15.\",\"remark\":\"UK-Barrowland Ballet will make its Asian debut at Shanghai Grand Theater on September 15. \\u201CTiger\\u201D is an incredibly moving piece about a dysfunctional family whose three members, Mom, Dad and their daughter Poppy, have become unable to interact and love each other. Mom spends her day cleaning obsessively, while Dad is buried in his work. Both are too wrapped up in their own worlds to notice their daughter is lonely and unhappy. \\u201CTiger\\u201D takes you on a sensory adventure. Up close to the action the audience surrounds the family\\u2019s home as it is transformed from a sterile space into a shifting world of live sound, color and explosive movement.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4201b7bac166adf29358518528b65ff2.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1439535089\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-14\\/256.html\",\"tid\":\"256\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:20\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 8-October 11|Phone=5033-9801|Add=Shanghai Himalayas Museum, 869 Yinghua Rd 樱花路869号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Dog Designs, kid artists\",\"ftitle\":\"From August 8 to October 11, the Shanghai Himalayas Museum will host an exhibition entitled \\u201CArchi-tecture for Dogs.\\u201D\",\"remark\":\"From August 8 to October 11, the Shanghai Himalayas Museum will host an exhibition entitled \\u201CArchi-tecture for Dogs.\\u201D This whimsical exhibit is curated by famed Japanese designer and MUJI art director Kenya Hara. On view will be 14 doghouses created by some of the world\\u2019s top designers and architectural firms, including Shigeru Ban, Ma Yansong and Altelier Bow-Wow. Launched in 2012, this exhibition hastoured the world and is now returning to the Shanghai Himalayas Mu- seum for the sixth time. \\u201CThis exhibition is not merely about architecture for animals or building houses for dogs. Through this opportunity to re-ob-serve the living environment of dogs, hopefully we can see our own surroundings, and ourselves, in a new way\\u201D. Visitors can also bring their dogs to play in a specially- designed \\u201Cpuppy park\\u201D located outside of the main display area. In addition to this exhibition, the museum is offering art lessons for children between seven and 12 years-of-age. But rather than drilling basic skills such as line drawing or sketching, the museum\\u2019s teachers hope to foster an interest in art and culture among children. Brainstorm- ing is also used to develop storylines and ideas, which are then painted by the students. \\u201CCapturing the same subject or merely copying is very boring. We want the children to gain knowledge while they are painting and to have their own thoughts about their works,\\u201D Wendy Zheng, a project as- sistant with the museum\\u2019s education department.   \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/81a582616c3c4635799fed6095a1cf5d.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1439288131\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-11\\/255.html\",\"tid\":\"255\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:20\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 24-25, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=380-880 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Concerts of BBC Philharmonic\",\"ftitle\":\"Founded in 1934, BBC Philharmonic is famous for its artistic innovation, outstanding performance, and a broad repertoire. \",\"remark\":\"Founded in 1934, BBC Philharmonic is famous for its artistic innovation, outstanding performance, and a broad repertoire. The orchestra has published more than 200 albums with critical acclaims. Its members include conductor Juanjo Menachem, violist Sarah Zhang and cellist Trey Lee. Menachem is one of the most celebrated conductors in Spain. Sarah Zhang, a Korean-American genius, gained fame when she was only 8 and has won many international awards since. She was invited to play in the 90th anniversary concert of the Philadelphia Orchestra. Trey Lee, the first Asian to win a top prize at the prestigious Antonia Janigro Cello Competition, has collaborated with esteemed conductors, composers and orchestras worldwide. He was described by The New York Times as \\u201Cexcellent cellist\\u2026 with enveloping richness and lyrical sensitivity.\\u201D       BBC Philharmonic will present two concerts at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 24-25.   2015\\/10\\/24      BRITTEN | Simple Symphony SIBELIUS | Violin Concerto in d-minor No.47 ELGAR | Enigma Variations 2015\\/10\\/25 GLINKA | Overture to Ruslan and Lyudmila  ELGAR | Cello Concerto in E minor LIQING YANG | Introduction, Chant and 