t Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Surprising MozART\",\"ftitle\":\"MozART group created a musical cabaret, where the music, not the words, are the source of joy and laughter.\",\"remark\":\"MozART group created a musical cabaret, where the music, not the words, are the source of joy and laughter. Taking a classical composition as their canvas, the group analyzes its structure and theme, then surrounds it with musical associations. Listeners are often left surprised and amazed, laughing and sometimes, even moved to tears. The musicians of the MozART group have been playing together since 1995. The quartet has performed with musicians from around the world, including shows with mime Irek Krosny and the multitalented Bobby McFerrin. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4556084238237ed6a9f82a30967ad7f7.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1438677956\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-04\\/252.html\",\"tid\":\"252\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:21\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 23, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Piano recital covers Beethoven and Brahms\",\"ftitle\":\"Sergio Tiempo will give a piano recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 23. The programs include Brahms\\u2019 \\u201CIntermezzo in B minor, Op. 119 No. 1,\\u201D Beethoven\\u2019s \\u201CSonata in F minor, Op. 57,\\u201D and many other classic tunes.\",\"remark\":\"Sergio Tiempo will give a piano recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 23. The programs include Brahms\\u2019 \\u201CIntermezzo in B minor, Op. 119 No. 1,\\u201D Beethoven\\u2019s \\u201CSonata in F minor, Op. 57,\\u201D and many other classic tunes. Born in Caracas, Venezuela, Tiempo began his piano studies with his mother, Lyl Tiempo, at the age of two and made his concert debut when he had just turned three. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/ba03ed27b82b86be940a2367f87b6881.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1438677744\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-04\\/251.html\",\"tid\":\"251\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:22\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 5, 2015|Time:1:30pm, 4pm|Tickets:80-180 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add:Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Wizards, lions and magic\",\"ftitle\":\"This children\\u2019s play is based on \\u201CThe Wizard of the Emerald City\\u201D books by Russian writer Alexander Volkov, who loosely was inspired by the \\u201CThe Wonderful Wizard of Oz\\u201D series. \",\"remark\":\"This children\\u2019s play is based on \\u201CThe Wizard of the Emerald City\\u201D books by Russian writer Alexander Volkov, who loosely was inspired by the \\u201CThe Wonderful Wizard of Oz\\u201D series.    \\u201CEmerald City\\u201D follows Ellie and her friends Totoshka, Iron Lumberjack, Scarecrow, and Lion on a journey to Emerald City, where a place full of magic, unusual inhabitants and wonderful animals await. Ellie and her friends face numerous challenges on the way to Emerald City and learn the importance of kindness, friendship and self-confidence.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/99df2fdd6f945e487158c9a7471adce0.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1438327344\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-31\\/250.html\",\"tid\":\"250\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:22\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 3-4, 2015|Time=10:30am, 2:30pm|Tickets:180 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add:Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs\",\"ftitle\":\"It is a children\\u2019s classic written by the Grimm brothers. The tale unfolds with an evil queen speaking to a magic mirror. She learns that her stepdaughter Snow White is the \\u201Cfairest in the land.\\u201D\",\"remark\":\"It is a children\\u2019s classic written by the Grimm brothers. The tale unfolds with an evil queen speaking to a magic mirror. She learns that her stepdaughter Snow White is the \\u201Cfairest in the land.\\u201D   Infuriated, the stepmother uses her powers to get rid of the girl so she can be the only beautiful woman in her kingdom. Meanwhile, Snow White meets some kind dwarfs in the forest who after become her  friends. Fighting for good, she goes through many breathtaking adventures and finds her true love. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/676dd3ba70ab2330c4fefeb22dd30a2c.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1438327133\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-31\\/249.html\",\"tid\":\"249\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:22\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through August 8, 2015|Time=11am-7pm, closed on Mondays|Add=200 Huayuangang Rd 花园港路200号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Top designer showcases best of British\",\"ftitle\":\"Renowned British designer Thomas Heatherwick, whose work ranges from his beautiful London 2012 Olympic cauldron to the iconic UK Pavilion at the 2010 World Expo Shanghai \\u2014 taking in his update on the iconic red London bus along the way \\u2014 is the subject of a city exhibition.\",\"remark\":\"Renowned British designer Thomas Heatherwick, whose work ranges from his beautiful London 2012 Olympic cauldron to the iconic UK Pavilion at the 2010 World Expo Shanghai \\u2014 taking in his update on the iconic red London bus along the way \\u2014 is the subject of a city exhibition. \\u201CInside Heatherwick Studio,\\u201D currently running at The Power Station of Art, showcases the work of a designer widely considered among Britain\\u2019s most innovative. The touring exhibition organized by the British Council, curated by Kate Goodwin and designed by Heatherwick Studio, aims to offer unique insights into the ideas and experiments that go into realizing projects that span architecture, engineering, furniture, sculpture and product design. It features drawings, models, films and test pieces generated by speculative and built projects from the past 20 years. Established by Thomas Heatherwick in 1994, the London-based Heatherwick Studio has a 170-strong team. Heatherwick says his studio aims to finding innovative design solutions, with a dedication to artistic thinking and the latent potential of materials and craftsmanship in the fields of architecture, urban infrastructure, design and strategic thinking. Outstanding contribution Heatherwick is an Honorary Fellow of the Royal Institute of British Architects and senior Research Fellow at the Victoria and Albert Museum. He was awarded the Prince Philip Designers Prize in 2006 and the London Design Medal in recognition of his outstanding contribution to design in 2010. Exhibition highlights include process models and full-size construction pieces from Heatherwick Studio\\u2019s Learning Hub. This is his project for Nanyang Technological University in Singapore. The form and structure of the hub aim to generate a new learning environment with oval classrooms bringing students and teachers together. Twelve stacks of classrooms, interspersed with gardens, rise around a naturally ventilated central atrium. Also on display is a model of the UK\\u2019s Pavilion for the 2010 World Expo in Shanghai \\u2014 a cube made up of 60,000 7.5 meter acrylic rods. Some 250,000 seeds from Britain\\u2019s Millennium Seed Bank were placed in the end of the rods, creating a magical \\u201Cseed cathedral\\u201D inside. At the close of the Expo, these were distributed across the world. Another highlight is a model and film of the London 2012 Olympic cauldron. The cauldron features 204 copper pieces, one for each of the participating countries, carried in to the stadium by the teams during the opening ceremony.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/93a8d9f6778c3789018cfb1cc2534a73.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1438068713\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-28\\/248.html\",\"tid\":\"248\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:22\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 25, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=160-680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People Ave 人民大道300号上海大剧院\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Three masterpieces\",\"ftitle\":\"Don\\u2019t miss the Australian Ballet as they perform three ballet masterpieces. From classical technique, haunting and emotional storytelling and athletic movement, this mixed program highlights the diverse ability of the dancers as they bring these famous international works to life. \",\"remark\":\"Don\\u2019t miss the Australian Ballet as they perform three ballet masterpieces. From classical technique, haunting and emotional storytelling and athletic movement, this mixed program highlights the diverse ability of the dancers as they bring these famous international works to life. The program will last 130 minutes and includes \\u201CSuite en Blanc,\\u201D \\u201CUnspoken Dialogues\\u201D and \\u201CIn the Upper Room.\\u201D \\u201CEvery inch of stage space, every bounce and jog, is rigorously calibrated, and the choreography demands from the dancers something akin to Olympic perfection of form,\\u201D the New York Times said in a review. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7c2a53b39350c94df360b221d886b3d3.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1438068125\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-28\\/247.html\",\"tid\":\"247\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:22\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 23-24, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=180-680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People Ave 人民大道300号上海大剧院\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Cinderella\\u2019 with a modern twist\",\"ftitle\":\"After a 10-year absence, the Australian Ballet is returning this autumn with the award-winning smash-hit production of Alexei Ratmansky\\u2019s \\u201CCinderella.\\u201D \",\"remark\":\"After a 10-year absence, the Australian Ballet is returning this autumn with the award-winning smash-hit production of Alexei Ratmansky\\u2019s \\u201CCinderella.\\u201D Bubbling with humor and life, this production of a timeless fairy tale will bewitch all over again. Ratmansky, the most in-demand choreographer in the world and the master of the modern story ballet, fills every bar of Prokofiev\\u2019s cinematic score as he charts Cinderella\\u2019s journey from rags to  rapture. The vivid designs draw inspiration from Dior, Schiaparelli, the elegance of 1940s Hollywood, and Surrealist art. Join the acclaimed dancers of the Australian Ballet as classical takes a modern twist in one of the world\\u2019s favorite fairy tales. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/d64077b0d2e34d3fa3ce17bc4ad754ae.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1437719711\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-24\\/245.html\",\"tid\":\"245\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:22\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 9, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Asian Youth Orchestra puts spotlight on young talent\",\"ftitle\":\"The 100 members of the Asian Youth Orchestra are among the finest young musicians in China, Indonesia, Japan, South Korea, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.\",\"remark\":\"The 100 members of the Asian Youth Orchestra are among the finest young musicians in China, Indonesia, Japan, South Korea, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. Chosen through highly competitive auditions held throughout the region, they are together for six weeks  each summer, initially for a three-week rehearsal camp in Hong Kong, then for a three-week international concert tour. Cellists Yo-Yo Ma, Mischa Maisky, Steven Isserlis, Wang Jian and Alisa Weilerstein are among those who have performed with AYO under the direction of principal conductor James Judd.   \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/c52de0115f688c68e634f86d636018c7.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1437469082\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-21\\/244.html\",\"tid\":\"244\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:23\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 16, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=150-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Irish national choir plans a wonderful night of music\",\"ftitle\":\"Anúna Ireland National Choir is an Irish choral group. In 1987 Dublin composer Michael McGlynn founded An Uaithne, a name which describes the three ancient types of Celtic music,\",\"remark\":\"Anúna Ireland National Choir is an Irish choral group. In 1987 Dublin composer Michael McGlynn founded An Uaithne, a name which describes the three ancient types of Celtic music, Suantraí (lullaby), Geantraí (happy songs) and Goltraí (lament). One of the group\\u2019s stated aims is to explore and redefine this music.   \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/0d01e02ed2346a85b327afd808f36c63.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1437468844\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-21\\/243.html\",\"tid\":\"243\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:23\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through August 23, 2015|Time=10am-6pm, closed on Mondays|Add=Shanghai Minsheng Art Museum, 570 Huaihai Rd 淮海西路570号，上海民生现代艺术馆\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Work, Rest and Play: British Photography from the 1960s to Today\",\"ftitle\":\"The \\u201CWork, Rest and Play: British Photography from the 1960s to Today\\u201D exhibition reflects upon the changes that have occurred in British culture over the last half century.\",\"remark\":\"The \\u201CWork, Rest and Play: British Photography from the 1960s to Today\\u201D exhibition reflects upon the changes that have occurred in British culture over the last half century. As part of the 2015 UK-China Year of Cultural Exchange, the exhibition is curated by The Photographers\\u2019 Gallery, London with Shanghai Minsheng Art Museum and the Cultural and Education Section of the British Consulate General in Shanghai acting as hosts. More than 400 images by 38 photographers and artists are on display. \\u201CThe show introduces the work of key figures who have contributed significantly to the development of the medium through the prism of documentary practices. While any exhibition of this kind cannot include everyone, this selection aims to highlight artists and photographers who, through their particular vision, enable us to understand the world in fresh and unexpected ways,\\u201D says Brett Rogers, director at The Photographers\\u2019 Gallery in London. Highlighting various approaches, from fashion and portraiture to photojournalism and fine art, the exhibit showcases the UK\\u2019s diversity. The dawn of the new millennium is a fascinating period in which Britain has experienced profound social and economic transformations. New technologies and the explosion of social media have changed how individuals communicate and how they express themselves. The wars in Afghanistan and Iraq, international terrorism, the financial crisis and globalization have been major events that have defined this new era. Photographers have traveled around the country observing these narratives and exploring the boundaries between the still and moving image. Their views often involve conceptual elements and tell contradictory stories ambiguously situated between fiction and fact. For example, Tim Walker\\u2019s fashion series evoked a fairytale-like world. The pleasurable escapism in the images comes across as more important than the clothes themselves. This new era is a stark contrast from the 1960s, when the country experienced numerous social and cultural changes. During the decade London became a center for music, fashion and a flourishing British art scene. Editorial photography dominated in magazines, as did professional studio portraiture \\u2014 evidence of the growing cult of celebrity within popular culture. Terence Donovan\\u2019s work had a playfulness that took fashion photography onto the street. Linda McCartney, married to the Beatles\\u2019 Paul McCartney, merged the public and the private to produce celebrity images that were almost like family snapshots. This new intimacy offered close look into the lives of famous people that viewers found appealing. By the 1970s, an economic recession had led to high unemployment. Numerous photographers became more politically conscious and socially engaged during this period. Some chose to point their lenses at declining industries and the people who were affected most. Photographers like Shirley Baker and Sirkka-Liisa Konttinen took an interest in working-class families and threatened communities in parts of England where traditional life was fading fast. Meanwhile, Vanley Burke focussed on ethnic minorities as they strived for equal rights. British society was defined by a new economy in the 1980s. Photographers once again showed a willingness to change with the times, dropping the documentary style in favor of satire. Martin Parr, a color photo pioneer, challenged the \\u201Cmythology of Britishness\\u201D with his satirical pictures of everyday life. The exhibition also looks at the rise of Britpop, Cool Britannia and the Girl Power phenomenon that dominated the 1990s. Portraying the young fans of the Spice Girls, Clare Strand\\u2019s images examine the vulnerable, preteen fans and contrast them with the stereotyped view of femininity embodied by their role models.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/248c557749a0a67be3b73c91a2caa5ae.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1437118755\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-17\\/242.html\",\"tid\":\"242\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:23\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 21, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"A perfect combination of a cappella and comedy\",\"ftitle\":\"Bringing harmony across the world, B vocal(Spanish) perfectly combines comic theatre and a cappella music: i.e. music performed with no instrumental accompaniment, created through imitating the sounds of instruments with their voices. \",\"remark\":\"Bringing harmony across the world, B vocal(Spanish) perfectly combines comic theatre and a cappella music: i.e. music performed with no instrumental accompaniment, created through imitating the sounds of instruments with their voices. B vocal blends together a cappella music, humor and theatre. One of their great successes is to be able to captivate any type of audience regardless of age or nationality. These traits have allowed them to build a quality artistic career path, leading to national and international prestige. They performed in the international exhibition Zaragoza 2008 and in the Spanish Pavilion of the Universal Exhibition of Shanghai in 2010. Special mention should be made of the educational work in family and children\\u2019s concerts that b vocal have undertaken since 1998. Over a million children of all ages have been able to enjoy their diverse shows, which revolve around various aspects of music and voice.    \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/fbf1352b2362f93d4c689ee147095d32.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1437118532\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-17\\/241.html\",\"tid\":\"241\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:23\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 10-12, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=300-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theatre -Lyric Theatre，300 Renming Avenue 上海大剧院，人民大道300号；\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Opera Die Zauberflote (Asia Premiere)\\u2014\\u2014A magical performance\",\"ftitle\":\"Opera \\u201CDie Zauberflöte,\\u201D or \\u201CThe Magic Flute,\\u201D presented by Komische Oper Berlin is coming this September. Since its establishment in 1892, Komische Oper Berlin has at various times been a consistent international trendsetter in the world of musical theater.\",\"remark\":\"Opera \\u201CDie Zauberflöte,\\u201D or \\u201CThe Magic Flute,\\u201D presented by Komische Oper Berlin is coming this September. Since its establishment in 1892, Komische Oper Berlin has at various times been a consistent international trendsetter in the world of musical theater. With immense, three-story spiders, flappers and demons, butterflies and  wolves \\u2014 this wildly inventive version of \\u201CThe Magic Flute\\u201D is like no other. It\\u2019s a perfect combination of all the things worth loving: silent movies, Weimar cabaret, David Lynch and the Brothers Grimm, according to a Guardian review.   Since arriving at the Komische Oper in 2012 Barrie Kosky has presided over a period of unprecedented success with the opera journal Opernwelt calling the Komische \'Opera House of the Year\' in 2013 and the International Opera Awards naming Kosky \'Director of the Year\' in 2014. Founded in 2005 by animator and illustrator Paul Barritt, and writer and performer Suzanne Andrade, 1927 has won critical and popular acclaim with works such as Between the Devil and the Deep Blue Sea and The Animals and Children Took to the Streets. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7b9d12214d4c12fa8e31f040ea11adc1.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1436930013\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-15\\/240.html\",\"tid\":\"240\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:23\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 3-26, 2015|Time=2:30pm, 7:30pm|Tickets=200-2000yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=China Art Museum，205 Shangnan Rd 中华艺术宫，上南路205号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Cavalia trots and twirls its way into town\",\"ftitle\":\"The highly acclaimed Cavalia opened in Shanghai in July. Promising a galloping good time, Cavalia is a blend of equestrianism and performing arts like acrobatics.\",\"remark\":\"The highly acclaimed Cavalia opened in Shanghai in July. Promising a galloping good time, Cavalia is a blend of equestrianism and performing arts like acrobatics. \\u201CThere is no other show like this in the world \\u2014 that\\u2019s why we have had such success so far,\\u201D says Normand Latourelle, who founded Cavalier in 2003 and remains its artistic director. \\u201CPeople in Shanghai are also going to see the amazement, see how beautiful the animals are.\\u201D Latourelle is renowned for his adventurous productions and is also one of the pioneers behind Cirque du Soleil. Cavalia, which features 40 horses, takes place at the White Theatre Tent next to China Art Museum. Not to be overshadowed by the horses, 40 riders, aerialists, acrobats, dancers and musicians from around the world will be a major part of the show. \\u201CCavalia is the biggest touring show in the world, including the logistics and performing arts,\\u201D Latourelle says. \\u201CThat\\u2019s a big challenge to bring such a big show from Canada to Shanghai. We are traveling with 100 containers of equipment. With 200 people working with me, and a talented local promoter, we finally made it possible. \\u201CWe are very proud of our horses, also the way we treat them. One of the key things to the success of Cavalia is \\u2018leave the horse, stay the horse,\\u2019 even though we have acrobatics flying, incredible music and 40 artists,\\u201D Latourelle adds. The show features 11 breeds including Spanish purebred, Percheron, Arabian, Lusitano, Warmblood and Quarter Horse. The animals are accompanied by a dedicated team of equine specialists. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/64a6b19ffacf879a89068b6576027f94.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1436929846\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-15\\/239.html\",\"tid\":\"239\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:23\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 21,2015|Time=8pm|Tickets=380-980yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Mercedes-Benz Arena, 1200 Shibo avenue 梅赛德斯奔驰文化中心，世博大道1200号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"MUSE Live in Shanghai 2015\",\"ftitle\":\"One of Britain\\u2019s biggest bands, MUSE are set to bring their spectacular, internationally-renowned live show to Shanghai for the first time on September 21 at Mercedes-Benz Arena. \",\"remark\":\"One of Britain\\u2019s biggest bands, MUSE are set to bring their spectacular, internationally-renowned live show to Shanghai for the first time on September 21 at Mercedes-Benz Arena. This tour is presented by AEG Live. Having played some of the biggest stadiums and festivals in the world, MUSE have built a reputation for electrifying live shows and creating incredible spectacles on stage.   Formed in Devon in the mid-\\u201890s, MUSE\\u2019s early material was likened to Radiohead, and their debut album Showbiz \\u2013 which featured the hit singles \\u2018Sunburn\\u2019 and \\u2018Unintended\\u2019 \\u2013 was a critical and commercial success. Since then, the band have gone on to establish themselves as one of the leading lights of British rock music, with a string of hit albums. And the trio are sure to be on fine form as they hit China just months after the release of their highly-anticipated seventh studio album Drones.   Given the band\'s live credentials and the fact that their Mercedes-Benz Arena concert will come soon after the release of their hotly anticipated new album, MUSE\\u2019s first ever Shanghai date is set to be one of the shows of the year in Shanghai.   Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/6bbb1fc313ee965ae4a0159798402cca.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1436514713\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-10\\/238.html\",\"tid\":\"238\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:23\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through July 24, 2015|Time=10am-5pm|Tickets=Free|Add=111 Jinzhu Rd 金珠路111号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Contemporary Visions: Italian Artists in China\",\"ftitle\":\"Organized by Shanghai International Culture Association and the Garuzzo Institute for the Visual Arts, a group show titled \\u201CContemporary Visions: Italian Artists in China\\u201D casts the spotlight on some of the most significant experiences of the current crop of Italian artists.\",\"remark\":\"Organized by Shanghai International Culture Association and the Garuzzo Institute for the Visual Arts, a group show titled \\u201CContemporary Visions: Italian Artists in China\\u201D casts the spotlight on some of the most significant experiences of the current crop of Italian artists. The exhibition encompasses a selection of works by 29 artists ranging from 25 to 50 years old. The exhibition involves multiple artistic expressions, such as drawing, painting, photography, installation, video and sculpture, demonstrating the feelings of contemporary Italian artists toward modern society. Click HERE to find more information about the exhibition.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/089798dfa64564028ffcffec3076d875.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1436323793\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-08\\/237.html\",\"tid\":\"237\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:24\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 14, 2015|Time=8pm|Tickets=480-3380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add:Mercerdes-Benz Arena, 1200 Expo Ave 世博大道1200号梅赛德斯奔驰文化艺术中心\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Bon Jovi comes to Shanghai for first ever show\",\"ftitle\":\"Bon Jovi, one of the most important acts in the history of rock and roll is coming to Shanghai, for what promises to be one of the year\\u2019s most popular shows.\",\"remark\":\"Bon Jovi, one of the most important acts in the history of rock and roll is coming to Shanghai, for what promises to be one of the year\\u2019s most popular shows. Bon Jovi will perform at Shanghai Mercedes-Benz Arena on September 14. The show will mark the band\\u2019s first ever trip to the city. In addition to the performance in Shanghai, Bon Jovi will also have two back-to-back performances in Macau on September 25 and 26 at Cotai Arena, The Venetian Macau. Bon Jovi has been one of the rock world\\u2019s most iconic acts for over three decades. The American legends, who have performed thousands of shows in more than 50 countries, promise to shake Shanghai with their spectacular show. Fans will be treated to an unforgettable night packed with classic Bon Jovi hits, including \\u201CLivin\\u2019 On A Prayer,\\u201D \\u201CYou Give Love A Bad Name,\\u201D \\u201CWho Says You Can\\u2019t Go Home,\\u201D \\u201CIt\\u2019s My Life\\u201D and many more. With over 130 million records sold, iconic frontman Jon Bon Jovi is recognized as one of the most talented singers in popular music.  For local rock fans, this concert is not to be missed. AEG Live, the live-entertainment division of Los Angeles-based AEG, is dedicated to all aspects of live contemporary music performance.  AEG Live is comprised of touring, festival, broadcast, merchandise and special event divisions. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4496e51b001d391a3d48a81f6266d0dc.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1436323436\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-08\\/236.html\",\"tid\":\"236\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:24\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 3-October 7, 2015|Time=10am-8pm|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Lafayette Arts & Design Center, 323 Fuxing Rd M. 拉法耶艺术设计中心，复兴中路323号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"The Beatles, Tomorrow\",\"ftitle\":\"Fans of the Beatles and people who love the song \\u201CHey, Jude\\u201D should mark dates of July 3 to October 7 on your calendar as their idols are coming to Shanghai.\",\"remark\":\"Fans of the Beatles and people who love the song \\u201CHey, Jude\\u201D should mark dates of July 3 to October 7 on your calendar as their idols are coming to Shanghai. An exhibition at the Lafayette Arts Center on Fuxing Road, \\u201CThe Beatles, Tomorrow,\\u201D will transport you back the 1960s. It is a tribute to all things Beatles and has been on a world tour with a stop in Taipei earlier this year. Visitors can see a large number of photos and personal items of the Beatle singers as well as more than 250 newspaper and magazine articles about the Fab Four -- Lennon, McCartney, Starr and Harrison. \\u201CThe Beatles, Tomorrow\\u201D show also features a reproduction of The Beatles\\u2019 first US television show and a reproduction of the famous Abbey Road album cover so you can act out that iconic scene with a little help from your friends. Well-known Shanghai radio DJs and bands will perform at the venue at night while food and wine will be served to bring The Beatles era back to life. Click HERE to buy the tickets!  \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/8176799c26bec7633c986686a81910e8.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1435904778\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-03\\/235.html\",\"tid\":\"235\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:24\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 29-August 2, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=180-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People\\\\\'s Ave, near Huangpi Rd N. 上海大剧院，人民大道300号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"It\\u2019s tough getting old\",\"ftitle\":\"In a small room where memories are hung on the walls, Andre and Dorine live like many elderly couples, gently decaying from daily routines and neglect. Their passion for each other now fading into indifference. The couple desperately needs to remember who they were.\",\"remark\":\"In a small room where memories are hung on the walls, Andre and Dorine live like many elderly couples, gently decaying from daily routines and neglect. Their passion for each other now fading into indifference. The couple desperately needs to remember who they were. Kulunka Teatro has created a piece of contemporary and committed mask theater that transcends language barriers. With no words, the story explores important themes with warmth and humor. \\u201CAndre and Dorine\\u201D has toured extensively in Spain, South America, the United States, United Kingdom and Europe. Now it is touring Asia. It was an award winner at the Birmingham European Theatre Festival in 2011, and at the La Habana International Theatre Festival 2011 (Cuba). Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/8b8c3ce52d158a4011d3c5dca1e3cec1.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1435904599\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-03\\/234.html\",\"tid\":\"234\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:24\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 30, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=160-680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People\\\\\'s Ave, near Huangpi Rd N. 上海大剧院，人民大道300号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Famous poem adapted to ballet\",\"ftitle\":\"The Chinese poem \\u201CSong of Everlasting Sorrow,\\u201D based upon the legendary romance between Emperor Xuanzong of the Tang Dynasty (AD 618-907), and Yang Yuhuan, his beloved concubine, was adapted into music by Bai Juyi.\",\"remark\":\"The Chinese poem \\u201CSong of Everlasting Sorrow,\\u201D based upon the legendary romance between Emperor Xuanzong of the Tang Dynasty (AD 618-907), and Yang Yuhuan, his beloved concubine, was adapted into music by Bai Juyi. Shanghai Grand Theater and Shanghai Ballet have co-produced \\u201CBallet Echoes of Eternity,\\u201D based on the poem. Choreographer Patrick de Bana has contributed to \\u201CEchoes.\\u201D The poem reads: \\u201CIn heaven like a pair of lovebirds, we\\u2019d fly wing to wing; Or else on earth, as twain trees with their branches entwining. Endures the earth, endures the heaven, they shall wear away. This sorrow, however, shall endure forever and a day.\\u201D Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/fb9f8e615df54e2150104c0417e9a639.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1435736811\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-01\\/233.html\",\"tid\":\"233\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:24\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 12, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=280-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall, 1380 Fuxing Rd M. 上交音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"\\u20182001\\u2019 score to be performed live\",\"ftitle\":\"Recognized as one of the greatest works of science fiction cinema, Stanley Kubrick\\u2019s \\u201C2001: A Space Odyssey\\u201D is acclaimed for its technological realism, creative audacity and inspired use of music. Now there\\u2019s a chance to watch the film while the soundtrack is performed live.\",\"remark\":\"Recognized as one of the greatest works of science fiction cinema, Stanley Kubrick\\u2019s \\u201C2001: A Space Odyssey\\u201D is acclaimed for its technological realism, creative audacity and inspired use of music. Now there\\u2019s a chance to watch the film while the soundtrack is performed live. The screenplay was partially inspired by Arthur C. Clarke\\u2019s short story \\u201CThe Sentinel.\\u201D Clarke concurrently wrote the novel 2001: A Space Odyssey, published soon after the film was released. The film follows a voyage to Jupiter with the sentient computer Hal after the discovery of a mysterious monolith that affected human evolution.   Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f70c035ca9b9b63da5deb45c6e35f3a6.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1435736339\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-01\\/232.html\",\"tid\":\"232\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:24\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 10, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Ticket=380,580 yuan|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall, 1380 Fuxin Rd M.复兴中路1380号上海交响乐团音乐厅\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"New York Philharmonic to perform in Shanghai\",\"ftitle\":\"Alan Gilbert will conduct the New York Philharmonic at the Shanghai Symphony Hall on July 10. The concert will also feature the celebrated Canadian pianist, Emanuel Ax.\",\"remark\":\"Alan Gilbert will conduct the New York Philharmonic at the Shanghai Symphony Hall on July 10. The concert will also feature the celebrated Canadian pianist, Emanuel Ax. The New York Philharmonic is the oldest symphonic orchestra in the United States and one of the oldest in the world. It gives more than 180 performances a year in collaboration with world-famous conductors and composers. Alan Gilbert is the first native New Yorker to be appointed the music director of the New York Philharmonic in September 2009. He also appeared as guest conductor with the Berlin Philharmonic, Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra, Boston Symphony Orchestra and Orchestra Philharmonique de Radio France. Programs for the Shanghai concert include \\u201CPiano Concerto No. 14 in E-flat major\\u201D by Mozart and \\u201CSymphony No. 5 in C-sharp minor\\u201D by Gustav Mahler. Born in Poland and educated in the Juilliard School of New York City, Emanuel Ax is regarded one of the world\\u2019s most talented pianists. He regularly performs in New York City, Boston, Chicago, Cleveland, Philadelphia and Saint Louis.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/883d3826d48475f2411b0d07a03d77e6.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1434016752\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/218.html\",\"tid\":\"218\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:24\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 7-9, 2015|Time=2pm, 7:15pm|Ticket=180-1000|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Culture Square, 597 Fuxing Rd M.上海文化广场，复兴中路597号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Diving into world of adventure\",\"ftitle\":\"The story is based on the classic book \\u201CAlice in Wonderland\\u201D by Lewis Carroll, but set in modern society. \",\"remark\":\" The story is based on the classic book \\u201CAlice in Wonderland\\u201D by Lewis Carroll, but set in modern society.  Ordinary guy Mr B has a busy life, filled with stresses enhanced by smart phones, tablet PCs and other gadgets that bring convenience but take us further from reality. After another long day, Mr B finds himself transported as if by magic to a special, colorful, happy place called Bubblelandia. The \\u201Cinhabitants\\u201D of Bubblelandia \\u2014 seahorses, dragon fish, starfish, mermaids, clown fish and others \\u2014 carry Mr B along in an adventure in this underwater mystery world where fantasy becomes reality. Produced by Brinum-X Entertainment, it combines drama, mime, dance, puppetry, juggling, contortionist, sand art and magic, with various stage effects adopting the  latest laser technologies, snow cannons, soap bubble tornadoes, theatrical fog, gigantic smoke rings, smoke-filled soap bubbles and optical illusions.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/12ac92ca766dde9e64429d2c8590d3a1.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1434016687\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/219.html\",\"tid\":\"219\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:25\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 22， 2015|Time=8pmTicket=400-1800 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Hongkou Stadium, 444 Jiangwan Rd E.虹口体育场，东江湾路444号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Linkin Park 2015 China Tour Shanghai\",\"ftitle\":\"The tickets for this concert are pre-sale tickets. We will deliver the tickets to you in June after you book the tickets online. The tickets are limited! Only 10 tickets are available!\",\"remark\":\" The tickets for this concert are pre-sale tickets. We will deliver the tickets to you in June after you book the tickets online. The tickets are limited! Only 10 tickets are available!   American rock band Linkin Park is heading to China again in July as part of its ongoing international tour. The band is scheduled to perform on July 22 at the Hongkou Football Stadium. Additional Chinese shows are slated for Nanjing (Jiangsu Province, July 17), Shenzhen (Guangdong Province, July 19), Chongqing (July 24) and Beijing (July 26). \\u201CWe\\u2019re honored to be headlining these five stadium dates and reuniting with our amazing fans in China,\\u201D said Mike Shinoda, one of the lead vocalists, in an official statement. The rockers are currently touring in support of their sixth studio album, \\u201CThe Hunting Party,\\u201D which was released in June 2014. The new album is the band\\u2019s first self-produced endeavor, as well as their first to rely heavily on minimally altered analog tape recording. In their own words, the newest record grew out of \\u201Ca hunger for a sound that we don\\u2019t hear anyone else making.\\u201D The upcoming China dates will mark Linkin Park\\u2019s third appearance in the country. They first performed in Shanghai in 2007 and then returned to the city in 2009. As a long-time Linkin Park fan, Shanghai native Chara Wu is excited about the new album and the concert in July. The 29-year-old attended the band\\u2019s last show in the city and still remembers every thrilling moment. \\u201CI had a really great time that night,\\u201D recalls Wu. \\u201CAll the fans were jumping and dancing, and then everybody started singing along when they performed \\u2018In the End\\u2019.\\u201D Linkin Park has built an immense following in China over the years among listeners like Wu. \\u201CTheir music is part of the memory of our generation. We grew up listening to them. We saw the band change over the years and fans would very much like to relive the exciting experience they had when they were young.\\u201D As one of the most successful rock bands of all time, Linkin Park has sold over 50 million albums worldwide and was the first rock band to achieve more than 1.9 billion views on YouTube. In 2005, the band founded Music For Relief, a non-profit organization dedicated to providing aid to victims of natural disasters. It recently announced a partnership with Rock in Rio as the legendary festival gears up for the launch of its first-ever event in the US later this month. The event will raise funds for reforestation efforts in areas affected by wildfires in California.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3adcf3275f885e2f39dbf86cc2e57efd.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1434016425\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/217.html\",\"tid\":\"217\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:25\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 15-16, 2015|Time=7:30pm, 2:30pm|Tickets=180-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theatre, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Percussion Concert Drumblebee\",\"ftitle\":\"In this musical for young audiences, four percussionist- explorers, who come from another century, are trying to catch the moon \\u2014 despite the weight of their instruments.\",\"remark\":\"In this musical for young audiences, four percussionist- explorers, who come from another century, are trying to catch the moon \\u2014 despite the weight of their instruments.  From Steve Reich to Goran Bregovic, through the Flight of the Bumblebee by Rimsky-Korsakov and an unrecognizable Ravel\\u2019s Bolero, Drumblebee is a  show of virtuosity staged by Dan Tanson, who creates a world where gravity, lights and music merge to become one. It has won such top prizes as the Audience Prize of the Young Audience Music Awards in Brussels and the Special Prize of the Jury of the Berlin Junge Ohren for its \\u201CDrumblebee\\u201D show.  The show also won prizes in both Art Basel and the Berlin Festival in 2012. Moreover, performers Quatuor Beat has become one of the most popular educational ensembles for Children\\u2019s Music in Europe.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/abaa859599e87a46ad48480e845425de.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1434016305\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/216.html\",\"tid\":\"216\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:25\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 16, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Ticket=280, 380 yuan|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall, 1380 Fuxin Rd M.复兴中路1380号上海交响乐团音乐厅\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"\\\\\'The Matrix\\u2019 concert\",\"ftitle\":\"Music in the 1999 sci-fi action film \\\\\\\"The Matrix\\\\\\\" will be performed in a concert at Shanghai Symphony Hall on July 16 as part of the Shanghai Summer Music Festival.\",\"remark\":\" Music in the 1999 sci-fi action film \\\"The Matrix\\\" will be performed in a concert at Shanghai Symphony Hall on July 16 as part of the Shanghai Summer Music Festival. The American-Australian film is famous for sound tracks composed and directed by Donald Romain Davis, who also produced music for BBC documentaries \\u201CBlue Planet,\\\" \\\"Frozen Planet\\\" and \\\"Planet Earth.\\\" The Hangzhou Philharmonic Orchestra, founded in 2007, will present the concert. Its 80 musicians are graduates from distinguished music conservatories in China and abroad.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/decb027cf798b1b25f8552e8ce92f8de.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1434016300\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/215.html\",\"tid\":\"215\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:25\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 14-16, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Ticket=80-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"\\\\\'Murmurs\\\\\' to hit stage in Shanghai\",\"ftitle\":\"The timeless charms of Charlie Chaplin are brought to life in the fantasy stage-show \\u201CMurmurs\\u201D \\u2014 also known as \\u201CWhat the Walls are Saying\\u201D \\u2014 a work created by the famed silent actor\\u2019s talented granddaughter, dancer and acrobat Aurelia Thierree.\",\"remark\":\" The timeless charms of Charlie Chaplin are brought to life in the fantasy stage-show \\u201CMurmurs\\u201D \\u2014 also known as \\u201CWhat the Walls are Saying\\u201D \\u2014 a work created by the famed silent actor\\u2019s talented granddaughter, dancer and acrobat Aurelia Thierree. The humorous and sentimental show has been described as a modern-day \\u201CAlice in Wonderland\\u201D by critics. Audiences around the world have already been delighted by this fantastic and visually stunning stage experience, which combines dance, acrobatics, magic and mime. Thierree plays a curious woman who wanders through a world of illusion, where rooms filled with various ordinary objects magically come alive or transform into fantastical creatures. Since the show\\u2019s debut in the UK back in 2011, \\u201CMurmurs\\u201D has been performed in more than 20 countries and regions. To date, the show has been staged over 1,000 times. In the eyes of Thierree, walls protects people\\u2019s privacy while also witnessing the joys and sorrows of their human inhabitants. She uses walls as metaphors for the sometimes fragile human world as well as our own inner emotional barriers.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3f2ec9c949ad80f8ed9a12c8b0ee57c2.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1434015987\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/214.html\",\"tid\":\"214\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-20 21:04:44\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 3-5, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Ticket=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Childrens Drama Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Dora\\u2019s Pirate Adventure (English and Chinese versions)\",\"ftitle\":\"Dora\\u2019s Pirate Adventure incorporates the interactive and educational elements that make Dora the Explorer one of the most popular shows on television.Like its TV shows,live shows of Dora the Explorer brings enjoyment to kids and their families.\",\"remark\":\" Dora\\u2019s Pirate Adventure incorporates the interactive and educational elements that make Dora the Explorer one of the most popular shows on television.Like its TV shows,live shows of Dora the Explorer brings enjoyment to kids and their families. Join Dora and the rest of her friends in Dora\\u2019s Pirate Adventure as they embark on an exciting trip to Treasure Island in search of the ultimate pirate party. Help them navigate over Dancing Mountain and through Silly Singing Bridge in pursuit of the Pirate Piggies. Along the way, Dora the Explorer fans will use their map-reading, counting, musical and language skills to successfully help Dora reach Treasure Island and avoid that pesky fox Swiper!     Type | Musical Duration | 70mins Age | 2-8 Director | Theresa Borg Producer | Nickelodeon、Life Like Touring Performance | Life Like Touring       The following sessions are performed in English: 3:30pm on July 3, 3:30pm on July 4, 10:30am on July 5. The other sessions are performed in Chinese. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/1431502194253565066.jpg\",\"newstime\":\"1432622315\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-05-26\\/164.html\",\"tid\":\"164\"}]', '2016-9-20 21:04:44', '2016-9-20 21:04:44');
