\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-16\\/301.html\",\"tid\":\"301\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:18:54\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 11, 2015-March 6, 2016 |Time=11:00am|Tickets=100-120 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Exhibition Center\",\"title\":\"\\u201CPierre Auguste Renoir\\u201D Exhibition\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The exhibition entitled \\u201CPierre Auguste Renoir, A life for painting\\u201D is currently taking place and will be on until March 6th at the No.2 West Hall of Shanghai Exhibition Center. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/1cbc317da91365dc3b4e7c8c5691b5dd.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The exhibition entitled \\u201CPierre Auguste Renoir, A life for painting\\u201D is currently taking place and will be on until March 6th at the No.2 West Hall of Shanghai Exhibition Center. Renoir was born in France in 1841 into a family of artisans and early in his career was influenced by the Impressionist movement.  This influence led him to create works of art that incorporated outdoor scenes completed with swift visible brushstrokes. By the 1880s, he had broken away from the Impressionist style and experimented with a more formalist style, which included depictions of the female nude.  The exhibition traces the evolution of Renoir\\u2019s style, which includes vivid colors and subject matters that reflect the socially conscious society of his times.   HERE to buy tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1449818633\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-11\\/300.html\",\"tid\":\"300\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:18:54\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=June 24, 2016 |Time=7:30pm|Tickets=50-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall Concert Hall\",\"title\":\"Glory of American and British Music World\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Chinese Piano Prodigy Niu Niu and Conductor Muhai Tang are coming to Shanghai\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/312779f89922a7a68d63a6224baa1d99.jpg\",\"remark\":\" Piano: Niu Niu (Shengliang Zhang) Chinese Piano Prodigy Niu Niu began studying the piano when he was 3 years old. He held his first recital when he was 6 and was recruited by the primary school attached to the Shanghai Conservatory of Music two years later. He was the youngest student at the time. In his first album in 2008 he played Mozart, in his second in 2010 he played Chopin, and in 2012 it was Liszt.   Conductor: Muhai Tang Tang was chief conductor of the Finnish National Opera and artistic director of Zurich Chamber Orchestra and the Shanghai Concert Hall since 2006. He also teaches at Shanghai Conservatory of Music.   Samuel Barber: Adagio for Strings Samuel Barber: Piano Concerto, Op.38 Edward Elgar: Enigma Variations, Op.36 Edward Elgar: Military Marches (\'Pomp and Circumstance\'), Op.39, No.1 HERE to buy tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1449818263\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-11\\/299.html\",\"tid\":\"299\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:18:54\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 26, 2015 |Time=7:30pm|Tickets=680-1280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Gymnasium\",\"title\":\"2015&2016 \\u201CTHE SQUALL\\u201D Rain Asia Tour in Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"2015&2016 \\u201CTHE SQUALL\\u201D Rain Asia Tour in Shanghai will be held at Shanghai Grand Stage on Dec.26, 2015. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/ad3f46ee0d43a5ab9a6e00ddc27da21a.jpg\",\"remark\":\"2015&2016 \\u201CTHE SQUALL\\u201D Rain Asia Tour in Shanghai will be held at Shanghai Grand Stage on Dec.26, 2015. Rain is a South Korean singer-songwriter, actor, and music producer.Rain\'s musical career includes seven albums (six Korean, one Japanese), 28 singles and numerous concert tours around the world.  His acting career began in 2003, when he won the KBS Best New Actor award for his role in the drama Sang Doo! Let\'s Go To School. In 2004, Rain won the KBS Excellence in Acting (Best Actor) award for his role in the drama Full House.  After starring in A Love To Kill, he acted in his first Korean film, I\'m a Cyborg, But That\'s OK (2006), which won the Alfred Bauer Prize at the Berlin International Film Festival. Rain has acted in the American films Speed Racer (2008) and Ninja Assassin (2009), the latter of which made him the first Korean to win an MTV award. Rain acted in another Korean film, R2B: Return to Base, that was released in August 2012. As a precursor to his new album, Rain starred in a reality show Rain Effect which Cube Entertainment stated \\\"You can meet Jung Ji Hoon as a human being.\\\" The show premieres on December 19. The new album, also titled Rain Effect, debuted on January 2, 2014 with music videos for double title tracks, \\\"30 Sexy\\\" and \\\"La Song,\\\" released beforehand. Click HERE to buy tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1449647465\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-09\\/298.html\",\"tid\":\"298\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:18:55\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=January 3, 2016|Time=8pm|Tickets=380-1080 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall - Concert Hall\",\"title\":\"ORF Radio-Symphonie orchester Wien 2016 Shanghai Concert\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"ORF Radio-Symphonie orchester Wien will bring their New Year concert to Shanghai\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/Users\\/zyq\\/MyWork\\/webroot\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7993724fe34b1d914f249b94badcd660.jpg\",\"remark\":\"ORF Vienna Radio Symphony Orchestra   The Vienna RSO is one of the three top orchestras alongside the Philharmonic and Symphoniker. It originated out of the orchestra of Austrian Radio in 1969 for the purpose of presenting contemporary orchestral works. Over the years, the repertoire expanded in different directions.   Conductor: Patrick