ard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"By Northern Ballet Britain, \\\\\\\"THE GREAT GATSBY\\\\\\\"  will be staged at the Shanghai Grand Theatre at the end of next month.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7f6ecec5c89800d646662fdb982e72e0.jpg\",\"remark\":\"By Northern Ballet Britain, \\\"THE GREAT GATSBY\\\"  will be staged at the Shanghai Grand Theatre at the end of next month. The story ballet tells a story about the heady, indulgent days of the roaring 1920s  on New York\\u2019s Long Island where a young Midwesterner Nick Carraway meets his infamous neighbour Jay Gatsby \\u2013 a mysterious millionaire with a secret past and a penchant for lavish parties. As the sparkling facade of Gatsby\\u2019s world begins to slip, Carraway comes to see the loneliness, obsession and tragedy that lie beneath.     Choreographed by David Nixon the dancers glide across the floor in gorgeous Chanel-inspired costumes to a sweeping, filmic score by Sir Richard Rodney Bennett CBE (Four Weddings and a Funeral, Murder on the Orient Express). Bursting with passion, style and drama, this blockbuster ballet comes for two performances in Shanghai Grand Theatre and three performances in NCPA only.   \\\"You will leave the theatre with a warm glow and a smile\\\" Sunday Express \\\"Nixon\\u2019s choreography really flies\\\" The Guardian     HERE to buy tickets\",\"newstime\":\"1451543920\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-31\\/312.html\",\"tid\":\"312\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:42\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Apr 08, 2016 |Time=8pm|Tickets=180-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall - Concert Hall\",\"title\":\"Sir Andrew Davis &Melbourne Symphony Orchestra\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Melbourne Symphony Orchestra is coming to Shanghai soon! \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/1cbacb979e670a6631169468d9b9b573.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Melbourne Symphony Orchestra is coming to Shanghai soon! The Melbourne Symphony Orchestra (MSO) is an orchestra based in Melbourne, Australia. It has 100 permanent musicians. Melbourne has the longest continuous history of orchestral music of any Australian city and the MSO is the oldest professional orchestra in Australia. The MSO performs to more than 200,000 people in Melbourne and regional Victoria in over 150 concerts a year. Following integration with the Melbourne Chorale in 2008, the Orchestra has responsibility for its own choir, the MSO Chorus. The orchestra relies on funding by the Victorian State Government through Arts Victoria, Department of Premier and Cabinet and the Federal governmentthrough the Australia Council and support from private corporations and donors. It is supported by Symphony Services International. HERE to buy tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1451542847\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-31\\/311.html\",\"tid\":\"311\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:43\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through February 15, 2016 |Time=10am-8pm |Tickets=120 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Chi K11 Art Space, 300 Huaihai Rd M.\",\"title\":\"The Major Exhibition-\\\\\'Media - Dalí\\\\\'\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"An exhibition of Salvador Dali, \\u201CMedia \\u2014 Dali\\u201D will be held in Shanghai K11 Art Mall from November 5 to February 15.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7bfc6c04e5d3ba5ef311f14d61d9cf72.jpg\",\"remark\":\"An exhibition of Salvador Dali, \\u201CMedia \\u2014 Dali\\u201D will be held in Shanghai K11 Art Mall from November 5 to February 15.   Born on May 11, 1904, in Spain, Dali is best known for his adventurous life. He is talented and unique. His fiercely technical yet highly unusual paintings, sculptures and visionary explorations in film and life-size interactive art ushered in a new generation of imaginative expression. As a great master in Surrealism, Dalí is considered one of the three most important Spanish artists along with Pablo Picasso and Joan Miro. The K11 Art Foundation and Gala-Salvador Dali Foundation will collaborate closely on the Surrealist exhibition at Shanghai K11 Art Mall. The two will also promote his works in China in other platforms, including new media, seminars and forums. It is expected to create new dialogues on surrealism and the role of contemporary art in Chinese society.  Click HERE to buy tickets!  \",\"newstime\":\"1451542563\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-31\\/310.html\",\"tid\":\"310\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:43\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Jan 31, 2016 |Time=8:30pm |Tickets=From 280yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=179 Yichang Rd, QSW Culture Center\",\"title\":\"Gigi D\\\\\'Alessio Malaterra World\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"CICC is delighted to announce that Gigi D\\\\\'Alessio Malaterra World tickets are on sale!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f7f487c67fcc10fd41b33c65a66fd8a6.jpg\",\"remark\":\"CICC is delighted to announce that Gigi D\'Alessio Malaterra World tickets are on sale!   Join us with your family and friends on January 31st at Shanghai QSW Culture Center, enjoy the singer reinterpreting the classics of the Neapolitan music and performing his masterpieces. Part of the proceeds will be donated to the ONLUS \\\"Terra dei Cuori.\\\" For more info and RSVP please write to malaterra@cameraitacina.com\",\"newstime\":\"1451542062\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-31\\/309.html\",\"tid\":\"309\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:43\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=April 24, 2016 |Time=8:00pm|Tickets=580-1080 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall \",\"title\":\"Rudolf Buchbinder&Staatskapelle Dresden\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Rudolf Buchbinder, who is firmly established as one of the world\\\\\'s foremost pianists, is invited by famous german  Orchestra Staatskapelle Dresden to perform at  Shanghai Symphony Hall!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/1d8adbd6a4fadab6425f6d4d1f7b286a.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Rudolf Buchbinder, who is firmly established as one of the world\'s foremost pianists, is invited by famous german  Orchestra Staatskapelle Dresden to perform at  Shanghai Symphony Hall! His comprehensive repertoire encompasses numerous 20th century compositions.  Vienna Academy of Music. In 1965 he made a tour of North and South America. In 1966 he won a special prize awarded at the Van Cliburn International Piano Competition. Subsequently he has toured with the Vienna Philharmonic and appeared as soloist around the world. He has also taught piano at the Basel Academy of Music. In 2009, Buchbinder was featured in the award-winning German-Austrian documentary Pianomania, about a Steinway & Sons piano tuner, which was directed by Lilian Franckand Robert Cibis. The film premiered theatrically in North America, where it was met with positive reviews by The New York Times. HERE to buy tickets!  \",\"newstime\":\"1450943876\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-24\\/308.html\",\"tid\":\"308\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:43\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=March 2, 2016|Time=8:00 pm|Tickets=180-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall\",\"title\":\"Ian Bostridge& Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Joined by  British period instrument  Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment, the  well-known London tenor Ian Bostridge will perform at Shanghai Symphony Hall on March, 2016.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f16b70a0d743f9e31d0df43768f74dde.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Joined by  British period instrument  Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment, the  well-known London tenor Ian Bostridge will perform at Shanghai Symphony Hall on March, 2016.   Bostridge only began singing professionally at age 27 and made his Wigmore Hall debut in 1993; his Purcell Room debut (an acclaimed Winterreise) and his Aldeburgh Festival debut in 1994; in 1995 he gave his first solo recital in the Wigmore Hall (winning the Royal Philharmonic Society\'s Debut Award); in 1996 he gave recitals inLyon, Cologne, London and at the Aldeburgh, Cheltenham and Edinburgh Festivals, and in 1997 at the Alte Oper, Frankfurt.     HERE to buy tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1450943580\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-24\\/307.html\",\"tid\":\"307\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:43\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=January 13, 2016 |Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center\",\"title\":\"The Romantic Harp Recital by Xavier de Maistre\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The Romantic Harp Recital by Xavier de Maistre is coming to Shanghai next month\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/2d7600fefb706c935a3ea0604598291d.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Xavier de Maistre was born in Toulon and began to study harp at the age of nine. He finished his studies with Catherine Michel and Jacqueline Borot in Paris. In 1998 he was awarded the first prize at the prestigious International Harp Competition in Bloomington, Indiana. He immediately became the first French musician to join the ranks of the prestigious Vienna Philharmonic Orchestra \\u2013 a position which he left in summer 2010.     Xavier de Maistre belongs to an elite category category of soloists who are redefining what is possible with their instrument. Aside from new commissions from composers such as Krzysztof Penderecki and Kaija Saariaho, he performs works like Smetana\\u2019s \\u201CMa Vlast\\\" with breathtaking precision, presenting masterful arrangements of works that are usually played by an entire orchestra. The interpretation of these works, that few harpists before him have even considered playing, has contributed to his reputation as one of the most creative and extraordinary musicians of his generation. Xavier de Maistre has appeared with major orchestras under the direction of such eminent conductors as Bertrand de Billy, Daniele Gatti, Kristjan Järvi, Philippe Jordan, Riccardo Muti, Andrés Orozco-Estrada, André Previn, Simon Rattle, Heinrich Schiff and Gilbert Varga. He performs at many of Europe\\u2019s leading festivals, including Schleswig-Holstein, Salzburg, Rheingau, Vienna and Verbier, the Budapest Spring Festival and the Wurzburg Mozart Festival. He collaborates with such chamber music partners as Diana Damrau, Mojca Erdmann, Daniel MüllerSchott, Baiba Skride, Arabella Steinbacher and Magali Mosnier.   Orchestral highlights of the 2013\\/14 season include an extensive tour with the Academy of St Martin in the Fields, performances with NHK Symphony Orchestra, Vienna Symphony Orchestra, tour concerts with Basel Chamber Orchestra and debuts with Helsinki Philharmonic, Royal Liverpool Philharmonic and Malmo Symphony Orchestras. The season concludes with the world premiere of a new concerto by Krzysztof Penderecki, reuniting de Maistre with Orchestre de Paris. De Maistre will also give solo recitals as far afield as Shanghai, Macao and Montreal and appears in duo performances with Diana Damrau at Schubertiade, Grafenegg and Istanbul Festivals, at the Munich Opera Festival (Bayerische Staatsoper) and London\\u2019s Wigmore Hall.   In 2008 Xavier de Maistre signed an exclusive contract with Sony Music. Releases so far have included music by Haydn, Rodrigo, Ginastera and Debussy \\u2013 the latter for which he was awarded the Echo Klassik Award 2009 as \\\"Instrumentalist of the Year\\\". In 2012 \\u201CNotte Veneziana\\u201D, a recording of baroque concertos with the Ensemble l\\u2019arte del mondo, was released. Highly acclaimed by the press, \\u201CNotte Veneziana\\u201D entered the top ten in the classical music charts. His latest releases include a DVD with Diana Damrau and a CD recording of Mozart piano concertos arranged for harp, with Mozarteum Salzburg and conductor Ivor Bolton.   Since 2001 Xavier de Maistre has taught at the Hamburg Academy of Music. He also gives regular masterclasses at New York\\u2019s Juilliard School of Music, Tokyo\\u2019s Toho University and London\\u2019s Trinity College of Music.   Click HERE to buy tickets.  \",\"newstime\":\"1450243647\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-16\\/305.html\",\"tid\":\"305\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:43\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=February 24, 2016-February 26, 2016 |Time=7:15 pm|Tickets=280-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Centre\",\"title\":\"Swan Lake by Imperial Russian Ballet in Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Swan Lake by Imperial Russian Ballet will come to Shanghai\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/9fb8ddf872803b3e12e744bd030df880.jpg\",\"remark\":\"     The artists of the company increase their skills under famous ballet teachers: A. Bondarenko, E.Vlasova, A. Kudelin, N. Osipian.  The Imperial Russian Ballet company is a member of European Cultural Center in Moscow under patronize of European Parliament. Gedeminas Taranda is one of the founders of European Cultural Center.     HERE to buy tickets.  \",\"newstime\":\"1450236155\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-16\\/304.html\",\"tid\":\"304\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:43\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=January 23，2016-January 24，2016|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=280-880 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Centre\",\"title\":\"The Nutcracker by Russian State Ballet in Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The Nutcracker by Russian State Ballet in Shanghai will be held at Shanghai Oriental Art Centre from Jan.23 to Jan.24, 2016.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/ccd10c2ba10fdcf1dfa5ee4ce22f4335.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The Nutcracker by Russian State Ballet in Shanghai will be held at Shanghai Oriental Art Centre from Jan.23 to Jan.24, 2016. The Nutcracker is a two-act ballet, originally choreographed by Marius Petipa and Lev Ivanov with a score by Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky (op. 71). The libretto is adapted from E.T.A. Hoffmann\'s story The Nutcracker and the Mouse King. It was given its première at the Mariinsky Theatre in St. Petersburg on Sunday, December 18, 1892, on a double-bill with Tchaikovsky\'s opera, Iolanta. HERE to buy tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1450235742\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-16\\/303.html\",\"tid\":\"303\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:43\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=January 15, 2016-January 16,2016 |Time=7:15 pm|Tickets=180-680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theatre \",\"title\":\"Dance of the world\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Dance of the world is hosted by UniArt Universal Culture & Media, will be shown in Shanghai Grand theater in Jan, 15th and 16th, 2016.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/dcd1e82e1512bb70a19f8904f1ffeeb0.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Dance of the world is hosted by UniArt Universal Culture & Media, will be shown in Shanghai Grand theater in Jan, 15th and 16th, 2016. Under the influence of multicultural background, dance of the world became an international and professional dancing group. It is produced by world famous entertainment producing company--Universal Entertainment, joined with European top choreographer master, Vadim Yelizarov, who is also the artistic director of this group. The fabulous dancing show created by the dancing masters. This show which is themed as the sublimation of love, based on palace dance, and combined with new dance elements presents the unique charm of dances from different places of the world : Romantic Waltz, Passionate      Tango, Enthusiastic Flamingo, and dazzling Cancan. Artists put the power, desire, and sacred    faith to every movement.  In this show, audience will go through time and geographical boundary, to enjoy the versatile    and luxury beauty from the world.   HERE to buy tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1450235289\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-16\\/301.html\",\"tid\":\"301\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:43\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 11, 2015-March 6, 2016 |Time=11:00am|Tickets=100-120 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Exhibition Center\",\"title\":\"\\u201CPierre Auguste Renoir\\u201D Exhibition\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The exhibition entitled \\u201CPierre Auguste Renoir, A life for painting\\u201D is currently taking place and will be on until March 6th at the No.2 West Hall of Shanghai Exhibition Center. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/1cbc317da91365dc3b4e7c8c5691b5dd.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The exhibition entitled \\u201CPierre Auguste Renoir, A life for painting\\u201D is currently taking place and will be on until March 6th at the No.2 West Hall of Shanghai Exhibition Center. Renoir was born in France in 1841 into a family of artisans and early in his career was influenced by the Impressionist movement.  This influence led him to create works of art that incorporated outdoor scenes completed with swift visible brushstrokes. By the 1880s, he had broken away from the Impressionist style and experimented with a more formalist style, which included depictions of the female nude.  The exhibition traces the evolution of Renoir\\u2019s style, which includes vivid colors and subject matters that reflect the socially conscious society of his times.   HERE to buy tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1449818633\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-11\\/300.html\",\"tid\":\"300\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:44\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=June 24, 2016 |Time=7:30pm|Tickets=50-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall Concert Hall\",\"title\":\"Glory of American and British Music World\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Chinese Piano Prodigy Niu Niu and Conductor Muhai Tang are coming to Shanghai\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/312779f89922a7a68d63a6224baa1d99.jpg\",\"remark\":\" Piano: Niu Niu (Shengliang Zhang) Chinese Piano Prodigy Niu Niu began studying the piano when he was 3 years old. He held his first recital when he was 6 and was recruited by the primary school attached to the Shanghai Conservatory of Music two years later. He was the youngest student at the time. In his first album in 2008 he played Mozart, in his second in 2010 he played Chopin, and in 2012 it was Liszt.   Conductor: Muhai Tang Tang was chief conductor of the Finnish National Opera and artistic director of Zurich Chamber Orchestra and the Shanghai Concert Hall since 2006. He also teaches at Shanghai Conservatory of Music.   Samuel Barber: Adagio for Strings Samuel Barber: Piano Concerto, Op.38 Edward Elgar: Enigma Variations, Op.36 Edward Elgar: Military Marches (\'Pomp and Circumstance\'), Op.39, No.1 HERE to buy tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1449818263\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-11\\/299.html\",\"tid\":\"299\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:44\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 26, 2015 |Time=7:30pm|Tickets=680-1280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Gymnasium\",\"title\":\"2015&2016 \\u201CTHE SQUALL\\u201D Rain Asia Tour in Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"2015&2016 \\u201CTHE SQUALL\\u201D Rain Asia Tour in Shanghai will be held at Shanghai Grand Stage on Dec.26, 2015. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/ad3f46ee0d43a5ab9a6e00ddc27da21a.jpg\",\"remark\":\"2015&2016 \\u201CTHE SQUALL\\u201D Rain Asia Tour in Shanghai will be held at Shanghai Grand Stage on Dec.26, 2015. Rain is a South Korean singer-songwriter, actor, and music producer.Rain\'s musical career includes seven albums (six Korean, one Japanese), 28 singles and numerous concert tours around the world.  His acting career began in 2003, when he won the KBS Best New Actor award for his role in the drama Sang Doo! Let\'s Go To School. In 2004, Rain won the KBS Excellence in Acting (Best Actor) award for his role in the drama Full House.  After starring in A Love To Kill, he acted in his first Korean film, I\'m a Cyborg, But That\'s OK (2006), which won the Alfred Bauer Prize at the Berlin International Film Festival. Rain has acted in the American films Speed Racer (2008) and Ninja Assassin (2009), the latter of which made him the first Korean to win an MTV award. Rain acted in another Korean film, R2B: Return to Base, that was released in August 2012. As a precursor to his new album, Rain starred in a reality show Rain Effect which Cube Entertainment stated \\\"You can meet Jung Ji Hoon as a human being.\\\" The show premieres on December 19. The new album, also titled Rain Effect, debuted on January 2, 2014 with music videos for double title tracks, \\\"30 Sexy\\\" and \\\"La Song,\\\" released beforehand. Click HERE to buy tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1449647465\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-09\\/298.html\",\"tid\":\"298\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:44\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=January 3, 2016|Time=8pm|Tickets=380-1080 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall - Concert Hall\",\"title\":\"ORF Radio-Symphonie orchester Wien 2016 Shanghai Concert\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"ORF Radio-Symphonie orchester Wien will bring their New Year concert to Shanghai\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7993724fe34b1d914f249b94badcd660.jpg\",\"remark\":\"ORF Vienna Radio Symphony Orchestra   The Vienna RSO is one of the three top orchestras alongside the Philharmonic and Symphoniker. It originated out of the orchestra of Austrian Radio in 1969 for the purpose of presenting contemporary orchestral works. Over the years, the repertoire expanded in different directions.   Conductor: Patrick Lange   ♪ Programme W.A. Mozart: Le nozze di Figaro Overture Antonín Dvořák: Symphony No.8 in G major, Op.88 Franz von Suppé: Light CalvaryOverture Johann Strauss II: KaiserWalzer (Emperor Waltz), Op.437 Gerhard E. Winkler: PussyPolka Johann Strauss II: AnnenPolka, Op.117 Johann Strauss II: Tritsch Tratsch Polka, Op.214   HERE to buy tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1449647166\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-09\\/297.html\",\"tid\":\"297\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:44\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 9, 2015-April 7, 2016|Time=10am-9:30pm |Tickets=130-252 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Hongqiao Tiandi Square\",\"title\":\"Da Vinci - The Genius Exhibition\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The exhibition appears at The Hub Pub Performance & Exhibition Center for a limited four-month engagement starting on December 8, 2015 and ending on April 7, 2016.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3fa0c982601180ceac2bd9eabe0432d4.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The exhibition appears at The Hub Pub Performance & Exhibition Center for a limited four-month engagement starting on December 8, 2015 and ending on April 7, 2016.   The interactive experience immerses guests in Leonardo\\u2019s timeless brilliance through full-scale interpretations of the mastermind\\u2019s inventions and unparalleled studies of his iconic art.   Five Hundred Years of Genius Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius demonstrates the full scope of Leonardo da Vinci\\u2019s remarkable genius as a painter, inventor, artist, anatomist, sculptor, engineer, musician and architect. The exhibition features 17 compelling themed areas of Da Vinci\\u2019s work, offering visitors an unmatched look inside the mind of the ultimate Renaissance man who laid the groundwork for some of modern society\\u2019s most impactful inventions, such as the helicopter, airplane, automobile, submarine, parachute and bicycle.   Italian artisans handcrafted all of the inventions brought to life for Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius, using the same techniques and materials from the Renaissance period. Scouring more than 6,000 pages from Da Vinci\\u2019s personal notebooks, the Artisans deciphered hidden clues, intentional mistakes and the unique mirror-image writing system that Da Vinci employed to keep his works top secret.   Visitors of Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius are invited to embrace the history, theory and objective behind each of Da Vinci\\u2019s designs and artworks through engaging and entertaining technologies. Guests will enjoy more than 200 unique pieces including 75 life-size machine inventions, entertaining animations of da Vinci\\u2019s most notable Renaissance works and an eye-opening, in-depth analysis of his most famous piece, \\u201CMona Lisa.\\u201D   Other highlights include reproductions of \\u201CVirgin of the Rocks\\u201D, and \\u201CThe Annunciation\\u201D, the controversial new Leonardo discovery \\u201CBella Principessa\\u201D, amazing anatomical sketches, the preparatory drawings of the \\u201CAnghiari Battle,\\u201D and educational animation presentations of \\u201CThe Last Supper\\u201D, displayed at actual size (29 x 14.5ft) where possible, the \\u201CVitruvian Man,\\u201D and the \\u201CSforza Horse\\u201D sculpture that offer never before seen perspectives on these famous works. Guests also will enjoy a glimpse into da Vinci\\u2019s mysterious alphabet and writing techniques as they browse touch-screen versions of his actual codices.   The Secrets of Mona Lisa \\u2013 Revelaed! \\\"Point a 240 megapixel camera with 13 color filters spanning the infrared, ultraviolet and normally visible spectra at the Mona Lisa, and what do you get? A whole new painting.\\u201D --Brandon Keim, Reporter, Wired Magazine   One highlight of Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius is the Secrets of Mona Lisa exhibit, featuring the findings of French scientific engineer and examiner of fine art, Pascal Cotte. Granted unprecedented access to \\u201CMona Lisa\\u201D by the French government and the Louvre Museum. Cotte was permitted to take \\u201CMona Lisa\\u201D off the wall and out of its frame to conduct a scientific analysis that revealed dozens of secrets about history\\u2019s most elusive art piece, all verified and approved by the Louvre Museum curators over a 2 year period. The exhibit showcases Cotte\\u2019s studies and 25 of his most compelling revelations, illustrated by 40 super-magnified, high-resolution sectional images exploring every aspect of the work.     Scientific Committee and Official Recognitions Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius was created with the assistance of the Museo Leonardo Da Vinci in Rome, Italy, Pascal Cotte of Lumiere Technologies, France, and a number of other experts in Italy and France. It is furthermore under the kind auspices of the City Council of Rome, the City Council of Florence and the City Council of Venice. Da Vinci \\u2013 The Genius celebrates one of the most revered and dynamic minds of all time. The exhibition has toured around 55 cities worldwide and attracted more than five million visitors.     Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1449646825\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-09\\/296.html\",\"tid\":\"296\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:45\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Dec 22, 2015 |Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-300 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0464|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center\",\"title\":\"Piano Recital by Yulianna Avdeeva\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Piano Recital by Yulianna Avdeeva is coming to Shanghai\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/54076fd12ae62f404ad0e2ddea820053.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Following her sensational win of the First Prize at the International Fryderyk Chopin Competition 2010 in Warsaw, Yulianna Avdeeva is fast establishing herself as an artist whose performances combine intense musicality and emotional depth with a formidable technique and intellectual rigour. She has performed with Czech Philharmonic, Warsaw Philharmonic Orchestra, Rundfunk-Sinfonieorchester Berlin, Finnish Radio Symphony orchestras, London Philharmonic Orchestra, Pittsburgh Symphony Orchestra, Orchestre Philharmonique Royal de Liège, Polish National Radio Symphony Orchestra, Pacific Symphony, Tchaikovsky Symphony Orchestra of Moscow Radio, Osaka Philharmonic Orchestra, to name just a few. Click HERE to buy tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1449043178\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-02\\/294.html\",\"tid\":\"294\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:45\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Dec 29, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-1680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0464|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center Concert Hall\",\"title\":\"Czech Philharmonic Shanghai New Year\\u2019s Concert\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\" the Czech Philharmonic will bring a New Year\\u2019s Concert to Shanghai\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/d9424307ced1f1b002c2580f5ad694df.jpg\",\"remark\":\"For over a century, the Czech Philharmonic has represented the pinnacle of Czech cultural achievement. In 1896, Dvořák conducted the orchestra\\u2019s debut performance at the Rudolfinum, still home to the orchestra\\u2019s Prague concerts. In 1908, Mahler conducted the Czech Philharmonic for the world premiere of his Symphony No.7. The orchestra\\u2019s reputation grew under Czech conductors Václav Talich, Rafael Kubelík, Karel Ančerl and Václav Neumann. Jiří Bělohlávek became Chief Conductor of the orchestra in 1990. Following his achievements, Gerd Albrecht, Vladimir Ashkenazy, Zdeněk Mácal and Eliahu Inbal took the role. In 2012, Jiří Bělohlávek returns as the orchestra\\u2019s Chief Conductor. Click HERE to buy tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1449042921\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-02\\/293.html\",\"tid\":\"293\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:45\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Jan 22, 2016-Jan 23, 2016|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=980-2280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0464|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center\",\"title\":\"Riccardo Muti & Chicago Symphony Orchestra\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Riccardo Muti leads Chicago Symphony Orchestra to Shanghai\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/5359200f4038f901425b53af1b934326.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Born in Naples, Italy, Riccardo Muti is one of the preeminent conductors of our day. In 2010, when he became the tenth music director of the world-renowned Chicago Symphony Orchestra (CSO), he had more than forty years of experience at the helm of Maggio Musicale Fiorentino (1968\\u20131980), the Philharmonia Orchestra (1972\\u20131982), the Philadelphia Orchestra (1980\\u20131992), and Teatro alla Scala (1986\\u20132005), and he has had a close relationship with the Vienna Philharmonic and the Salzburg Festival for more than 45 years.  He is an honorary member of Vienna\\u2019s Gesellschaft der Musikfreunde, the Vienna Hofmusikkapelle, the Vienna Philharmonic, and the Vienna State Opera.   Muti has received innumerable international honors. He is a Cavaliere di Gran Croce of the Italian Republic, Knight Commander of the British Empire, Officer of the French Legion of Honor, Knight of the Grand Cross First Class of the Order of Saint Gregory the Great and a recipient of the German Verdienstkreuz and the Russian Order of Friendship. Muti has also received Israel\\u2019s Wolf Prize for the arts, Sweden\\u2019s Birgit Nilsson Prize, and Spain\\u2019s Prince of Asturias Award. Passionate about teaching young musicians, Muti founded the Luigi Cherubini Youth Orchestra in 2004 and the Riccardo Muti Italian Opera Academy in 2015. Click HERE to buy tickets.  \",\"newstime\":\"1449042563\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-02\\/292.html\",\"tid\":\"292\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:45\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Jan 9, 2016|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=480-1280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0464|Add=Shanghai International Gymnastics Center, 777 Wuyi Rd \",\"title\":\"Love Radio Victor Wong 2016 Shanghai Concert\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/777d20a81b11afc18d3567d1dfd086d4.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Love Radio Victor Wong 2016 Shanghai Concert will be held at Shanghai International Gymnastics Center on Jan.9, 2016. Victor Wong Pin Kuan is a Chinese singer of Malaysian citizenship who has made his name in the Taiwan music scene. He formed a duo group with Michael Wong named Michael & Victor in 1995 when they first started out as singers under Rock Records. On Jan.9, 2016, with the warm love songs, he comes for you. Click HERE to buy tickets.  \",\"newstime\":\"1449041432\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-02\\/291.html\",\"tid\":\"291\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:45\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Dee 31, 2015-Jan 2, 2016|Time=2:30pm, 7:30pm|Tickets=280-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 苗江路800号上海儿童艺术剧场\",\"title\":\"Angel-voiced youngsters to serenade local audiences\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Renowned Italian children\\u2019s choir Piccolo Coro Dell\\u2019Antoniano will perform in Shanghai from December 31 to January 2. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3877cf7597bf0aaa55bacf98c066fe5c.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Renowned Italian children\\u2019s choir Piccolo Coro Dell\\u2019Antoniano will perform in Shanghai from December 31 to January 2. The choir was established in 1963, and has since become one of the most famous children\\u2019s choirs in the world \\u2014 as well as a Good Will Ambassador for UNICEF. The group has recorded more than 1,000 songs over a 50-year period, in addition to countless concerts and performances on television and radio. The concerts in Shanghai will be conducted by Sabrina Simoni and last for roughly 90 minutes. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1447839402\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-18\\/290.html\",\"tid\":\"290\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:45\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Dec 31, 2015|Time=2pm, 7:30pm, 10:30pm|Tickets:80-980 yuan|Phone=021-5386 6666|Add:523 Yan\\\\\'an Rd 延安东路523号\",\"title\":\"New Year concert from Vienna\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Vienna Johann Strauss Capelle will present a New Year concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on December 31.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/d069f0f2b80f2f7ced731bb4af49ceab.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Vienna Johann Strauss Capelle will present a New Year concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on December 31. The orchestra has given nearly 3,000 concerts since its debut in 1977 in countries such as Spain, Portugal, Italy, the United States, China and Japan. All the musicians wear red jackets and white trousers as their predecessors more than 100 years ago. HERE to buy the tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1447839153\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-18\\/289.html\",\"tid\":\"289\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through January 31, 2016|Time=10:30am-8:30pm|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Global Harbor, 3300 Zhongshan Rd N. 中山北路3300号上海环球港\",\"title\":\"Thirty top Picasso pieces on display\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Pablo Picasso (1881-1973) is an icon in Western modern art history. A special exhibition titled \\u201CThe Legend of Art: Picasso\\u201D is on display at Global Harbor Museum through to January 31, 2016.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3e553ef83edb1b7481ed0986bb2fb12c.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Pablo Picasso (1881-1973) is an icon in Western modern art history. A special exhibition titled \\u201CThe Legend of Art: Picasso\\u201D is on display at Global Harbor Museum through to January 31, 2016. As one of the greatest and most influential artists of the 20th century, Picasso, a Spanish painter, sculptor, printmaker, ceramist, stage designer, poet and playwright, spent most of his adult life in France.  He is known for co-founding the Cubist movement. Picasso, Henri Matisse and Marcel Duchamp are regarded as the three artists who most defined the revolutionary developments in arts in the opening decades of the 20th century.  The exhibition features nearly 87 artworks created by Picasso and 81 pictures on loan from a group of private collectors around the world. The art forms vary from canvas, print, sketches to paper cutting, sculpture and porcelain. During the first decade of the 20th century, Picasso\\u2019s style changed as he experimented with different theories, techniques, and ideas. His work is often categorized into periods. While the names of many of his later periods are debated, the most commonly accepted in his work are the Blue Period (1901\\u20131904), the Rose Period (1904\\u20131906), the African-influenced Period (1907\\u20131909), Analytic Cubism (1909\\u20131912), and Synthetic Cubism (1912\\u20131919), also referred to as the Crystal period. Yuexing Group chairman Ding Zuohong said: \\u201CThe exhibition includes nearly 30 important artworks by Picasso, such as \\u2018The Musketeer\\u2019 and \\u2018Melon Slice\\u2019 from his idyllic period and \\u2018Bacchanal with Acrobats\\u2019 from his new classicism period.\\u201D As well as the regular artworks on display, the organizer has developed an opportunity for patrons to fuse illusionary art with realistic art.  Visitors can wear 3D glasses to appreciate the masterpieces of Picasso from six different periods. It will also be fun to take your own photo and develop it into a \\u201CCubism\\u201D period picture.   HERE to buy the tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1446802570\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-06\\/288.html\",\"tid\":\"288\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 14-15, 2015|Time=10:30am, 7:30pm|Tickets=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theatre, 800 Miaojiang Rd 苗江路800号，上海儿童艺术剧院\",\"title\":\"Joja Wendt plans concerts in Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"In 1990, pianist Joja Wendt joined Joe Cocker\\u2019s world tour. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f9b40a6c1e090db97f8ed122e6a9ee00.jpg\",\"remark\":\"In 1990, pianist Joja Wendt joined Joe Cocker\\u2019s world tour. After several collaborations with famous artists, Wendt began to focus more on his own recitals. His style is a mix of jazz, classical music, ballads and rock. A recipient of the renowned Louis-Armstrong Award, Wendt was the top ticket selling artist in Germany among pianists. Furthermore, he presents his music in a very humorous and creative way. His strong stage presence and interaction with the audience are key factors in his success. \",\"newstime\":\"1446800592\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-06\\/287.html\",\"tid\":\"287\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 28-29, 2015|Time=10:20am, 2:30pm|Tickets=180 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=800 Miaojiang Rd, Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theatre 苗江路800号上海儿童艺术剧场\",\"title\":\"Tiny figurines come to life in magical children\\u2019s play\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"\\u201CA Mano\\u201D is a play told with small figurines fashioned out  of plasticine, like the ones children often make. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/de86242c0273f375c1936688d09bb839.jpg\",\"remark\":\"\\u201CA Mano\\u201D is a play told with small figurines fashioned out  of plasticine, like the ones children often make. The play tells a story of friendship on a temporary stage barricaded with furniture. With movements set to the music of Edith Piaf, the tiny characters first appear, then interact, then get to know each other and eventually forge ties based on small and shared dreams. These subtle exchanges slowly give rise to stronger feelings of caring and friendship. \\u201CA Mano\\u201D is a story brimming with imagination and inventiveness, told with  four hands and presented for the very first time in China. This is a definite must-see!   HERE to buy the tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1446633170\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-04\\/286.html\",\"tid\":\"286\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 20-22, 2015|Time=10:30am, 3pm, 7:30pm|Tickets=280-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1200 Shibo Ave, Mercedes-Benz Arena 世博大道1200号梅赛德斯奔驰文化中心\",\"title\":\"Heart-warming fun at \\u2018Magic Ice Festival\\u2019\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Get ready to enter a world of enchantment featuring the most magical moments from across the land as Disney On Ice presents \\u201CMagical Ice Festival.\\u201D\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/324d9245a54c373cabe5238699af6cd4.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Get ready to enter a world of enchantment featuring the most magical moments from across the land as Disney On Ice presents \\u201CMagical Ice Festival.\\u201D Audiences be whisked away into the wintery world of Disney\\u2019s Academy-Award winning film \\u201CFrozen,\\u201D to join royal sisters Elsa and Anna, the hilarious snowman Olaf, rugged mountainman Kristoff and his loyal reindeer Sven in a story full of action, adventure, magic and unforgettable characters. HERE to buy the tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1446633014\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-11-04\\/285.html\",\"tid\":\"285\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 3-4, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-300 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=288 Anfu Rd, Shanghai Drama Art Center 安福路288号上海话剧艺术中心\",\"title\":\"Indian adaptation of Shakespeare\\u2019s \\u2018Twelfth Night\\u2019\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"In the household of Olivia, two campaigns are being quietly waged \\u2014 one by lovesick Lord Orsino against the heart of the indifferent Olivia.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/a1609653228c415943a440ea838bae38.jpg\",\"remark\":\"In the household of Olivia, two campaigns are being quietly waged \\u2014 one by lovesick Lord Orsino against the heart of the indifferent Olivia; the other by an alliance of servants and hangers-on against her steward, the pompous Malvolio. Filled with a cast of unforgettable characters, this Indian adaptation of Shakespeare\\u2019s \\u201CTwelfth Night\\u201D mixes cruelty with high comedy and pangs of unrequited love. The comedy will be presented with Chinese and English subtitles.\",\"newstime\":\"1446199517\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-30\\/284.html\",\"tid\":\"284\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 15, 2015-January 17, 2016|Time=2pm; 7:15pm|Tickets=200-1280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Culture Square, 36 Yongjia Rd 永嘉路36号上海文化广场\",\"title\":\"War Horse\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The Chinese version of \\u201CWar Horse\\u201D will be staged at Shanghai Culture Square.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/aebc78736df91a8271fb5002b1ba87dd.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The Chinese version of \\u201CWar Horse\\u201D will be staged at Shanghai Culture Square. It is a play based on the book of the same name by children\'s writer Michael Morpurgo, adapted for stage by Nick Stafford. Its West End and Broadway productions met with critical acclaim and won several awards, including an Olivier Award and five Tony Awards. The Chinese production premiered at Beijing\\u2019s National Theatre Company of China in September and will tour to the theaters in Shanghai. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1446199395\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-30\\/283.html\",\"tid\":\"283\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 13-14, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=180-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People Ave. 人民大道300号上海大剧院\",\"title\":\"Modern dance examines meaning of life\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Life, conceived within fragile bodies, exists in a fierce world. To fight against the tide or be carried along with it, choices tend to play tricks  with our minds.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4bc395e4e5491e3b4ba1d3f93ce75477.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Life, conceived within fragile bodies, exists in a fierce world. To fight against the tide or be carried along with it, choices tend to play tricks  with our minds. But as long as the soul is free from binding, we can always find our way. As some might say, life is a battle field and one needs to fight back like a tiger to move forward. D.LAB will present the modern dance \\u201CFragile\\u201D at Shanghai Grand Theater. The group\\u2019s ides about dancing  transcend body movements. They consider all types of artistic expression integrated with music, performance, video and sound, painting and art to add value to any dance. \",\"newstime\":\"1445593181\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-23\\/282.html\",\"tid\":\"282\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 13, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=180-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"title\":\"Musicians to celebrate victory against Japan with concert\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Pianist Gong Tianpeng, conductor Zhang Liang, violist Liu Xiao and the Shanghai Opera House chorus will present a concert that celebrates the 70th anniversary of victory in the War of Resistance against Japanese Aggression at Shanghai Symphony Hall on December 13. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/efa2e597778dd9eca9bbe101765dc5b3.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Pianist Gong Tianpeng, conductor Zhang Liang, violist Liu Xiao and the Shanghai Opera House chorus will present a concert that celebrates the 70th anniversary of victory in the War of Resistance against Japanese Aggression at Shanghai Symphony Hall on December 13.  Described by The Washington Post as an artist \\u201Cwith the confidence of a weathered veteran and a welcome unbridled quality to his playing,\\u201D Gong has established himself as one of the most gifted musicians of his generation. At 18, Gong has become an internationally active concert pianist and a six-time American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers National Award-winning composer since 2006. \",\"newstime\":\"1445593016\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-23\\/281.html\",\"tid\":\"281\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December 18-20， 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"title\":\"\\\\\'Seven Young Goats and the Wolf\\u2019\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Adapted from the classic Grimms\\u2019 fairy tale into an easily digestible and educational stage play, \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7ecdd23ba4cc815b06350c2ccf703c91.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Adapted from the classic Grimms\\u2019 fairy tale into an easily digestible and educational stage play, the \\u201CSeven Young Goats and the Wolf\\u201D features adorable puppet costumes, gorgeous stage effects, melodious songs and refined performances. This lively story teaches children how to identify risks, to avoid being cheated and to protect themselves from being harmed. Children will learn the immensity of maternal love and the power that courage can bring. The play also tells children the importance of getting along with others and respecting those with different values. Children will quickly be drawn in by this compelling story. \\\\ \",\"newstime\":\"1445332688\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-20\\/280.html\",\"tid\":\"280\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 28， 2015|Time=7:45pm|Tickets=180-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"title\":\"Fleishers to play Brahms, Debussy and Schubert\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"American pianist and conductor Leon Fleisher and Katherine Jacobson Fleisher will give a concert at the Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 28.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/cbae391066ad2bf8c1a37cc04301add7.jpg\",\"remark\":\"American pianist and conductor Leon Fleisher and Katherine Jacobson Fleisher will give a concert at the Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 28. Those attending can expect to hear Johannes Brahms\\u2019 \\u201CLiebesliederWaltzer, Op. 52a 20,\\u2019\\u201D Claude Debussy\\u2019s \\u201CLa Puerta del Vino from Préludes, Book II 4,\\u201D and Franz Schubert \\u2019s \\u201CFantasy in F minor for piano four-hands, D. 940 20.\\u201D Leon Fleisher was born in San Francisco into a poor Jewish family and started studying the piano at age four. He made his public debut at age eight and played with the New York Philharmonic under Pierre Monteux at the age of 16. Monteux famously called him \\u201Cthe pianistic find of the century.\\u201D \",\"newstime\":\"1445332480\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-20\\/279.html\",\"tid\":\"279\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:46\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 31, 2015|Time=7:45pm|Tickets=280-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall, 1380 Fuxing Rd M. 复兴中路1380号，上海交响乐团音乐厅\",\"title\":\"Bostridge at Shanghai Symphony Hall\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The acclaimed tenor Ian Bostridge will perform with guitarist Yang Xuefei at Shanghai Symphony Hall on October 31.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/40bf7b71492855ba33189ec64142a4f3.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The acclaimed tenor Ian Bostridge will perform with guitarist Yang Xuefei at Shanghai Symphony Hall on October 31. Songs include Dominick Argento\\u2019s \\u201CLetters from Composers,\\u201D John Dowland\\u2019s \\u201CIn Darkness Let Me Dwell\\u201D and Franz Schubert\\u2019s \\u201CDie Mainacht, D.194.\\u201D Bostridge was a post-doctoral fellow in history at Corpus Christi College, Oxford, before embarking on a full-time career as a singer. He has performed at some of the world\\u2019s major concert halls and at festivals in Salzburg, Edinburgh, Munich and Vienna. He made his operatic debut in 1994 as Lysander in Britten\\u2019s \\u201CA Midsummer Night\\u2019s Dream\\u201D with Opera Australia at the Edinburgh Festival. In 1999, he premiered a songcycle written for him by Hans Werner Henze. \",\"newstime\":\"1444990325\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-16\\/277.html\",\"tid\":\"277\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:47\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 16-18, 2015|Time=11am,5pm,7:30pm,11pm|Tickets:80-680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"title\":\"World\\u2019s longest opera coming to Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"\\u201CDer Ring des Nibelungen\\u201D is the longest opera in the world. It consists of four parts including Das Rheingold, Die Walküre, Siegfried and Gotterdammerung.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/0e4bd03b5361afb13b9bb34b921ddded.jpg\",\"remark\":\"\\u201CDer Ring des Nibelungen\\u201D is the longest opera in the world. It consists of four parts including Das Rheingold, Die Walküre, Siegfried and Gotterdammerung. The complete 24-hour Ring cycle was launched by Gustav Kuhn at the Tirol Festival in 2003. Since then, as Kuhn\\u2019s reading has both broadened and deepened, this opera has also been improved and the work as a whole has a more integrated feel than ever before. The opera was written by Richard Wagner over a period of 24 years.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1444730255\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-13\\/275.html\",\"tid\":\"275\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:47\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 18, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Phone=021-5292 0164|Venue=Shanghai Culture Square\",\"title\":\"Dance legend Guillem presents \\u2018Life in Progress\\u2019\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Famous dancer Sylvie Guillem will present her final dance program, \\u201CLife in Progress,\\u201D a Sadler \\\\\'s Wells London Production co-produced with Les Nuits de Fourvière, China Shanghai International Arts Festival and Guillem.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/ccc90e7dd969e09f17a445833460d92d.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Famous dancer Sylvie Guillem will present her final dance program, \\u201CLife in Progress,\\u201D a Sadler \'s Wells London Production co-produced with Les Nuits de Fourvière, China Shanghai International Arts Festival and Guillem. She will dance two new works including Technê, a solo choreographed by Sacred Monsters\\u2019creator Akram Khan and Here & After, a duet with Italian dancer Emanuela Montanari from La Scala. Guillem, a world famous dancer with an extensive career at the Paris Opera Ballet, has diversified as a dancer forging an undisputable reputation as a major force in the world of contemporary dance. Her awards include an Olivier award, a Golden Lion for Lifetime Achievement by the Venice Biennale, the Officier de la Légion d\\u2019Honneur, Commandeur dans l\\u2019Ordre National du Mérite, Officier des Arts et Lettres, and, in Britain, an honorary CBE.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!  \",\"newstime\":\"1444730011\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-10-13\\/274.html\",\"tid\":\"274\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:47\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 3-4, 2015|Add=Binjiang Greenland in Xuhui District 徐汇滨江绿地\",\"title\":\"2015 Storm Electronic Music Festival\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The 2015 Storm Electronic Music Festival, the largest outdoor electronic dance music festival in China, will be staged on October 3 and 4 at Binjiang Greenland. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/8cef4b9004c0beae44a0b9282213c3bc.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The 2015 Storm Electronic Music Festival, the largest outdoor electronic dance music festival in China, will be staged on October 3 and 4 at Binjiang Greenland. Scheduled to perform are electronic music heavyweights Tiesto, Skrillex, and Avicii. Tiesto was named \\u201Cthe greatest DJ of all time\\u201D by Mixmag, while Skrillex has won three Grammy Awards. The French Apple Art Festival will also run between September 30 and October 10 at Shanghai Chenshan Botanic Garden. The festival will feature some 1,000 apples decorated with images of the Mona Lisa, the Summer Palace and other scenes.\",\"newstime\":\"1443513538\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-29\\/273.html\",\"tid\":\"273\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:47\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 30-October 7, 2015|Add=Chenshan Botanical Garden, 3888 Chenhua Rd 辰花公路3888号，辰山植物园\",\"title\":\"French Apple Art Festival\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"These apples were cultivated at the Les Jardins Fruitiers de Laquenexy in Moselle, France, using an old but refined technique. As they grew, these apples were covered by black paper cut into different patterns \\u2014 the areas which were not exposed to the sun did not turn red, allowing artistic patterns to emerge in the lighter-colored areas.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/023f2fe53bebb776379f0c06ee872035.jpg\",\"remark\":\"These apples were cultivated at the Les Jardins Fruitiers de Laquenexy in Moselle, France, using an old but refined technique. As they grew, these apples were covered by black paper cut into different patterns \\u2014 the areas which were not exposed to the sun did not turn red, allowing artistic patterns to emerge in the lighter-colored areas. According to organizers, out of 1,000 apples this process will only work correctly for four or five. The apples will be available to purchase at prices up to 1,000 yuan (US$161). This is the first time such apples have been displayed outside France. Also on display will be seven large-scale mosaics each made from thousands of different colored apples.\",\"newstime\":\"1443513436\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-29\\/272.html\",\"tid\":\"272\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:47\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 3, 2015|Time=8pm|Tickets=280-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"title\":\"Taiwan Philharmonic\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Taiwan Philharmonic, led by conductor Shao-Chia Lu and violinist Cho-Liang Lin, will present a concert on November 3 at Shanghai Symphony Hall. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3a41ed5c98c29ad6f6300013acecad4f.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Taiwan Philharmonic, led by conductor Shao-Chia Lu and violinist Cho-Liang Lin, will present a concert on November 3 at Shanghai Symphony Hall. The program includes Huang Ruo\\u2019s \\u201CBecoming Another,\\u201D Tchaikovsky\\u2019s \\u201CViolin Concerto in D major,\\u201D and Rachmaninov\\u2019s Symphony No.2 in E minor. Founded in 1986, the Taiwan Philharmonic has given thousands of concerts, launched many music activities and become one of the top orchestras in Asia. Taiwan Philharmonic works regularly with and internationally acclaimed musicians, such as Lorin Maazel and Rudolf Barshai. \",\"newstime\":\"1442913527\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-22\\/271.html\",\"tid\":\"271\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:47\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 7, 2015|Time=7:45pm|Tickets=80-280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add:1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"title\":\"New Cologne Piano Trio pops by in November\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The trio will present a concert at Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 7. The Cologne Piano Trio comprises violin soloist Walter Schreiber, cello soloist Joanna Schryn and pianist Xin Sui. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/604b2640b094dd46d0d92781dc6cdd2b.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The trio will present a concert at Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 7. The Cologne Piano Trio comprises violin soloist Walter Schreiber, cello soloist Joanna Schryn and pianist Xin Sui. Xin has succeeded Guenter Ludwig, who retired. They have performed many concerts in China. Recently the threesome released their first CD with masterpieces from Ludwig van Beethoven. \\u201CThe idea of our new style is to use our highly developed skills on the instruments paired with virtuosity to give life to the music notes. Tolerance paired with highly emotional expressions is significant for our music,\\u201D they said in a press release. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1442913271\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-22\\/270.html\",\"tid\":\"270\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:47\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 1, 2015|Time=7:45pm|Tickets=180-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"title\":\"Xu and friends plan special performance\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Xu Zhong and his friends Ni Haiye, Liu Yunjie, Manuel Kastl and Klaidi Sahatci will perform at Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 1. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/c38c8efbffc174e467ef65afbc70f467.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Xu Zhong and his friends Ni Haiye, Liu Yunjie, Manuel Kastl and Klaidi Sahatci will perform at Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 1. They will play Schumann\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quintet in E flat Major\\u201D and Shostakovich\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quintet in G minor.\\u201D Xu is one of the most internationally renowned Chinese pianists and conductors. He is the founding member and artistic director of the China Shanghai International Piano Competition, deputy chairman of Shanghai Oriental Art Center Arts Committee. Xu has won prestigious international piano competitions since 1988. He has collaborated with some of the world\\u2019s best musicians and orchestras. \",\"newstime\":\"1442559617\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-18\\/269.html\",\"tid\":\"269\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:47\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 1-2, 2015|Time=2:30pm, 7:30pm|Tickets=180-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"title\":\"Music from the \\u2018Frozen Plane\\u2019 documentary\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Shanghai Opera House Orchestra will perform the score from the BBC television series \\u201CFrozen Plane\\u201D about the world\\u2019s polar regions.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/14db930118b34ac0bf391716cdfae0a8.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Shanghai Opera House Orchestra will perform the score from the BBC television series \\u201CFrozen Plane\\u201D about the world\\u2019s polar regions. The music will be accompanied by the documentary in high-definition. George Fenton composed the score. \\u201CFrozen Planet\\\" documents the melting polar ice and the creatures living that live in these regions. \",\"newstime\":\"1442559380\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-18\\/268.html\",\"tid\":\"268\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:47\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=December24，2015|Time=180-380 yuan|Tickets=180-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"title\":\"Tang, Huang to perform in December\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"To celebrate the 70th anniversary of the victory in World War II, a concert led by conductor Tang Muhai and violist Huang Mengla will be presented at Shanghai Symphony Hall on December 24. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/35d8e2513bc030a0db999158c158abee.jpg\",\"remark\":\"To celebrate the 70th anniversary of the victory in World War II, a concert led by conductor Tang Muhai and violist Huang Mengla will be presented at Shanghai Symphony Hall on December 24. The program includes Aram Khachaturian\\u2019s \\u201CViolin Concerto in D minor\\u201D and Dmitri Shostakovich\\u2019s \\u201CSymphony No. 9 in E-flat major.\\u201D Tang initially learned music with his parents, and later studied composition and conducting at the Shanghai Conservatory of Music, receiving a diploma in both. Tang won a 2002 Grammy Award for Best Classical Contemporary Composition for Christopher Rouse\\u2019s Concert de Gaudí. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1441962497\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-11\\/266.html\",\"tid\":\"266\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:48\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 26, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=180-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Concert Hall, 523 Yan\\\\\'an Rd E. 上海音乐厅， 延安东路523号\",\"title\":\"Ditto will show some love for Schubert and Brahms\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The ensemble Ditto will present a concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on September 26. The program includes Schubert\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quintet in A major\\u201D and Brahms\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quartet in G minor.\\u201D\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/e86cdd425935c0e248462ba90c66c276.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The ensemble Ditto will present a concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on September 26. The program includes Schubert\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quintet in A major\\u201D and Brahms\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Quartet in G minor.\\u201D Ditto, formed in 2007, has a legion of fans from teenage girls to women in their thirties. They ranked first in ticket sales at Seoul Arts Center\\u2019s concert hall for the first half of this year. They also ranked first in 2008 and 2009. Ditto first gained fame by performing on a real-time live broadcast concert for the portal site NAVER. They have also held a street concert to reach a broader audience. Another characteristic of the ensemble is that members perform long solos in order to raise the reputation of the group. \",\"newstime\":\"1441961200\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-09-11\\/265.html\",\"tid\":\"265\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:48\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 7, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=280-880 yuan|Phone+021-5292 0164|Add=1380 Fuxing Rd M. Shanghai Symphony Hall 上海交响乐团音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"title\":\"Full metal racket\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"For a blast of German Brass, head to Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 7.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3680b45cab33949365615a7f81a0e823.jpg\",\"remark\":\"For a blast of German Brass, head to Shanghai Symphony Hall on November 7. Founded in 1974 as a brass quintet by Enrique Cresp, German Brass creates \\u201Cdiversity in unity  \\u2014 producing a unique collective sound with 10 individualists and renowned soloists from outstanding German orchestras. They play chamber music but with symphonic magnificence and dynamics that only brass instrumentalists can produce. \",\"newstime\":\"1440748534\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-28\\/264.html\",\"tid\":\"264\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:48\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 4-5，2015|Time=10:30am, 2:30pm|Tickets=180-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"title\":\"It\\u2019s grrreat!\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Adapted and directed by David Wood, Judith Kerr\\u2019s Olivier Award nominated \\u201CThe Tiger Who Came to Tea\\u201D is the perfect slice of teatime mayhem, with sing-a-long tunes, oodles of magic and interactive fun for children aged three plus and their families.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/aa0b86649fcd9ff836b2b8cae9592ee9.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Adapted and directed by David Wood, Judith Kerr\\u2019s Olivier Award nominated \\u201CThe Tiger Who Came to Tea\\u201D is the perfect slice of teatime mayhem, with sing-a-long tunes, oodles of magic and interactive fun for children aged three plus and their families. The tiger comes to have afternoon tea? Maybe it sounds incredible. However, in the world of Kerr\\u2019s picture books, it seems very natural. When Sophie and her mummy welcome the hungry tiger to tea, he proceeds to eat all the sandwiches, buns and biscuits \\u2014 and manages to the drink all the water in the tap! And if you\\u2019ve never had a tiger arrive for tea, then this lovable production is the perfect way to show the whole family how to behave the next time you ring the doorbell.  \",\"newstime\":\"1440748321\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-28\\/263.html\",\"tid\":\"263\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:48\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 4-6, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=80-680 yuan|Add=shanghai Grand Theater, 300 Renmin Ave. 上海大剧院 人民大道300号\",\"title\":\"Endangered ibis inspiration for new dance show\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The crested ibis \\u2014 with its red face and pink, orange wings \\u2014 has long been appreciated throughout East Asia for its beautiful appearance and as a symbol of good luck and happiness.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/33fce0f5c93361d3995b4dd7626da442.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The crested ibis \\u2014 with its red face and pink, orange wings \\u2014 has long been appreciated throughout East Asia for its beautiful appearance and as a symbol of good luck and happiness. The bird itself though has not been so lucky. Starting in the early 20th century, urbanization across the region has pushed the species to the brink of extinction. The striking bird and its harrowing story are the subject of a dance drama entitled \\u201CCrested Ibises,\\u201D which is coming to the Shanghai Grand Theater this October. The touring show, presented by Shanghai Dance Theater, was performed in 19 cities across Japan over the summer. The show\\u2019s creator, Chen Feihua, was inspired by video images of the crested ibis shown at the Japan Pavilion during the World Expo Shanghai 2010. \\u201CThey were so elegant and beautiful, just like dancers moving on stage,\\u201D says Chen, who is also the president of Shanghai Dance Theater. After learning about the human efforts to pull the species back from extinction, Chen became even more determined to bring the bird and its story to the stage. In ancient times, the crested ibis was widely seen and admired in both China and Japan. The species began to dwindle in the 20th century as growing cities in both countries lead to habitat loss. The bird was believed to have been wiped out completely in the wild until 1981, when seven crested ibises were spotted in Yangxian County of central China\\u2019s Shaanxi Province. Scientists from China and Japan eventually joined hands to save the crested ibis. With the help of artificial insemination and conservation areas, there are now an estimated 2,000 crested ibises living in China, plus another 200 in Japan. \\u201CWe are not the only residents on this Earth. We should leave living space for other creatures while protecting ours as well,\\u201D says Chen. Work on Chen\\u2019s show was finally completed last year with the help of playwright Luo Huaizhen and director Tong Ruirui. At the beginning of the show, man coexists peacefully with the ibis in a lush natural environment. Later, the bird is shown slowing succumbing to the forces of urbanization. According to Chen, the bird\\u2019s near extinction is represented by a glass cover descending upon the drama\\u2019s main avian protagonist, turning her into a specimen. \\u201CI\\u2019m glad this message is being delivered,\\u201D says Chen. \\u201CI think our success largely lies in the realization that environmental protection is a shared problem facing people all over the world. This has helped pave the way for cross-cultural communication.\\u201D Pulling off dance moves based on the crested ibis was no easy feat, according to Zhu Jiejing, the show\\u2019s lead dancer during its recent tour of Japan. Many of the show\\u2019s moves involve unfamiliar gestures and poses, such as exaggerated forearm movements meant to represent the bird\\u2019s natural movements. \\u201CThis is the first time the crested ibis has been depicted in dance, so we had no available models to learn from. We had to make things distinctive,\\u201D says Zhu. \\u201CThe crested ibis is not dazzling like the peacock and does not have the wide wingspan of the swan. Fragility and sensitivity are the soul of the crested ibis.\\u201D   \",\"newstime\":\"1440747884\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-28\\/262.html\",\"tid\":\"262\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:48\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 19|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=280-1280 yuan|Add:Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 Renmin Ave. 上海大剧院 人民大道300号\",\"title\":\"WDR Symphony Orchestra Cologne plans big concert\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"WDR Symphony Orchestra Cologne with its conductor Jukka-Pekka Saraste and violinist Frank Peter Zimmermann will present a concert on October 19 at Shanghai Grand Theater. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3b38aa79b536564564850b25dfcd4156.jpg\",\"remark\":\"WDR Symphony Orchestra Cologne with its conductor Jukka-Pekka Saraste and violinist Frank Peter Zimmermann will present a concert on October 19 at Shanghai Grand Theater. The program includes Brahms Violin Concerto and Brahms Symphony No. 4. Existing for more than 65 years, the WDR Symphony Orchestra Cologne is one of the most important broadcast orchestras in Europe. Since the 2010-11 season, Saraste has been the chief conductor of the orchestra. Zimmermann has performed with all major orchestras and many renowned conductors around the world.  \",\"newstime\":\"1440747718\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-28\\/261.html\",\"tid\":\"261\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:48\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 15, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-680 yuan|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd. 上海东方艺术中心,丁香路425号\",\"title\":\"Mikhail Pletnev to play piano recital in Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Russian pianist Mikhail Pletnev will give a recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 15. He will play Beethoven\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Sonata No. 10\\u201D and \\u201CPiano Sonata No. 17\\u201D and Scriabin\\u2019s \\u201C24 Preludes.\\u201D\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/631770d4b81c241c37a9b6dd863d1782.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Russian pianist Mikhail Pletnev will give a recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 15. He will play Beethoven\\u2019s \\u201CPiano Sonata No. 10\\u201D and \\u201CPiano Sonata No. 17\\u201D and Scriabin\\u2019s \\u201C24 Preludes.\\u201D  Born into a Russian family of musicians, Pletnev went to study at the Moscow Central School of Music at age 13 and won the first prize of the 1978 Tchaikovsky International Piano Competition at age 21. He became international famous overnight and his recordings garnered numerous prizes, including the 2005 Grammy Award. Pletnev is now one of Russia\'s most respected artists. \",\"newstime\":\"1440576990\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-26\\/260.html\",\"tid\":\"260\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:48\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 4, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=280-480|Add=Shanghai Concert Hall, 523 East Yanan Rd. 延安东路523号，上海音乐厅\",\"title\":\"Clarinetist Meyer\\\\\'s solo show\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Paul Meyer will come to Shanghai and give a concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on September 4. Songs include Claude Debussy\\u2019s \\u201CPremière rapsodie for Clarinet and Piano,\\u201D Leonard Bernstein\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Clarinet and Piano\\u201D and Alban Berg\\u2019s \\u201CFour Pieces for Clarinet and Piano, Op. 5.\\u201D\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f47bff825c292cee8cdae45e059760b2.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Paul Meyer will come to Shanghai and give a concert at Shanghai Concert Hall on September 4. Songs include Claude Debussy\\u2019s \\u201CPremière rapsodie for Clarinet and Piano,\\u201D Leonard Bernstein\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Clarinet and Piano\\u201D and Alban Berg\\u2019s \\u201CFour Pieces for Clarinet and Piano, Op. 5.\\u201D Born in 1965, Meyer is recognized as one of the most outstanding clarinet soloists in this era. He made his debut in 1982, at the age of 17, as laureate of the prestigious Eurovision Contest. In 1983, he was appointed principal clarinet with the Orchestre de l\\u2019Opéra National de Lyon, then with the Ensemble intercontemporain in 1984 and with the Opéra de Paris in 1985. He soon left these orchestras to begin an international career as soloist. Simultaneously his passion for conducting led him early on to study with Charles Bruck at the Pierre Monteux school in Maine.     \",\"newstime\":\"1440576453\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-26\\/259.html\",\"tid\":\"259\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=November 12, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=480-1280 yuan|Phone=52920164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 丁香路425号 上海东方艺术中心\",\"title\":\"Violin Rectial by Itzhak Perlman\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The Israeli conductor Itzhak Perlman will present the violin recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on November 12. The programs include Leclair\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Violin and Piano in D major\\u201D, Brahms\\u2019s \\u201CSonatensatz in C minor\\u201D and Franck\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Violin and Piano in A Major\\u201D.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/dff3477c5f55b77e92a6dd785729186f.jpg\",\"remark\":\"    The Israeli conductor Itzhak Perlman will present the violin recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on November 12. The programs include Leclair\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Violin and Piano in D major\\u201D, Brahms\\u2019s \\u201CSonatensatz in C minor\\u201D and Franck\\u2019s \\u201CSonata for Violin and Piano in A Major\\u201D. Born in 1945, Perlman started his music life at the age of three and completed his initial training at the Academy of Music in Tel Aviv. He has performed as conductor with every major orchestras and in recitals and festival around the world. Perlam also has been a soloist for a number of film scores such as the theme of the 1993 film Schindler\'s List by John Williams, which subsequently won an Academy Award for Best Original Score. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1439883207\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-18\\/258.html\",\"tid\":\"258\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 26-27, 2015|Time=10:30am, 2:30pm|Tickets=80-380 yuan|Phone=4009215686|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 苗江路800号, 上海儿童艺术剧场\",\"title\":\"Fun for children with the dancing Moomins\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Dancing Moominvalley, a dance production based on Tove Jansson\\u2019s book \\u201CThe Tales from the Moominvalley,\\u201D will be presented at Shanghai Children\\u2019s Theater in September.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4eb1c8e3473636f22426ee1c4d13cc1d.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Dancing Moominvalley, a dance production based on Tove Jansson\\u2019s book \\u201CThe Tales from the Moominvalley,\\u201D will be presented at Shanghai Children\\u2019s Theater in September.  A visually spectacular, fully composed contemporary dance piece for the whole family, Dancing Moominvalley takes a new approach to the Moomins, but the themes will be familiar to those who have read the books.  \\u201CDancing Moominvalley @ Shanghai Expo\\u201D was presented at Shanghai World Expo 2010. It received a Shanghai Expo 2010 Culture Award, the only such award received by the Finnish Pavilion Culture Program.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1439878446\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-18\\/257.html\",\"tid\":\"257\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 15-17,2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=100-200 yuan|Phone=53866666|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 Renmin Ave. 上海大剧院 人民大道300号\",\"title\":\"Tiger\\u2019 looks at life of a dysfunctional family\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"UK-Barrowland Ballet will make its Asian debut at Shanghai Grand Theater on September 15.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4201b7bac166adf29358518528b65ff2.jpg\",\"remark\":\"UK-Barrowland Ballet will make its Asian debut at Shanghai Grand Theater on September 15. \\u201CTiger\\u201D is an incredibly moving piece about a dysfunctional family whose three members, Mom, Dad and their daughter Poppy, have become unable to interact and love each other. Mom spends her day cleaning obsessively, while Dad is buried in his work. Both are too wrapped up in their own worlds to notice their daughter is lonely and unhappy. \\u201CTiger\\u201D takes you on a sensory adventure. Up close to the action the audience surrounds the family\\u2019s home as it is transformed from a sterile space into a shifting world of live sound, color and explosive movement.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1439535089\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-14\\/256.html\",\"tid\":\"256\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 8-October 11|Phone=5033-9801|Add=Shanghai Himalayas Museum, 869 Yinghua Rd 樱花路869号\",\"title\":\"Dog Designs, kid artists\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"From August 8 to October 11, the Shanghai Himalayas Museum will host an exhibition entitled \\u201CArchi-tecture for Dogs.\\u201D\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/81a582616c3c4635799fed6095a1cf5d.jpg\",\"remark\":\"From August 8 to October 11, the Shanghai Himalayas Museum will host an exhibition entitled \\u201CArchi-tecture for Dogs.\\u201D This whimsical exhibit is curated by famed Japanese designer and MUJI art director Kenya Hara. On view will be 14 doghouses created by some of the world\\u2019s top designers and architectural firms, including Shigeru Ban, Ma Yansong and Altelier Bow-Wow. Launched in 2012, this exhibition hastoured the world and is now returning to the Shanghai Himalayas Mu- seum for the sixth time. \\u201CThis exhibition is not merely about architecture for animals or building houses for dogs. Through this opportunity to re-ob-serve the living environment of dogs, hopefully we can see our own surroundings, and ourselves, in a new way\\u201D. Visitors can also bring their dogs to play in a specially- designed \\u201Cpuppy park\\u201D located outside of the main display area. In addition to this exhibition, the museum is offering art lessons for children between seven and 12 years-of-age. But rather than drilling basic skills such as line drawing or sketching, the museum\\u2019s teachers hope to foster an interest in art and culture among children. Brainstorm- ing is also used to develop storylines and ideas, which are then painted by the students. \\u201CCapturing the same subject or merely copying is very boring. We want the children to gain knowledge while they are painting and to have their own thoughts about their works,\\u201D Wendy Zheng, a project as- sistant with the museum\\u2019s education department.   \",\"newstime\":\"1439288131\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-11\\/255.html\",\"tid\":\"255\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 24-25, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=380-880 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"title\":\"Concerts of BBC Philharmonic\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Founded in 1934, BBC Philharmonic is famous for its artistic innovation, outstanding performance, and a broad repertoire. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7ba6ac45c414f1be47d3264ad3742108.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Founded in 1934, BBC Philharmonic is famous for its artistic innovation, outstanding performance, and a broad repertoire. The orchestra has published more than 200 albums with critical acclaims. Its members include conductor Juanjo Menachem, violist Sarah Zhang and cellist Trey Lee. Menachem is one of the most celebrated conductors in Spain. Sarah Zhang, a Korean-American genius, gained fame when she was only 8 and has won many international awards since. She was invited to play in the 90th anniversary concert of the Philadelphia Orchestra. Trey Lee, the first Asian to win a top prize at the prestigious Antonia Janigro Cello Competition, has collaborated with esteemed conductors, composers and orchestras worldwide. He was described by The New York Times as \\u201Cexcellent cellist\\u2026 with enveloping richness and lyrical sensitivity.\\u201D       BBC Philharmonic will present two concerts at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 24-25.   2015\\/10\\/24      BRITTEN | Simple Symphony SIBELIUS | Violin Concerto in d-minor No.47 ELGAR | Enigma Variations 2015\\/10\\/25 GLINKA | Overture to Ruslan and Lyudmila  ELGAR | Cello Concerto in E minor LIQING YANG | Introduction, Chant and Allegro XUNTIAN HE | Pipa Pattern GUOHUI YE | Picture of Dancing Dragon MINGWU YIN | Ink Wash Painting *Program is subject to change Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1439187466\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-10\\/254.html\",\"tid\":\"254\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 30-31, 2015|Time=10:30am, 2:30pm, 7:30pm|Tickets=280-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"title\":\"Exciting new production of \\u2018The Sound of Music\\u2019\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"In 2007, Salzburg Marionette Theatre premiered a new production of \\u201CThe Sound of Music,\\u201D directed by Richard Hamburger. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/74260cb8606d0853521ea007f005e428.jpg\",\"remark\":\"In 2007, Salzburg Marionette Theatre premiered a new production of \\u201CThe Sound of Music,\\u201D directed by Richard Hamburger. Salzburg was home of the Von Trapp family and was featured heavily in the 1965 film production of the same name starring Julie Andrews and Christopher Plummer. The play tells the story of Maria and the family of captain Georg Von Trapp, who offers Maria a job as a governess to his children. The Salzburg Marionette Theatre was established in 1913 by professor Anton Aicher and is one of the oldest continuously open marionette theaters in the world. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1439186879\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-10\\/253.html\",\"tid\":\"253\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 20, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"title\":\"Surprising MozART\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"MozART group created a musical cabaret, where the music, not the words, are the source of joy and laughter.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4556084238237ed6a9f82a30967ad7f7.jpg\",\"remark\":\"MozART group created a musical cabaret, where the music, not the words, are the source of joy and laughter. Taking a classical composition as their canvas, the group analyzes its structure and theme, then surrounds it with musical associations. Listeners are often left surprised and amazed, laughing and sometimes, even moved to tears. The musicians of the MozART group have been playing together since 1995. The quartet has performed with musicians from around the world, including shows with mime Irek Krosny and the multitalented Bobby McFerrin. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1438677956\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-04\\/252.html\",\"tid\":\"252\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 23, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"title\":\"Piano recital covers Beethoven and Brahms\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Sergio Tiempo will give a piano recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 23. The programs include Brahms\\u2019 \\u201CIntermezzo in B minor, Op. 119 No. 1,\\u201D Beethoven\\u2019s \\u201CSonata in F minor, Op. 57,\\u201D and many other classic tunes.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/ba03ed27b82b86be940a2367f87b6881.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Sergio Tiempo will give a piano recital at Shanghai Oriental Art Center on October 23. The programs include Brahms\\u2019 \\u201CIntermezzo in B minor, Op. 119 No. 1,\\u201D Beethoven\\u2019s \\u201CSonata in F minor, Op. 57,\\u201D and many other classic tunes. Born in Caracas, Venezuela, Tiempo began his piano studies with his mother, Lyl Tiempo, at the age of two and made his concert debut when he had just turned three. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1438677744\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-08-04\\/251.html\",\"tid\":\"251\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 5, 2015|Time:1:30pm, 4pm|Tickets:80-180 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add:Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"title\":\"Wizards, lions and magic\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"This children\\u2019s play is based on \\u201CThe Wizard of the Emerald City\\u201D books by Russian writer Alexander Volkov, who loosely was inspired by the \\u201CThe Wonderful Wizard of Oz\\u201D series. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/99df2fdd6f945e487158c9a7471adce0.jpg\",\"remark\":\"This children\\u2019s play is based on \\u201CThe Wizard of the Emerald City\\u201D books by Russian writer Alexander Volkov, who loosely was inspired by the \\u201CThe Wonderful Wizard of Oz\\u201D series.    \\u201CEmerald City\\u201D follows Ellie and her friends Totoshka, Iron Lumberjack, Scarecrow, and Lion on a journey to Emerald City, where a place full of magic, unusual inhabitants and wonderful animals await. Ellie and her friends face numerous challenges on the way to Emerald City and learn the importance of kindness, friendship and self-confidence.  Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1438327344\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-31\\/250.html\",\"tid\":\"250\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:49\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 3-4, 2015|Time=10:30am, 2:30pm|Tickets:180 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add:Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"title\":\"Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"It is a children\\u2019s classic written by the Grimm brothers. The tale unfolds with an evil queen speaking to a magic mirror. She learns that her stepdaughter Snow White is the \\u201Cfairest in the land.\\u201D\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/676dd3ba70ab2330c4fefeb22dd30a2c.jpg\",\"remark\":\"It is a children\\u2019s classic written by the Grimm brothers. The tale unfolds with an evil queen speaking to a magic mirror. She learns that her stepdaughter Snow White is the \\u201Cfairest in the land.\\u201D   Infuriated, the stepmother uses her powers to get rid of the girl so she can be the only beautiful woman in her kingdom. Meanwhile, Snow White meets some kind dwarfs in the forest who after become her  friends. Fighting for good, she goes through many breathtaking adventures and finds her true love. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1438327133\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-31\\/249.html\",\"tid\":\"249\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through August 8, 2015|Time=11am-7pm, closed on Mondays|Add=200 Huayuangang Rd 花园港路200号\",\"title\":\"Top designer showcases best of British\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Renowned British designer Thomas Heatherwick, whose work ranges from his beautiful London 2012 Olympic cauldron to the iconic UK Pavilion at the 2010 World Expo Shanghai \\u2014 taking in his update on the iconic red London bus along the way \\u2014 is the subject of a city exhibition.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/93a8d9f6778c3789018cfb1cc2534a73.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Renowned British designer Thomas Heatherwick, whose work ranges from his beautiful London 2012 Olympic cauldron to the iconic UK Pavilion at the 2010 World Expo Shanghai \\u2014 taking in his update on the iconic red London bus along the way \\u2014 is the subject of a city exhibition. \\u201CInside Heatherwick Studio,\\u201D currently running at The Power Station of Art, showcases the work of a designer widely considered among Britain\\u2019s most innovative. The touring exhibition organized by the British Council, curated by Kate Goodwin and designed by Heatherwick Studio, aims to offer unique insights into the ideas and experiments that go into realizing projects that span architecture, engineering, furniture, sculpture and product design. It features drawings, models, films and test pieces generated by speculative and built projects from the past 20 years. Established by Thomas Heatherwick in 1994, the London-based Heatherwick Studio has a 170-strong team. Heatherwick says his studio aims to finding innovative design solutions, with a dedication to artistic thinking and the latent potential of materials and craftsmanship in the fields of architecture, urban infrastructure, design and strategic thinking. Outstanding contribution Heatherwick is an Honorary Fellow of the Royal Institute of British Architects and senior Research Fellow at the Victoria and Albert Museum. He was awarded the Prince Philip Designers Prize in 2006 and the London Design Medal in recognition of his outstanding contribution to design in 2010. Exhibition highlights include process models and full-size construction pieces from Heatherwick Studio\\u2019s Learning Hub. This is his project for Nanyang Technological University in Singapore. The form and structure of the hub aim to generate a new learning environment with oval classrooms bringing students and teachers together. Twelve stacks of classrooms, interspersed with gardens, rise around a naturally ventilated central atrium. Also on display is a model of the UK\\u2019s Pavilion for the 2010 World Expo in Shanghai \\u2014 a cube made up of 60,000 7.5 meter acrylic rods. Some 250,000 seeds from Britain\\u2019s Millennium Seed Bank were placed in the end of the rods, creating a magical \\u201Cseed cathedral\\u201D inside. At the close of the Expo, these were distributed across the world. Another highlight is a model and film of the London 2012 Olympic cauldron. The cauldron features 204 copper pieces, one for each of the participating countries, carried in to the stadium by the teams during the opening ceremony.\",\"newstime\":\"1438068713\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-28\\/248.html\",\"tid\":\"248\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 25, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=160-680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People Ave 人民大道300号上海大剧院\",\"title\":\"Three masterpieces\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Don\\u2019t miss the Australian Ballet as they perform three ballet masterpieces. From classical technique, haunting and emotional storytelling and athletic movement, this mixed program highlights the diverse ability of the dancers as they bring these famous international works to life. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7c2a53b39350c94df360b221d886b3d3.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Don\\u2019t miss the Australian Ballet as they perform three ballet masterpieces. From classical technique, haunting and emotional storytelling and athletic movement, this mixed program highlights the diverse ability of the dancers as they bring these famous international works to life. The program will last 130 minutes and includes \\u201CSuite en Blanc,\\u201D \\u201CUnspoken Dialogues\\u201D and \\u201CIn the Upper Room.\\u201D \\u201CEvery inch of stage space, every bounce and jog, is rigorously calibrated, and the choreography demands from the dancers something akin to Olympic perfection of form,\\u201D the New York Times said in a review. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1438068125\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-28\\/247.html\",\"tid\":\"247\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=October 23-24, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=180-680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People Ave 人民大道300号上海大剧院\",\"title\":\"Cinderella\\u2019 with a modern twist\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"After a 10-year absence, the Australian Ballet is returning this autumn with the award-winning smash-hit production of Alexei Ratmansky\\u2019s \\u201CCinderella.\\u201D \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/d64077b0d2e34d3fa3ce17bc4ad754ae.jpg\",\"remark\":\"After a 10-year absence, the Australian Ballet is returning this autumn with the award-winning smash-hit production of Alexei Ratmansky\\u2019s \\u201CCinderella.\\u201D Bubbling with humor and life, this production of a timeless fairy tale will bewitch all over again. Ratmansky, the most in-demand choreographer in the world and the master of the modern story ballet, fills every bar of Prokofiev\\u2019s cinematic score as he charts Cinderella\\u2019s journey from rags to  rapture. The vivid designs draw inspiration from Dior, Schiaparelli, the elegance of 1940s Hollywood, and Surrealist art. Join the acclaimed dancers of the Australian Ballet as classical takes a modern twist in one of the world\\u2019s favorite fairy tales. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1437719711\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-24\\/245.html\",\"tid\":\"245\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 9, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-280 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"title\":\"Asian Youth Orchestra puts spotlight on young talent\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The 100 members of the Asian Youth Orchestra are among the finest young musicians in China, Indonesia, Japan, South Korea, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/c52de0115f688c68e634f86d636018c7.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The 100 members of the Asian Youth Orchestra are among the finest young musicians in China, Indonesia, Japan, South Korea, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. Chosen through highly competitive auditions held throughout the region, they are together for six weeks  each summer, initially for a three-week rehearsal camp in Hong Kong, then for a three-week international concert tour. Cellists Yo-Yo Ma, Mischa Maisky, Steven Isserlis, Wang Jian and Alisa Weilerstein are among those who have performed with AYO under the direction of principal conductor James Judd.   \",\"newstime\":\"1437469082\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-21\\/244.html\",\"tid\":\"244\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 16, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=150-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd 上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"title\":\"Irish national choir plans a wonderful night of music\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Anúna Ireland National Choir is an Irish choral group. In 1987 Dublin composer Michael McGlynn founded An Uaithne, a name which describes the three ancient types of Celtic music,\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/0d01e02ed2346a85b327afd808f36c63.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Anúna Ireland National Choir is an Irish choral group. In 1987 Dublin composer Michael McGlynn founded An Uaithne, a name which describes the three ancient types of Celtic music, Suantraí (lullaby), Geantraí (happy songs) and Goltraí (lament). One of the group\\u2019s stated aims is to explore and redefine this music.   \",\"newstime\":\"1437468844\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-21\\/243.html\",\"tid\":\"243\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through August 23, 2015|Time=10am-6pm, closed on Mondays|Add=Shanghai Minsheng Art Museum, 570 Huaihai Rd 淮海西路570号，上海民生现代艺术馆\",\"title\":\"Work, Rest and Play: British Photography from the 1960s to Today\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The \\u201CWork, Rest and Play: British Photography from the 1960s to Today\\u201D exhibition reflects upon the changes that have occurred in British culture over the last half century.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/248c557749a0a67be3b73c91a2caa5ae.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The \\u201CWork, Rest and Play: British Photography from the 1960s to Today\\u201D exhibition reflects upon the changes that have occurred in British culture over the last half century. As part of the 2015 UK-China Year of Cultural Exchange, the exhibition is curated by The Photographers\\u2019 Gallery, London with Shanghai Minsheng Art Museum and the Cultural and Education Section of the British Consulate General in Shanghai acting as hosts. More than 400 images by 38 photographers and artists are on display. \\u201CThe show introduces the work of key figures who have contributed significantly to the development of the medium through the prism of documentary practices. While any exhibition of this kind cannot include everyone, this selection aims to highlight artists and photographers who, through their particular vision, enable us to understand the world in fresh and unexpected ways,\\u201D says Brett Rogers, director at The Photographers\\u2019 Gallery in London. Highlighting various approaches, from fashion and portraiture to photojournalism and fine art, the exhibit showcases the UK\\u2019s diversity. The dawn of the new millennium is a fascinating period in which Britain has experienced profound social and economic transformations. New technologies and the explosion of social media have changed how individuals communicate and how they express themselves. The wars in Afghanistan and Iraq, international terrorism, the financial crisis and globalization have been major events that have defined this new era. Photographers have traveled around the country observing these narratives and exploring the boundaries between the still and moving image. Their views often involve conceptual elements and tell contradictory stories ambiguously situated between fiction and fact. For example, Tim Walker\\u2019s fashion series evoked a fairytale-like world. The pleasurable escapism in the images comes across as more important than the clothes themselves. This new era is a stark contrast from the 1960s, when the country experienced numerous social and cultural changes. During the decade London became a center for music, fashion and a flourishing British art scene. Editorial photography dominated in magazines, as did professional studio portraiture \\u2014 evidence of the growing cult of celebrity within popular culture. Terence Donovan\\u2019s work had a playfulness that took fashion photography onto the street. Linda McCartney, married to the Beatles\\u2019 Paul McCartney, merged the public and the private to produce celebrity images that were almost like family snapshots. This new intimacy offered close look into the lives of famous people that viewers found appealing. By the 1970s, an economic recession had led to high unemployment. Numerous photographers became more politically conscious and socially engaged during this period. Some chose to point their lenses at declining industries and the people who were affected most. Photographers like Shirley Baker and Sirkka-Liisa Konttinen took an interest in working-class families and threatened communities in parts of England where traditional life was fading fast. Meanwhile, Vanley Burke focussed on ethnic minorities as they strived for equal rights. British society was defined by a new economy in the 1980s. Photographers once again showed a willingness to change with the times, dropping the documentary style in favor of satire. Martin Parr, a color photo pioneer, challenged the \\u201Cmythology of Britishness\\u201D with his satirical pictures of everyday life. The exhibition also looks at the rise of Britpop, Cool Britannia and the Girl Power phenomenon that dominated the 1990s. Portraying the young fans of the Spice Girls, Clare Strand\\u2019s images examine the vulnerable, preteen fans and contrast them with the stereotyped view of femininity embodied by their role models.\",\"newstime\":\"1437118755\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-17\\/242.html\",\"tid\":\"242\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 21, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"title\":\"A perfect combination of a cappella and comedy\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Bringing harmony across the world, B vocal(Spanish) perfectly combines comic theatre and a cappella music: i.e. music performed with no instrumental accompaniment, created through imitating the sounds of instruments with their voices. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/fbf1352b2362f93d4c689ee147095d32.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Bringing harmony across the world, B vocal(Spanish) perfectly combines comic theatre and a cappella music: i.e. music performed with no instrumental accompaniment, created through imitating the sounds of instruments with their voices. B vocal blends together a cappella music, humor and theatre. One of their great successes is to be able to captivate any type of audience regardless of age or nationality. These traits have allowed them to build a quality artistic career path, leading to national and international prestige. They performed in the international exhibition Zaragoza 2008 and in the Spanish Pavilion of the Universal Exhibition of Shanghai in 2010. Special mention should be made of the educational work in family and children\\u2019s concerts that b vocal have undertaken since 1998. Over a million children of all ages have been able to enjoy their diverse shows, which revolve around various aspects of music and voice.    \",\"newstime\":\"1437118532\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-17\\/241.html\",\"tid\":\"241\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 10-12, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=300-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theatre -Lyric Theatre，300 Renming Avenue 上海大剧院，人民大道300号；\",\"title\":\"Opera Die Zauberflote (Asia Premiere)\\u2014\\u2014A magical performance\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Opera \\u201CDie Zauberflöte,\\u201D or \\u201CThe Magic Flute,\\u201D presented by Komische Oper Berlin is coming this September. Since its establishment in 1892, Komische Oper Berlin has at various times been a consistent international trendsetter in the world of musical theater.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7b9d12214d4c12fa8e31f040ea11adc1.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Opera \\u201CDie Zauberflöte,\\u201D or \\u201CThe Magic Flute,\\u201D presented by Komische Oper Berlin is coming this September. Since its establishment in 1892, Komische Oper Berlin has at various times been a consistent international trendsetter in the world of musical theater. With immense, three-story spiders, flappers and demons, butterflies and  wolves \\u2014 this wildly inventive version of \\u201CThe Magic Flute\\u201D is like no other. It\\u2019s a perfect combination of all the things worth loving: silent movies, Weimar cabaret, David Lynch and the Brothers Grimm, according to a Guardian review.   Since arriving at the Komische Oper in 2012 Barrie Kosky has presided over a period of unprecedented success with the opera journal Opernwelt calling the Komische \'Opera House of the Year\' in 2013 and the International Opera Awards naming Kosky \'Director of the Year\' in 2014. Founded in 2005 by animator and illustrator Paul Barritt, and writer and performer Suzanne Andrade, 1927 has won critical and popular acclaim with works such as Between the Devil and the Deep Blue Sea and The Animals and Children Took to the Streets. \",\"newstime\":\"1436930013\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-15\\/240.html\",\"tid\":\"240\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 3-26, 2015|Time=2:30pm, 7:30pm|Tickets=200-2000yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=China Art Museum，205 Shangnan Rd 中华艺术宫，上南路205号\",\"title\":\"Cavalia trots and twirls its way into town\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The highly acclaimed Cavalia opened in Shanghai in July. Promising a galloping good time, Cavalia is a blend of equestrianism and performing arts like acrobatics.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/64a6b19ffacf879a89068b6576027f94.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The highly acclaimed Cavalia opened in Shanghai in July. Promising a galloping good time, Cavalia is a blend of equestrianism and performing arts like acrobatics. \\u201CThere is no other show like this in the world \\u2014 that\\u2019s why we have had such success so far,\\u201D says Normand Latourelle, who founded Cavalier in 2003 and remains its artistic director. \\u201CPeople in Shanghai are also going to see the amazement, see how beautiful the animals are.\\u201D Latourelle is renowned for his adventurous productions and is also one of the pioneers behind Cirque du Soleil. Cavalia, which features 40 horses, takes place at the White Theatre Tent next to China Art Museum. Not to be overshadowed by the horses, 40 riders, aerialists, acrobats, dancers and musicians from around the world will be a major part of the show. \\u201CCavalia is the biggest touring show in the world, including the logistics and performing arts,\\u201D Latourelle says. \\u201CThat\\u2019s a big challenge to bring such a big show from Canada to Shanghai. We are traveling with 100 containers of equipment. With 200 people working with me, and a talented local promoter, we finally made it possible. \\u201CWe are very proud of our horses, also the way we treat them. One of the key things to the success of Cavalia is \\u2018leave the horse, stay the horse,\\u2019 even though we have acrobatics flying, incredible music and 40 artists,\\u201D Latourelle adds. The show features 11 breeds including Spanish purebred, Percheron, Arabian, Lusitano, Warmblood and Quarter Horse. The animals are accompanied by a dedicated team of equine specialists. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1436929846\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-15\\/239.html\",\"tid\":\"239\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 21,2015|Time=8pm|Tickets=380-980yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Mercedes-Benz Arena, 1200 Shibo avenue 梅赛德斯奔驰文化中心，世博大道1200号\",\"title\":\"MUSE Live in Shanghai 2015\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"One of Britain\\u2019s biggest bands, MUSE are set to bring their spectacular, internationally-renowned live show to Shanghai for the first time on September 21 at Mercedes-Benz Arena. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/6bbb1fc313ee965ae4a0159798402cca.jpg\",\"remark\":\"One of Britain\\u2019s biggest bands, MUSE are set to bring their spectacular, internationally-renowned live show to Shanghai for the first time on September 21 at Mercedes-Benz Arena. This tour is presented by AEG Live. Having played some of the biggest stadiums and festivals in the world, MUSE have built a reputation for electrifying live shows and creating incredible spectacles on stage.   Formed in Devon in the mid-\\u201890s, MUSE\\u2019s early material was likened to Radiohead, and their debut album Showbiz \\u2013 which featured the hit singles \\u2018Sunburn\\u2019 and \\u2018Unintended\\u2019 \\u2013 was a critical and commercial success. Since then, the band have gone on to establish themselves as one of the leading lights of British rock music, with a string of hit albums. And the trio are sure to be on fine form as they hit China just months after the release of their highly-anticipated seventh studio album Drones.   Given the band\'s live credentials and the fact that their Mercedes-Benz Arena concert will come soon after the release of their hotly anticipated new album, MUSE\\u2019s first ever Shanghai date is set to be one of the shows of the year in Shanghai.   Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1436514713\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-10\\/238.html\",\"tid\":\"238\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:50\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through July 24, 2015|Time=10am-5pm|Tickets=Free|Add=111 Jinzhu Rd 金珠路111号\",\"title\":\"Contemporary Visions: Italian Artists in China\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Organized by Shanghai International Culture Association and the Garuzzo Institute for the Visual Arts, a group show titled \\u201CContemporary Visions: Italian Artists in China\\u201D casts the spotlight on some of the most significant experiences of the current crop of Italian artists.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/089798dfa64564028ffcffec3076d875.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Organized by Shanghai International Culture Association and the Garuzzo Institute for the Visual Arts, a group show titled \\u201CContemporary Visions: Italian Artists in China\\u201D casts the spotlight on some of the most significant experiences of the current crop of Italian artists. The exhibition encompasses a selection of works by 29 artists ranging from 25 to 50 years old. The exhibition involves multiple artistic expressions, such as drawing, painting, photography, installation, video and sculpture, demonstrating the feelings of contemporary Italian artists toward modern society. Click HERE to find more information about the exhibition.\",\"newstime\":\"1436323793\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-08\\/237.html\",\"tid\":\"237\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=September 14, 2015|Time=8pm|Tickets=480-3380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add:Mercerdes-Benz Arena, 1200 Expo Ave 世博大道1200号梅赛德斯奔驰文化艺术中心\",\"title\":\"Bon Jovi comes to Shanghai for first ever show\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Bon Jovi, one of the most important acts in the history of rock and roll is coming to Shanghai, for what promises to be one of the year\\u2019s most popular shows.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/4496e51b001d391a3d48a81f6266d0dc.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Bon Jovi, one of the most important acts in the history of rock and roll is coming to Shanghai, for what promises to be one of the year\\u2019s most popular shows. Bon Jovi will perform at Shanghai Mercedes-Benz Arena on September 14. The show will mark the band\\u2019s first ever trip to the city. In addition to the performance in Shanghai, Bon Jovi will also have two back-to-back performances in Macau on September 25 and 26 at Cotai Arena, The Venetian Macau. Bon Jovi has been one of the rock world\\u2019s most iconic acts for over three decades. The American legends, who have performed thousands of shows in more than 50 countries, promise to shake Shanghai with their spectacular show. Fans will be treated to an unforgettable night packed with classic Bon Jovi hits, including \\u201CLivin\\u2019 On A Prayer,\\u201D \\u201CYou Give Love A Bad Name,\\u201D \\u201CWho Says You Can\\u2019t Go Home,\\u201D \\u201CIt\\u2019s My Life\\u201D and many more. With over 130 million records sold, iconic frontman Jon Bon Jovi is recognized as one of the most talented singers in popular music.  For local rock fans, this concert is not to be missed. AEG Live, the live-entertainment division of Los Angeles-based AEG, is dedicated to all aspects of live contemporary music performance.  AEG Live is comprised of touring, festival, broadcast, merchandise and special event divisions. Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1436323436\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-08\\/236.html\",\"tid\":\"236\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 3-October 7, 2015|Time=10am-8pm|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Lafayette Arts & Design Center, 323 Fuxing Rd M. 拉法耶艺术设计中心，复兴中路323号\",\"title\":\"The Beatles, Tomorrow\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Fans of the Beatles and people who love the song \\u201CHey, Jude\\u201D should mark dates of July 3 to October 7 on your calendar as their idols are coming to Shanghai.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/8176799c26bec7633c986686a81910e8.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Fans of the Beatles and people who love the song \\u201CHey, Jude\\u201D should mark dates of July 3 to October 7 on your calendar as their idols are coming to Shanghai. An exhibition at the Lafayette Arts Center on Fuxing Road, \\u201CThe Beatles, Tomorrow,\\u201D will transport you back the 1960s. It is a tribute to all things Beatles and has been on a world tour with a stop in Taipei earlier this year. Visitors can see a large number of photos and personal items of the Beatle singers as well as more than 250 newspaper and magazine articles about the Fab Four -- Lennon, McCartney, Starr and Harrison. \\u201CThe Beatles, Tomorrow\\u201D show also features a reproduction of The Beatles\\u2019 first US television show and a reproduction of the famous Abbey Road album cover so you can act out that iconic scene with a little help from your friends. Well-known Shanghai radio DJs and bands will perform at the venue at night while food and wine will be served to bring The Beatles era back to life. Click HERE to buy the tickets!  \",\"newstime\":\"1435904778\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-03\\/235.html\",\"tid\":\"235\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 29-August 2, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=180-380 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People\\\\\'s Ave, near Huangpi Rd N. 上海大剧院，人民大道300号\",\"title\":\"It\\u2019s tough getting old\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"In a small room where memories are hung on the walls, Andre and Dorine live like many elderly couples, gently decaying from daily routines and neglect. Their passion for each other now fading into indifference. The couple desperately needs to remember who they were.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/8b8c3ce52d158a4011d3c5dca1e3cec1.jpg\",\"remark\":\"In a small room where memories are hung on the walls, Andre and Dorine live like many elderly couples, gently decaying from daily routines and neglect. Their passion for each other now fading into indifference. The couple desperately needs to remember who they were. Kulunka Teatro has created a piece of contemporary and committed mask theater that transcends language barriers. With no words, the story explores important themes with warmth and humor. \\u201CAndre and Dorine\\u201D has toured extensively in Spain, South America, the United States, United Kingdom and Europe. Now it is touring Asia. It was an award winner at the Birmingham European Theatre Festival in 2011, and at the La Habana International Theatre Festival 2011 (Cuba). Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1435904599\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-03\\/234.html\",\"tid\":\"234\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 30, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=160-680 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theater, 300 People\\\\\'s Ave, near Huangpi Rd N. 上海大剧院，人民大道300号\",\"title\":\"Famous poem adapted to ballet\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The Chinese poem \\u201CSong of Everlasting Sorrow,\\u201D based upon the legendary romance between Emperor Xuanzong of the Tang Dynasty (AD 618-907), and Yang Yuhuan, his beloved concubine, was adapted into music by Bai Juyi.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/fb9f8e615df54e2150104c0417e9a639.jpg\",\"remark\":\"The Chinese poem \\u201CSong of Everlasting Sorrow,\\u201D based upon the legendary romance between Emperor Xuanzong of the Tang Dynasty (AD 618-907), and Yang Yuhuan, his beloved concubine, was adapted into music by Bai Juyi. Shanghai Grand Theater and Shanghai Ballet have co-produced \\u201CBallet Echoes of Eternity,\\u201D based on the poem. Choreographer Patrick de Bana has contributed to \\u201CEchoes.\\u201D The poem reads: \\u201CIn heaven like a pair of lovebirds, we\\u2019d fly wing to wing; Or else on earth, as twain trees with their branches entwining. Endures the earth, endures the heaven, they shall wear away. This sorrow, however, shall endure forever and a day.\\u201D Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1435736811\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-01\\/233.html\",\"tid\":\"233\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 12, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Tickets=280-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall, 1380 Fuxing Rd M. 上交音乐厅，复兴中路1380号\",\"title\":\"\\u20182001\\u2019 score to be performed live\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Recognized as one of the greatest works of science fiction cinema, Stanley Kubrick\\u2019s \\u201C2001: A Space Odyssey\\u201D is acclaimed for its technological realism, creative audacity and inspired use of music. Now there\\u2019s a chance to watch the film while the soundtrack is performed live.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f70c035ca9b9b63da5deb45c6e35f3a6.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Recognized as one of the greatest works of science fiction cinema, Stanley Kubrick\\u2019s \\u201C2001: A Space Odyssey\\u201D is acclaimed for its technological realism, creative audacity and inspired use of music. Now there\\u2019s a chance to watch the film while the soundtrack is performed live. The screenplay was partially inspired by Arthur C. Clarke\\u2019s short story \\u201CThe Sentinel.\\u201D Clarke concurrently wrote the novel 2001: A Space Odyssey, published soon after the film was released. The film follows a voyage to Jupiter with the sentient computer Hal after the discovery of a mysterious monolith that affected human evolution.   Click HERE to buy the tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1435736339\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-07-01\\/232.html\",\"tid\":\"232\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 10, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Ticket=380,580 yuan|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall, 1380 Fuxin Rd M.复兴中路1380号上海交响乐团音乐厅\",\"title\":\"New York Philharmonic to perform in Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Alan Gilbert will conduct the New York Philharmonic at the Shanghai Symphony Hall on July 10. The concert will also feature the celebrated Canadian pianist, Emanuel Ax.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/883d3826d48475f2411b0d07a03d77e6.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Alan Gilbert will conduct the New York Philharmonic at the Shanghai Symphony Hall on July 10. The concert will also feature the celebrated Canadian pianist, Emanuel Ax. The New York Philharmonic is the oldest symphonic orchestra in the United States and one of the oldest in the world. It gives more than 180 performances a year in collaboration with world-famous conductors and composers. Alan Gilbert is the first native New Yorker to be appointed the music director of the New York Philharmonic in September 2009. He also appeared as guest conductor with the Berlin Philharmonic, Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra, Boston Symphony Orchestra and Orchestra Philharmonique de Radio France. Programs for the Shanghai concert include \\u201CPiano Concerto No. 14 in E-flat major\\u201D by Mozart and \\u201CSymphony No. 5 in C-sharp minor\\u201D by Gustav Mahler. Born in Poland and educated in the Juilliard School of New York City, Emanuel Ax is regarded one of the world\\u2019s most talented pianists. He regularly performs in New York City, Boston, Chicago, Cleveland, Philadelphia and Saint Louis.\",\"newstime\":\"1434016752\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/218.html\",\"tid\":\"218\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 7-9, 2015|Time=2pm, 7:15pm|Ticket=180-1000|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Culture Square, 597 Fuxing Rd M.上海文化广场，复兴中路597号\",\"title\":\"Diving into world of adventure\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The story is based on the classic book \\u201CAlice in Wonderland\\u201D by Lewis Carroll, but set in modern society. \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/12ac92ca766dde9e64429d2c8590d3a1.jpg\",\"remark\":\" The story is based on the classic book \\u201CAlice in Wonderland\\u201D by Lewis Carroll, but set in modern society.  Ordinary guy Mr B has a busy life, filled with stresses enhanced by smart phones, tablet PCs and other gadgets that bring convenience but take us further from reality. After another long day, Mr B finds himself transported as if by magic to a special, colorful, happy place called Bubblelandia. The \\u201Cinhabitants\\u201D of Bubblelandia \\u2014 seahorses, dragon fish, starfish, mermaids, clown fish and others \\u2014 carry Mr B along in an adventure in this underwater mystery world where fantasy becomes reality. Produced by Brinum-X Entertainment, it combines drama, mime, dance, puppetry, juggling, contortionist, sand art and magic, with various stage effects adopting the  latest laser technologies, snow cannons, soap bubble tornadoes, theatrical fog, gigantic smoke rings, smoke-filled soap bubbles and optical illusions.\",\"newstime\":\"1434016687\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/219.html\",\"tid\":\"219\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 22， 2015|Time=8pmTicket=400-1800 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Hongkou Stadium, 444 Jiangwan Rd E.虹口体育场，东江湾路444号\",\"title\":\"Linkin Park 2015 China Tour Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The tickets for this concert are pre-sale tickets. We will deliver the tickets to you in June after you book the tickets online. The tickets are limited! Only 10 tickets are available!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3adcf3275f885e2f39dbf86cc2e57efd.jpg\",\"remark\":\" The tickets for this concert are pre-sale tickets. We will deliver the tickets to you in June after you book the tickets online. The tickets are limited! Only 10 tickets are available!   American rock band Linkin Park is heading to China again in July as part of its ongoing international tour. The band is scheduled to perform on July 22 at the Hongkou Football Stadium. Additional Chinese shows are slated for Nanjing (Jiangsu Province, July 17), Shenzhen (Guangdong Province, July 19), Chongqing (July 24) and Beijing (July 26). \\u201CWe\\u2019re honored to be headlining these five stadium dates and reuniting with our amazing fans in China,\\u201D said Mike Shinoda, one of the lead vocalists, in an official statement. The rockers are currently touring in support of their sixth studio album, \\u201CThe Hunting Party,\\u201D which was released in June 2014. The new album is the band\\u2019s first self-produced endeavor, as well as their first to rely heavily on minimally altered analog tape recording. In their own words, the newest record grew out of \\u201Ca hunger for a sound that we don\\u2019t hear anyone else making.\\u201D The upcoming China dates will mark Linkin Park\\u2019s third appearance in the country. They first performed in Shanghai in 2007 and then returned to the city in 2009. As a long-time Linkin Park fan, Shanghai native Chara Wu is excited about the new album and the concert in July. The 29-year-old attended the band\\u2019s last show in the city and still remembers every thrilling moment. \\u201CI had a really great time that night,\\u201D recalls Wu. \\u201CAll the fans were jumping and dancing, and then everybody started singing along when they performed \\u2018In the End\\u2019.\\u201D Linkin Park has built an immense following in China over the years among listeners like Wu. \\u201CTheir music is part of the memory of our generation. We grew up listening to them. We saw the band change over the years and fans would very much like to relive the exciting experience they had when they were young.\\u201D As one of the most successful rock bands of all time, Linkin Park has sold over 50 million albums worldwide and was the first rock band to achieve more than 1.9 billion views on YouTube. In 2005, the band founded Music For Relief, a non-profit organization dedicated to providing aid to victims of natural disasters. It recently announced a partnership with Rock in Rio as the legendary festival gears up for the launch of its first-ever event in the US later this month. The event will raise funds for reforestation efforts in areas affected by wildfires in California.\",\"newstime\":\"1434016425\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/217.html\",\"tid\":\"217\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 15-16, 2015|Time=7:30pm, 2:30pm|Tickets=180-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Children\\\\\'s Theatre, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"title\":\"Percussion Concert Drumblebee\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"In this musical for young audiences, four percussionist- explorers, who come from another century, are trying to catch the moon \\u2014 despite the weight of their instruments.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/abaa859599e87a46ad48480e845425de.jpg\",\"remark\":\"In this musical for young audiences, four percussionist- explorers, who come from another century, are trying to catch the moon \\u2014 despite the weight of their instruments.  From Steve Reich to Goran Bregovic, through the Flight of the Bumblebee by Rimsky-Korsakov and an unrecognizable Ravel\\u2019s Bolero, Drumblebee is a  show of virtuosity staged by Dan Tanson, who creates a world where gravity, lights and music merge to become one. It has won such top prizes as the Audience Prize of the Young Audience Music Awards in Brussels and the Special Prize of the Jury of the Berlin Junge Ohren for its \\u201CDrumblebee\\u201D show.  The show also won prizes in both Art Basel and the Berlin Festival in 2012. Moreover, performers Quatuor Beat has become one of the most popular educational ensembles for Children\\u2019s Music in Europe.\",\"newstime\":\"1434016305\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/216.html\",\"tid\":\"216\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 16, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Ticket=280, 380 yuan|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall, 1380 Fuxin Rd M.复兴中路1380号上海交响乐团音乐厅\",\"title\":\"\\\\\'The Matrix\\u2019 concert\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Music in the 1999 sci-fi action film \\\\\\\"The Matrix\\\\\\\" will be performed in a concert at Shanghai Symphony Hall on July 16 as part of the Shanghai Summer Music Festival.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/decb027cf798b1b25f8552e8ce92f8de.jpg\",\"remark\":\" Music in the 1999 sci-fi action film \\\"The Matrix\\\" will be performed in a concert at Shanghai Symphony Hall on July 16 as part of the Shanghai Summer Music Festival. The American-Australian film is famous for sound tracks composed and directed by Donald Romain Davis, who also produced music for BBC documentaries \\u201CBlue Planet,\\\" \\\"Frozen Planet\\\" and \\\"Planet Earth.\\\" The Hangzhou Philharmonic Orchestra, founded in 2007, will present the concert. Its 80 musicians are graduates from distinguished music conservatories in China and abroad.\",\"newstime\":\"1434016300\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/215.html\",\"tid\":\"215\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:48:51\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=August 14-16, 2015|Time=7:15pm|Ticket=80-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center, 425 Dingxiang Rd上海东方艺术中心，丁香路425号\",\"title\":\"\\\\\'Murmurs\\\\\' to hit stage in Shanghai\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"The timeless charms of Charlie Chaplin are brought to life in the fantasy stage-show \\u201CMurmurs\\u201D \\u2014 also known as \\u201CWhat the Walls are Saying\\u201D \\u2014 a work created by the famed silent actor\\u2019s talented granddaughter, dancer and acrobat Aurelia Thierree.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/3f2ec9c949ad80f8ed9a12c8b0ee57c2.jpg\",\"remark\":\" The timeless charms of Charlie Chaplin are brought to life in the fantasy stage-show \\u201CMurmurs\\u201D \\u2014 also known as \\u201CWhat the Walls are Saying\\u201D \\u2014 a work created by the famed silent actor\\u2019s talented granddaughter, dancer and acrobat Aurelia Thierree. The humorous and sentimental show has been described as a modern-day \\u201CAlice in Wonderland\\u201D by critics. Audiences around the world have already been delighted by this fantastic and visually stunning stage experience, which combines dance, acrobatics, magic and mime. Thierree plays a curious woman who wanders through a world of illusion, where rooms filled with various ordinary objects magically come alive or transform into fantastical creatures. Since the show\\u2019s debut in the UK back in 2011, \\u201CMurmurs\\u201D has been performed in more than 20 countries and regions. To date, the show has been staged over 1,000 times. In the eyes of Thierree, walls protects people\\u2019s privacy while also witnessing the joys and sorrows of their human inhabitants. She uses walls as metaphors for the sometimes fragile human world as well as our own inner emotional barriers.\",\"newstime\":\"1434015987\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-06-11\\/214.html\",\"tid\":\"214\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:50:07\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=July 3-5, 2015|Time=7:30pm|Ticket=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Childrens Drama Theater, 800 Miaojiang Rd 上海儿童艺术剧场，苗江路800号\",\"title\":\"Dora\\u2019s Pirate Adventure (English and Chinese versions)\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"ftitle\":\"Dora\\u2019s Pirate Adventure incorporates the interactive and educational elements that make Dora the Explorer one of the most popular shows on television.Like its TV shows,live shows of Dora the Explorer brings enjoyment to kids and their families.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/1431502194253565066.jpg\",\"remark\":\" Dora\\u2019s Pirate Adventure incorporates the interactive and educational elements that make Dora the Explorer one of the most popular shows on television.Like its TV shows,live shows of Dora the Explorer brings enjoyment to kids and their families. Join Dora and the rest of her friends in Dora\\u2019s Pirate Adventure as they embark on an exciting trip to Treasure Island in search of the ultimate pirate party. Help them navigate over Dancing Mountain and through Silly Singing Bridge in pursuit of the Pirate Piggies. Along the way, Dora the Explorer fans will use their map-reading, counting, musical and language skills to successfully help Dora reach Treasure Island and avoid that pesky fox Swiper!     Type | Musical Duration | 70mins Age | 2-8 Director | Theresa Borg Producer | Nickelodeon、Life Like Touring Performance | Life Like Touring       The following sessions are performed in English: 3:30pm on July 3, 3:30pm on July 4, 10:30am on July 5. The other sessions are performed in Chinese. \",\"newstime\":\"1432622315\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-05-26\\/164.html\",\"tid\":\"164\"}]', '2016-9-21 7:50:07', '2016-9-21 7:50:07');
INSERT INTO `tbl_data` VALUES ('105', '7', '{\"createtime\":\"2016-9-21 7:50:07\",\"remark\":\"sh\",\"velocity\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/road\\/velocity.jpg\",\"intercity\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/road\\/intercity.jpg\",\"city\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/road\\/city.jpg\"}', '2016-9-21 7:50:07', '2016-9-21 7:50:07'), ('106', '1', '{\"lblpp\":\"PM<sub>2.5<\\/sub>\",\"createtime\":\"2016-10-17 10:27:56\",\"nD\":\"60\",\"remark\":\"sh\",\"color\":\"#FC0\",\"lblND\":\"43.2μg\\/m<sup>3<\\/sup>\",\"image\":\"002.png\",\"flbltime\":\"17日下午\",\"method\":\"极少数异常敏感人群应减少户外活动\",\"aq\":\"良\",\"health\":\"空气质量可接受，但某些污染物可能对极少数异常敏感人群健康有较弱影响\",\"flblcontent\":\"优到良\",\"aqi24hr\":\"74，良\"}', '2016-10-17 10:27:56', '2016-10-17 10:27:56'), ('107', '3', '[{\"r_time\":\"2016\\/10\\/17 10:00:36\",\"image\":\"9647970195.JPG\",\"switch\":\"1\",\"sSD\":\"舒适\",\"code\":\"1\",\"type\":\"正常\",\"info\":\"上海东方明珠广播电视塔（简称\\u201C东方明珠\\u201D）于1994年10月18日正式对外营业，总投资8.3亿元。 东方明珠坐落于上海黄浦江畔、浦东陆家嘴嘴尖，卓然秀立于陆家嘴地区现代化建筑楼群，与隔江的外滩万国建筑博览群交相辉映，展现了上海作为国际大都市的壮观景色。设计者富于想象地将十一个大小不一、高低错落的球体从蔚蓝的天空串联到绿色如茵的草地上，远处看宛如两颗红宝石的巨大球体，晶莹夺目，描绘了一幅\\u201C大珠小珠落玉盘\\u201D的如梦画卷。东方明珠集都市观光、时尚餐饮、购物娱乐、历史陈列、浦江游览等多功能于一体，已成为上海的标志性建筑和旅游热门景点之一，被列入上海十大新景观，是全国首批5A级旅游景区。了解上海，从东方明珠开始。东方明珠热忱欢迎您的光临！网址：www.orientalpearltower.com        咨询电话：021-58791888\",\"startTime\":\"08:00\",\"location_y\":\"31.245099\",\"location_x\":\"121.506377\",\"time\":\"2016-10-17 10:30:00\",\"num\":\"763\",\"rank\":\"5A\",\"end_time\":\"21:30\",\"county\":\"浦东新区\",\"initial\":\"DFMZGBDST\",\"name\":\"东方明珠广播电视塔\",\"maxNum\":\"15000\"},{\"r_time\":\"2016\\/10\\/17 10:17:28\",\"image\":\"图片111111_20160302080923201.png\",\"switch\":\"1\",\"sSD\":\"舒适\",\"code\":\"2\",\"type\":\"正常\",\"info\":\"上海野生动物园是由上海市人民政府和原国家林业部合作建设，集野生动物饲养、展览、繁育保护、科普教育与休闲娱乐为一体的主题公园。景区于1995年11月18日正式对外开放，地处上海浦东新区，占地153公顷（约2300亩），是2007年国家旅游局评定的5A级旅游景区。        园内汇集着世界各地具有代表性的动物和珍稀动物二百余种，上万余头（只），有我国珍稀保护动物：大熊猫、金丝猴、金毛羚牛、朱鹮等，还有来自国外的长颈鹿、斑马、羚羊、白犀牛、猎豹等。         联系电话：021-61180000\",\"startTime\":\"08:00\",\"location_y\":\"31.05928\",\"location_x\":\"121.723586\",\"time\":\"2016-10-17 10:30:00\",\"num\":\"1769\",\"rank\":\"5A\",\"end_time\":\"17:00\",\"county\":\"浦东新区\",\"initial\":\"SHYSDWY\",\"name\":\"上海野生动物园\",\"maxNum\":\"60000\"},{\"r_time\":\"2016\\/10\\/17 10:28:53\",\"image\":\"\",\"switch\":\"1\",\"sSD\":\"舒适\",\"code\":\"3\",\"type\":\"闭园\",\"info\":\"上海科技馆 上海科技馆主馆占地面积6.8万多平方米，建筑面积9.8万平方米，分为11个风格各异的主题展区、4个高科技特种影院、3个古今中外科学家及其足迹的艺术长廊、2个主题特展和若干个临时展厅，它们共同为四方游客生动地演绎着\\u201C自然、人、科技\\u201D的永恒话题。\",\"startTime\":\"09:00\",\"location_y\":\"31.224219\",\"location_x\":\"121.54785\",\"time\":\"2016-10-17 10:30:00\",\"num\":\"0\",\"rank\":\"5A\",\"end_time\":\"17:15\",\"county\":\"浦东新区\",\"initial\":\"SHKJG\",\"name\":\"上海科技馆\",\"maxNum\":\"13500\"},{\"r_time\":\"2016\\/10\\/17 10:21:13\",\"image\":\"\",\"switch\":\"1\",\"sSD\":\"舒适\",\"code\":\"4\",\"type\":\"正常\",\"info\":\"上海自然博物馆（上海科技馆分馆）座落于上海市静安雕塑公园内，建筑面积45,257 平方米，展览教育服务面积32,200 平方米，预计年接待观众80-120万人次，将成为上海市重要的科普教育基地和公众社会文化交流平台。\",\"startTime\":\"09:00\",\"location_y\":\"31.241294\",\"location_x\":\"121.469083\",\"time\":\"2016-10-17 10:30:00\",\"num\":\"0\",\"rank\":\"\",\"end_time\":\"17:15\",\"county\":\"静安区\",\"initial\":\"SHZRBWGSHKJGFG\",\"name\":\"上海自然博物馆（上海科技馆分馆）\",\"maxNum\":\"5900\"},{\"r_time\":\"2016\\/10\\/17 10:25:16\",\"image\":\"730966348.jpg\",\"switch\":\"1\",\"sSD\":\"舒适\",\"code\":\"5\",\"type\":\"正常\",\"info\":\"上海博物馆是一座中国古代艺术博物馆，筹建于1950年，原址在旧跑马总会，1959年10月迁入旧中汇大楼。上海博物馆新馆位于上海市中心人民广场，于1996年10月12日全面建成开放。建筑总面积39200平方米，高29.5米，象征\\u201C天圆地方\\u201D的圆顶方体基座构成了新馆不同凡响的视觉效果。上海博物馆目前设有十一个专馆，分门类展出青铜、雕刻、陶瓷、书法、绘画、玺印、钱币、中国少数民族工艺、玉器和明清家具。还设有三个特别展览厅，不定期引进国内外艺术精品展。    上海博物馆拥有馆藏文物100余万件，其中珍贵文物14万件，包括青铜器、陶瓷器、书法、绘画、玉牙器、竹木漆器、甲骨、玺印等 21个门类，尤以青铜器、陶瓷器、书法、绘画为特色。藏品之丰富、质量之精湛，在国内外享有盛誉。地址：上海市黄浦区人民大道201号开放时间：9:00-17:00（16:00停止入场）景区咨询联系电话：63723500上海博物馆实时信息常态发布工作从2015年10月1日起正式开始。\",\"startTime\":\"09:00\",\"location_y\":\"31.234223\",\"location_x\":\"121.48204\",\"time\":\"2016-10-17 10:30:00\",\"num\":\"604\",\"rank\":\"