1a Buniatishvili\",\"ftitle\":\"Khat1a Buniatishvili will hold a concert at the Shanghai Oriental Art Center on March 18.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/5aa6c4f0ebceaf7f62f79899e1e721e6.jpg\",\"remark\":\"\",\"newstime\":\"1452235881\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.comhttp:\\/\\/www.idealshanghai.com\\/goods\\/2172\\/\",\"tid\":\"315\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Jan 8-Feb 28, 20166 |Time=10am-8pm |Tickets=70-320 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Super Brand Mall\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"HARRY POTTER™: THE EXHIBITION in Shanghai\",\"ftitle\":\"In this amazing exhibition, guests will get an up close and personal look at the artistry and craftsmanship that went into creating the iconic props and costumes that appeared throughout the Harry Potter™ films. These authentic artifacts will be displayed in elaborate settings inspired by locations from Hogwarts™ School of Witchcraft and Wizardry including the Gryffindor™ common room, Hagrid\\u2019s hut and the Great Hall.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/e5c0d60fb9615be30330fae5d2fa573c.jpg\",\"remark\":\"\",\"newstime\":\"1452235603\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.comhttp:\\/\\/www.idealshanghai.com\\/goods\\/2171\\/\",\"tid\":\"314\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through Mar 20, 2016 |Time=10am-6 pm |Tickets=50-220 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Himalayas Museum\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Dunhuang: Song of Living Beings\",\"ftitle\":\"THE very best of the famed Mogao Grottoes are in town, and with it the fabled tale of Ruru the deer.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/621f52a1ca01040e3bdaccac196d97ff.jpg\",\"remark\":\"\",\"newstime\":\"1452235042\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.comhttp:\\/\\/www.idealshanghai.com\\/goods\\/2173\\/\",\"tid\":\"313\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Jan 30, 2016 |Time=7:15pm|Tickets=180-880 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Grand Theatre -Lyric Theatre\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"THE GREAT GATSBY by Northern Ballet Britain\",\"ftitle\":\"By Northern Ballet Britain, \\\\\\\"THE GREAT GATSBY\\\\\\\"  will be staged at the Shanghai Grand Theatre at the end of next month.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7f6ecec5c89800d646662fdb982e72e0.jpg\",\"remark\":\"By Northern Ballet Britain, \\\"THE GREAT GATSBY\\\"  will be staged at the Shanghai Grand Theatre at the end of next month. The story ballet tells a story about the heady, indulgent days of the roaring 1920s  on New York\\u2019s Long Island where a young Midwesterner Nick Carraway meets his infamous neighbour Jay Gatsby \\u2013 a mysterious millionaire with a secret past and a penchant for lavish parties. As the sparkling facade of Gatsby\\u2019s world begins to slip, Carraway comes to see the loneliness, obsession and tragedy that lie beneath.     Choreographed by David Nixon the dancers glide across the floor in gorgeous Chanel-inspired costumes to a sweeping, filmic score by Sir Richard Rodney Bennett CBE (Four Weddings and a Funeral, Murder on the Orient Express). Bursting with passion, style and drama, this blockbuster ballet comes for two performances in Shanghai Grand Theatre and three performances in NCPA only.   \\\"You will leave the theatre with a warm glow and a smile\\\" Sunday Express \\\"Nixon\\u2019s choreography really flies\\\" The Guardian     HERE to buy tickets\",\"newstime\":\"1451543920\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-31\\/312.html\",\"tid\":\"312\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Apr 08, 2016 |Time=8pm|Tickets=180-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall - Concert Hall\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Sir Andrew Davis &Melbourne Symphony Orchestra\",\"ftitle\":\"Melbourne Symphony Orchestra is coming to Shanghai soon! \",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/1cbacb979e670a6631169468d9b9b573.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Melbourne Symphony Orchestra is coming to Shanghai soon! The Melbourne Symphony Orchestra (MSO) is an orchestra based in Melbourne, Australia. It has 100 permanent musicians. Melbourne has the longest continuous history of orchestral music of any Australian city and the MSO is the oldest professional orchestra in Australia. The MSO performs to more than 200,000 people in Melbourne and regional Victoria in over 150 concerts a year. Following integration with the Melbourne Chorale in 2008, the Orchestra has responsibility for its own choir, the MSO Chorus. The orchestra relies on funding by the Victorian State Government through Arts Victoria, Department of Premier and Cabinet and the Federal governmentthrough the Australia Council and support from private corporations and donors. It is supported by Symphony Services International. HERE to buy tickets!\",\"newstime\":\"1451542847\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-31\\/311.html\",\"tid\":\"311\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Through February 15, 2016 |Time=10am-8pm |Tickets=120 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Chi K11 Art Space, 300 Huaihai Rd M.\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"The Major Exhibition-\\\\\'Media - Dalí\\\\\'\",\"ftitle\":\"An exhibition of Salvador Dali, \\u201CMedia \\u2014 Dali\\u201D will be held in Shanghai K11 Art Mall from November 5 to February 15.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/7bfc6c04e5d3ba5ef311f14d61d9cf72.jpg\",\"remark\":\"An exhibition of Salvador Dali, \\u201CMedia \\u2014 Dali\\u201D will be held in Shanghai K11 Art Mall from November 5 to February 15.   Born on May 11, 1904, in Spain, Dali is best known for his adventurous life. He is talented and unique. His fiercely technical yet highly unusual paintings, sculptures and visionary explorations in film and life-size interactive art ushered in a new generation of imaginative expression. As a great master in Surrealism, Dalí is considered one of the three most important Spanish artists along with Pablo Picasso and Joan Miro. The K11 Art Foundation and Gala-Salvador Dali Foundation will collaborate closely on the Surrealist exhibition at Shanghai K11 Art Mall. The two will also promote his works in China in other platforms, including new media, seminars and forums. It is expected to create new dialogues on surrealism and the role of contemporary art in Chinese society.  Click HERE to buy tickets!  \",\"newstime\":\"1451542563\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-31\\/310.html\",\"tid\":\"310\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=Jan 31, 2016 |Time=8:30pm |Tickets=From 280yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=179 Yichang Rd, QSW Culture Center\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Gigi D\\\\\'Alessio Malaterra World\",\"ftitle\":\"CICC is delighted to announce that Gigi D\\\\\'Alessio Malaterra World tickets are on sale!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f7f487c67fcc10fd41b33c65a66fd8a6.jpg\",\"remark\":\"CICC is delighted to announce that Gigi D\'Alessio Malaterra World tickets are on sale!   Join us with your family and friends on January 31st at Shanghai QSW Culture Center, enjoy the singer reinterpreting the classics of the Neapolitan music and performing his masterpieces. Part of the proceeds will be donated to the ONLUS \\\"Terra dei Cuori.\\\" For more info and RSVP please write to malaterra@cameraitacina.com\",\"newstime\":\"1451542062\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-31\\/309.html\",\"tid\":\"309\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=April 24, 2016 |Time=8:00pm|Tickets=580-1080 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall \",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Rudolf Buchbinder&Staatskapelle Dresden\",\"ftitle\":\"Rudolf Buchbinder, who is firmly established as one of the world\\\\\'s foremost pianists, is invited by famous german  Orchestra Staatskapelle Dresden to perform at  Shanghai Symphony Hall!\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/1d8adbd6a4fadab6425f6d4d1f7b286a.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Rudolf Buchbinder, who is firmly established as one of the world\'s foremost pianists, is invited by famous german  Orchestra Staatskapelle Dresden to perform at  Shanghai Symphony Hall! His comprehensive repertoire encompasses numerous 20th century compositions.  Vienna Academy of Music. In 1965 he made a tour of North and South America. In 1966 he won a special prize awarded at the Van Cliburn International Piano Competition. Subsequently he has toured with the Vienna Philharmonic and appeared as soloist around the world. He has also taught piano at the Basel Academy of Music. In 2009, Buchbinder was featured in the award-winning German-Austrian documentary Pianomania, about a Steinway & Sons piano tuner, which was directed by Lilian Franckand Robert Cibis. The film premiered theatrically in North America, where it was met with positive reviews by The New York Times. HERE to buy tickets!  \",\"newstime\":\"1450943876\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-24\\/308.html\",\"tid\":\"308\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=March 2, 2016|Time=8:00 pm|Tickets=180-580 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Symphony Hall\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Ian Bostridge& Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment\",\"ftitle\":\"Joined by  British period instrument  Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment, the  well-known London tenor Ian Bostridge will perform at Shanghai Symphony Hall on March, 2016.\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/f16b70a0d743f9e31d0df43768f74dde.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Joined by  British period instrument  Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment, the  well-known London tenor Ian Bostridge will perform at Shanghai Symphony Hall on March, 2016.   Bostridge only began singing professionally at age 27 and made his Wigmore Hall debut in 1993; his Purcell Room debut (an acclaimed Winterreise) and his Aldeburgh Festival debut in 1994; in 1995 he gave his first solo recital in the Wigmore Hall (winning the Royal Philharmonic Society\'s Debut Award); in 1996 he gave recitals inLyon, Cologne, London and at the Aldeburgh, Cheltenham and Edinburgh Festivals, and in 1997 at the Alte Oper, Frankfurt.     HERE to buy tickets.\",\"newstime\":\"1450943580\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-24\\/307.html\",\"tid\":\"307\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:17\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=January 13, 2016 |Time=7:30pm|Tickets=80-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Center\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"The Romantic Harp Recital by Xavier de Maistre\",\"ftitle\":\"The Romantic Harp Recital by Xavier de Maistre is coming to Shanghai next month\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/2d7600fefb706c935a3ea0604598291d.jpg\",\"remark\":\"Xavier de Maistre was born in Toulon and began to study harp at the age of nine. He finished his studies with Catherine Michel and Jacqueline Borot in Paris. In 1998 he was awarded the first prize at the prestigious International Harp Competition in Bloomington, Indiana. He immediately became the first French musician to join the ranks of the prestigious Vienna Philharmonic Orchestra \\u2013 a position which he left in summer 2010.     Xavier de Maistre belongs to an elite category category of soloists who are redefining what is possible with their instrument. Aside from new commissions from composers such as Krzysztof Penderecki and Kaija Saariaho, he performs works like Smetana\\u2019s \\u201CMa Vlast\\\" with breathtaking precision, presenting masterful arrangements of works that are usually played by an entire orchestra. The interpretation of these works, that few harpists before him have even considered playing, has contributed to his reputation as one of the most creative and extraordinary musicians of his generation. Xavier de Maistre has appeared with major orchestras under the direction of such eminent conductors as Bertrand de Billy, Daniele Gatti, Kristjan Järvi, Philippe Jordan, Riccardo Muti, Andrés Orozco-Estrada, André Previn, Simon Rattle, Heinrich Schiff and Gilbert Varga. He performs at many of Europe\\u2019s leading festivals, including Schleswig-Holstein, Salzburg, Rheingau, Vienna and Verbier, the Budapest Spring Festival and the Wurzburg Mozart Festival. He collaborates with such chamber music partners as Diana Damrau, Mojca Erdmann, Daniel MüllerSchott, Baiba Skride, Arabella Steinbacher and Magali Mosnier.   Orchestral highlights of the 2013\\/14 season include an extensive tour with the Academy of St Martin in the Fields, performances with NHK Symphony Orchestra, Vienna Symphony Orchestra, tour concerts with Basel Chamber Orchestra and debuts with Helsinki Philharmonic, Royal Liverpool Philharmonic and Malmo Symphony Orchestras. The season concludes with the world premiere of a new concerto by Krzysztof Penderecki, reuniting de Maistre with Orchestre de Paris. De Maistre will also give solo recitals as far afield as Shanghai, Macao and Montreal and appears in duo performances with Diana Damrau at Schubertiade, Grafenegg and Istanbul Festivals, at the Munich Opera Festival (Bayerische Staatsoper) and London\\u2019s Wigmore Hall.   In 2008 Xavier de Maistre signed an exclusive contract with Sony Music. Releases so far have included music by Haydn, Rodrigo, Ginastera and Debussy \\u2013 the latter for which he was awarded the Echo Klassik Award 2009 as \\\"Instrumentalist of the Year\\\". In 2012 \\u201CNotte Veneziana\\u201D, a recording of baroque concertos with the Ensemble l\\u2019arte del mondo, was released. Highly acclaimed by the press, \\u201CNotte Veneziana\\u201D entered the top ten in the classical music charts. His latest releases include a DVD with Diana Damrau and a CD recording of Mozart piano concertos arranged for harp, with Mozarteum Salzburg and conductor Ivor Bolton.   Since 2001 Xavier de Maistre has taught at the Hamburg Academy of Music. He also gives regular masterclasses at New York\\u2019s Juilliard School of Music, Tokyo\\u2019s Toho University and London\\u2019s Trinity College of Music.   Click HERE to buy tickets.  \",\"newstime\":\"1450243647\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-16\\/305.html\",\"tid\":\"305\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:18\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=February 24, 2016-February 26, 2016 |Time=7:15 pm|Tickets=280-480 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Centre\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"Swan Lake by Imperial Russian Ballet in Shanghai\",\"ftitle\":\"Swan Lake by Imperial Russian Ballet will come to Shanghai\",\"titlepic\":\"\\/media\\/imgcache\\/SHLife\\/what\\/9fb8ddf872803b3e12e744bd030df880.jpg\",\"remark\":\"     The artists of the company increase their skills under famous ballet teachers: A. Bondarenko, E.Vlasova, A. Kudelin, N. Osipian.  The Imperial Russian Ballet company is a member of European Cultural Center in Moscow under patronize of European Parliament. Gedeminas Taranda is one of the founders of European Cultural Center.     HERE to buy tickets.  \",\"newstime\":\"1450236155\",\"titleurl\":\"http:\\/\\/act.shanghaicity.openservice.kankanews.com\\/iloveshanghai\\/what\\/on\\/2015-12-16\\/304.html\",\"tid\":\"304\"},{\"createtime\":\"2016-10-23 22:48:18\",\"smalltext\":\"Date=January 23，2016-January 24，2016|Time=7:15pm|Tickets=280-880 yuan|Phone=021-5292 0164|Add=Shanghai Oriental Art Centre\",\"keyboard\":\"\",\"title\":\"The Nutcracker by